f baseball -- players, fans, sportswriters, broadcasters, managers, coaches, scouts, groundkeepers, batboys, ballpark vendors, agents and the owners. Everybody is eagerly awaiting the first pitch of the game and the first home run. Old records will be broken and new marks set. It all gets under way today with this lineup of games:\n\n<Toledo Rainiers:team#18> @ <North Hempstead Knights:team#24>\n<Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> @ <Mannford Monsters:team#17>\n<Chandler Capitals:team#22> @ <Fort Wayne Blue Falcons:team#21>\n<Grand Rapids Blue Jackets:team#20> @ <Jersey City Wild Dogs:team#23>\n<Leesburg Privateers:team#26> @ <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32>\n<Tampa Brawlers:team#29> @ <Bakersfield Millionaires:team#27>\n<Fair Haven Earthquakes:team#25> @ <Donna Whitecaps:team#28>\n<Irving Badlanders:team#30> @ <Cypress Royals:team#31>\n"), (116, "League Punishes Pair for Fighting", 157, 1481, 0, 0, 0, 25, 28, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 25, 0, 0, "2022-4-12", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Adam Green:player#157> of <Fair Haven:team#25> and <Mel Sosa:player#1481> of <Donna:team#28> were the main participants in a recent bench-clearing brawl and today the league handed out its punishment. <Green:player#157> will have to miss 3 games for his part in the brawl, while <Sosa:player#1481> was given 7 games. League officials announced their suspensions today.\n\n\n\n"), (117, "Graham Kimball Plans to Retire", 750, 0, 0, 0, 0, 41, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-4-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "\"I can\'t play this game the way I could before,\" came the assessment from <Graham Kimball:player#750> today.\n\nA bleary-eyed Kimball told reporters that he was wrapping up his career at long last.\n\n\n\"I can tell when it\'s going to rain, my big toe always hurts the day before. And I spend hours after each game icing down my knees,\" he said. \"My joints ache and I\'m about sick to death of stinking like ointment at all hours trying to bounce back for the next game. Road trips seem twice as long nowadays. I want to spend each night in my own bed.\"\n\nReporters were surprised when they heard a litany of complaints from Kimball, who usually has an upbeat and pleasant personality in the clubhouse.\n\nAs the <Orlando:team#41> manager said, \"This boys game will make a man real old real quick. The daily grind, the marathon each season, it wears on your soul. Looks like Father Time caught up with Graham. I have nothing but respect for the guy.\"\n\n"), (118, "Fehnel Swats 3 Homers", 2225, 0, 0, 0, 0, 36, 35, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 36, 0, 0, "2022-4-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was a good day for the <Sparta Mavericks:team#36> and an exceptional one for <Perry Fehnel:player#2225>. The 22-year-old second baseman sent three bombs out of the park to help the Mavericks beat the <Buffalo Sluggers:team#35> 8-3 at Sluggers Grounds.\n\n\"When you\'re in the zone, the game really slows down,\" <Fehnel:player#2225> said when asked about his performance later. \"I couldn\'t even tell you what pitches were thrown. Today feels great, but it is a long season and tomorrow is another day.\"\n\nFor the day, he scored 3 times, drove in 4 runs and smacked 3 hits in 5 at-bats.\n\n<Perry Fehnel:player#2225> hit a solo-shot off <Scott Pottenger:player#1197> in the 2nd, hit a solo-shot off <Scott Pottenger:player#1197> in the 4th, grounded out in the 5th, hit a two-run home run off <Jonathan Keiser:player#608> in the 7th and struck out in the 8th.\n\n<Fehnel:player#2225> is swinging at a .458 pace on the year with 3 home runs, 5 RBIs and 4 runs scored. He has played in 6 games. \n"), (119, "Season-Ending Injury for Burt", 1385, 0, 0, 0, 0, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 25, 0, -5, "2022-4-14", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Kevin Burt:player#1385> had to wait several agonizing days to find out his diagnosis after suffering a torn labrum on 04/12/2022. Today he received word from the <Fair Haven:team#25> doctor that he would be out the rest of the year. Team officials called it a huge setback but something they would have to overcome.\n\n"), (120, "Red-Hot Modesto Scorches Razorbacks", 770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 46, 47, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 46, 0, 0, "2022-4-14", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It doesn\'t happen very often, but it did for <Rodolfo Modesto:player#770> today -- a 5-hit effort. He went on a rampage at Fighters Field and paced the Fighters to a 5-4 win over the <Pittsburgh Razorbacks:team#47>.\n\nAfter his dynamite batting performance, the <Corpus Christi:team#46> third baseman told reporters that he \"just tried to get in a good count and have a good at-bat. That\'s all I can control.\"\n\nHis philosophy paid dividends today. He slammed 5 hits in 5 tries and put his name in the record book. <Rodolfo Modesto:player#770> hit a solo-shot off <John Lettis:player#965> in the 1st, doubled in the 2nd, doubled in the 4th, singled in the 6th and singled in the 8th.\n\nSo far this season <Modesto:player#770> has hit .407 with 1 home run, 2 RBIs and scored 5 times.\n"), (121, "Rowdy Players Suspended by League", 1679, 1382, 0, 0, 0, 51, 56, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 51, 0, 0, "2022-4-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Baseball officials have suspended two players for \"inappropriate and aggressive conduct\" in yesterday\'s <Cincinnati:team#51>-<Madison:team#56> contest at Tropics Park. The Tropics <Jorge Trujillo:player#1679> and the Astros <Antonio Sandoval:player#1382> will have to sit out 5 and 3 games respectively for their parts in the brawl. \n\nThis year <Trujillo:player#1679> is hitting .139 with 5 hits, 1 home run, 3 RBIs and has scored 6 runs.\n\n"), (122, "Capitals Pitching Ravaged by Aguilar", 1661, 0, 0, 0, 0, 49, 55, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 49, 0, 0, "2022-4-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Atlanta Dingos:team#49> center fielder <Alex Aguilar:player#1661> wielded a big stick today against the <Kansas City Capitals:team#55> and his club walked off the field winners by the score of 10-6. Aguilar helped tame Kansas City with 5 hits in 5 at-bats. <Alex Aguilar:player#1661> singled in the 1st, singled in the 3rd, hit an RBI single in the 4th, walked in the 6th, hit an RBI single in the 8th and singled in the 9th.\n\nThus far this season in 5 games Aguilar is batting .538 with 1 home run, 4 RBIs and 3 runs scored. He has 7 hits in 13 at-bats.\n"), (123, "Free-for-All Costs Rodriguez and Diaz 5-Game Suspensions", 721, 1153, 0, 0, 0, 9, 14, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-4-17", 0, 1, -1, 0, "In an announcement today, the league informed <Andy Rodriguez:player#721> of <San Francisco:team#9> and <Carlos Diaz:player#1153> of <New York:team#14> that they both had been suspended 5 games for fighting in a recent game.\n\nThe league president told them, \"This type of aggressive behavior will not be tolerated in this league.\"\n\n<Rodriguez:player#721> wasn\'t happy with the length of his suspension. He thought he got the worst deal and told the league commissioner, \"In any fight, whoever throws the first punch should get a more severe penalty. If I threw the first punch, I\'d expect to get the most punishment. Whoever took the blow should get a lesser punishment.\"\n\nHis manager agreed with him and said something needs to be done about it. \"<Rodriguez:player#721> is right. The league needs to look at its policy and make sure the punishment fits the crime.\"\n\nTo date, <Rodriguez:player#721> has collected 9 hits for a .243 average. He has posted 2 home runs, scored 3 runs and driven in 7 runs.\n\n<Diaz:player#1153> has taken the mound for 7 relief appearances this season, nailing down no saves while notching a 1-0 record with a 6.00 ERA. The <New York:team#14> reliever has limited opposing batters to a .370 batting average.\n"), (124, "Red-Hot Rampage Reaps SL1 Reward", 301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 5, 0, 0, "2022-4-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "His hard work and hustle paid off this week. The hard-working and hard-playing <Dave Martinez:player#301> was rewarded with the Sub League 1 Player of the Week honors.\n\nThe scrappy <San Diego Fighting Knights:team#5> shortstop hit .375 while collecting 9 hits in 24 at-bats, 4 home runs and 9 RBIs.\n\n"), (125, "Week\'s #1 Player: San Francisco\'s Franco", 723, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-4-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "In the twilight of his career, 35-year-old <Willie Franco:player#723> of <San Francisco:team#9> recaptured some of the old magic last week and came away with the Sub League 2 Player of the Week Award.\n\n\"I\'ve been playing since I was a kid,\" <Franco:player#723> told reporters, \"but you\'re never too old to feel the thrill of success.\"\n\nFranco outpaced the rest of the league\'s hitters last week, reeling off 6 hits in 10 at-bats, 3 home runs, and 6 RBIs to stake his claim to the award.\n\n"), (126, "Beiting Wins SL1 Player of the Week Honors", 1350, 0, 0, 0, 0, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 21, 0, 0, "2022-4-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The #1 hitter in the Sub League 1 was <Fort Wayne:team#21> center fielder <Matt Beiting:player#1350>. He was selected the Player of the Week.\n\nDuring the week Beiting banged out a .476 batting average (10-for-21), 3 home runs, 7 runs batted in and scored 5 runs. \n\n"), (127, "Dominguez Honored by Sub League 2", 1272, 0, 0, 0, 0, 32, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 32, 0, 0, "2022-4-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Nick Dominguez:player#1272> of the Sioux City Apple Sox had a super week and today was voted the Player of the Week by the Sub League 2.\n\nThe 24-year-old left fielder put up a .333 average with a .370 on-base percentage, racking up 8 hits in 24 at-bats, 7 home runs, 18 RBIs and 8 runs scored. \n\n"), (128, "Player of the Week: Sparta\'s Fehnel", 2225, 0, 0, 0, 0, 36, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 36, 0, 0, "2022-4-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Today the Sub League 1 announced its Player of the Week Award winner -- <Sparta Mavericks:team#36> second baseman <Perry Fehnel:player#2225>, who batted .400 (12-for-30) with 6 home runs, 8 RBIs and 9 runs scored. \n\n"), (129, "SL2 Premier