n opponents batting AVG?\n\n<Mike Hagmeier:player#1300>, MOD,  .138\n<Luis Cervantes:player#1721>, KC,  .145\n<Anbessa Limas:player#1380>, MAD,  .146\n<Mario Lopez:player#1673>, CIN,  .152\n<Jordan Carrasco:player#2349>, DM,  .171\n"), (139, "MacBeth Batters Fort Wayne Big Time", 535, 0, 0, 0, 0, 20, 21, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 20, 0, 0, "2022-4-19", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Phil MacBeth:player#535> led <Grand Rapids:team#20> to a 8-7 victory today over the <Fort Wayne Blue Falcons:team#21>. He stroked 5 hits in 6 at-bats to spark his club in the win.\n\n<Phil MacBeth:player#535> hit an RBI single in the 1st, hit an RBI single in the 2nd, singled in the 5th, singled in the 7th, flied out in the 9th and hit an RBI single in the 11th. \n\nThis season <MacBeth:player#535> is hitting .333 with no home runs.\n"), (140, "League Punishes Pair for Fighting", 1108, 780, 0, 0, 0, 48, 41, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 48, 0, 0, "2022-4-19", 0, 1, -1, 0, "After an intense confrontation, both the Cheetahs <Carlos Rosa:player#1108> and the Schooners <Judah Byrdsong:player#780> were handed their punishments today. The league commissioner\'s office issued suspensions for an on-the-field conflict that occurred at a recent <Winston-Salem:team#48>-<Orlando:team#41> game. <Carlos Rosa:player#1108> will miss 4 games, while <Judah Byrdsong:player#780> was suspended for 6 games.\n\n\"Sometimes we go too far and have to pay the consequences,\" <Carlos Rosa:player#1108> commented later. \"Hopefully cooler heads will prevail the next time we play.\"\n\nThis season <Rosa:player#1108> has hit at a .150 clip with 2 RBIs, 0 home runs and 0 runs scored.\n\n"), (141, "Corpus Christi Loses Modesto for Season", 770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 46, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 46, 0, -5, "2022-4-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Rodolfo Modesto:player#770> had hoped for the best, but expected the worst. Today, he learned from the <Corpus Christi:team#46> medical staff that he would miss the rest of the season. The <Corpus Christi:team#46> third baseman suffered a fractured knee in an earlier ballgame. He admitted to being discouraged, but said he plans to come back strong next year.\n\nSo far this season <Modesto:player#770> is hitting .432 with 1 home run.\n"), (142, "Injury Update for St. Petersburg, Gonzalez", 564, 0, 0, 0, 0, 42, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 42, 0, -5, "2022-4-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The latest news from the <St. Petersburg Naturals:team#42> clubhouse is this: reliever <Rafael Gonzalez:player#564> is expected to be out of action for another 4 months. He has a torn labrum, sustained on 04/20/2022. Gonzalez expressed a bit of relief. \"At least now I know,\" he said.\n\nThis season <Gonzalez:player#564> has logged no saves. He has thrown 7 innings, dished out 8 strikeouts and walked 0 while putting up a 0-1 mark and a 2.57 ERA.\n"), (143, "Rainiers Campbell Hanging up His Spikes", 44, 0, 0, 0, 0, 18, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-4-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Flanked by his two young children, <Billy Campbell:player#44> said his reason for retirement is simple.\n\n\"I want to spend more time being a father now,\" the <Toledo Rainiers:team#18> reliever said in announcing that this season would be his last in pro baseball. \"I\'m 40 years old now, I think it\'s a good time to go.\"\n\n"), (144, "Big Bang! 3 HR for San Francisco\'s Hernandez", 726, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 13, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-4-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Fort Worth Shamrocks:team#13> won\'t soon forget the display of raw power put on today by <Jose Hernandez:player#726> of the <San Francisco Valley Cats:team#9>. He victimized the Shamrocks by pounding three pitches out of Shamrocks Stadium to spark his club to the 20-9 win.\n\n\"I got three pitches down the pipe and popped them,\" <Hernandez:player#726> told reporters. \"Today I was in a groove. Tomorrow, I could just pop up the same pitches and go 0-for-3.\"\n\nIn addition to the homers, he collected 10 RBIs and scored 5 runs.\n\n<Jose Hernandez:player#726> struck out in the 1st, hit a solo-shot off <Josh Asbill:player#612> in the 4th, hit a three-run home run off <Josh Asbill:player#612> in the 5th, walked in the 8th, hit a GRAND SLAM off <Dusty Martz:player#1282> in the 8th and hit a two-run double in the 9th.\n\n<Hernandez:player#726> is batting .333 with 9 home runs and 27 RBIs this season.\n"), (145, "Fernandez Electric in 5-0 Greenville Win", 60, 0, 0, 0, 0, 33, 40, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 33, 0, 0, "2022-4-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Greenville Silver Wolves:team#33> rolled to an easy 5-0 win over the <Burnside Chaparrals:team#40> at Silver Wolves Field today. Leading the way to victory was starter <Mike Fernandez:player#60>, who shackled the <Burnside Chaparrals:team#40> and held them scoreless on a 4-hitter.\n\n\"This is what every pitcher wants to do when they go out there,\" Fernandez said in his postgame press conference.\n\n"), (146, "Is Controversial Center Fielder Secretly a Softie?", 17, 0, 0, 0, 0, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-4-23", 0, 1, -1, 0, "File this story under \"whoda\' thunk it?\" <Brooklyn Storm:team#6>\'s center fielder <Jim Lickey:player#17> is seen by some as being aloof and a bit of a loner. \"I\'d call him \'intense,\'\" teammate <Rafael Dominguez:player#31> put it judiciously. Lickey\'s reputation isn\'t helped by his sometimes contentious relationship with the media, and most reporters would agree that he\'s not the easiest player to interview, let alone get to know. If he\'d agree to talk with you, Lickey would probably explain that he puts all of his effort into his peformance on the field, and that he\'s focused on winning a championship, not a popularity contest.\n\nSo everybody agrees that Lickey is, as the old-timers would say, a \"tough egg.\" But maybe he isn\'t as hard-boiled as most folks might think. An inside source recently reported that Lickey has been volunteering his time at the Youth Baseball Foundation in Brooklyn. When initially confronted with the story, Lickey angrily denied it, but his teammates were unanimous in support of his generous and, frankly, unexpected gesture. \"It shows what we always suspected, that his heart is in the right place,\" said Dominguez. \"He really cares about kids, and that\'s what counts in the end.\"\n\nDoes this signal the emergence of a kinder, gentler Lickey? Maybe, maybe not. But don\'t be surprised if you see him a get a few more high-fives from his fellow Brooklyn players and perhaps a few more autograph requests from some of the kids who benefitted from his previously secret generosity.\n"), (147, "San Diego Loses Pamfili for 4 Months", 314, 0, 0, 0, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 5, 0, -5, "2022-4-24", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The injury that has kept <Rinaldo Pamfili:player#314> out of action since 04/23/2022 will keep him out a while longer. <San Diego Fighting Knights:team#5> officials made the announcement this afternoon. They said that Pamfili is expected to miss at least 4 months with a fractured elbow.\n\nFor the year <Pamfili:player#314> is batting .241 with 14 hits and 2 home runs. He has scored 6 times and driven in 4.\n"), (148, "No Comeback This Season for Griffis", 1913, 0, 0, 0, 0, 63, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 63, 0, -5, "2022-4-24", 0, 1, -1, 0, "After several days of waiting for test results, bad news was delivered to <Mike Griffis:player#1913> today. The <Starks:team#63> third baseman will be out the rest of the year due to a torn posterior cruciate ligament he suffered on 04/21/2022. \n\nThis season <Griffis:player#1913> is batting at a .245 clip with 4 home runs and 5 RBIs. \n"), (149, "Franklin Socks It to Greenville 3 Times", 1192, 0, 0, 0, 0, 40, 33, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 40, 0, 0, "2022-4-24", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Ben Franklin:player#1192> went the distance three times in the <Burnside:team#40>-<Greenville:team#33> tilt at Silver Wolves Field today, but the Chaparrals lost, 10-8.\n\n\"Gosh, it\'s a shame we didn\'t win this game,\" Franklin said later.\n\nFor the day, the <Burnside:team#40> left fielder went 3-for-5 against <Greenville:team#33> with 7 RBIs and 3 runs scored in a brilliant display of power hitting.\n\n\"I was in a groove and every pitch they tossed up there looked like a basketball,\" he said. \"I tell you what, I was surprised because I didn\'t think the last ball had enough to get out. I thought it was just going to be a long out.\"\n\n<Ben Franklin:player#1192> hit a three-run home run off <Ruben Mezia:player#1065> in the 1st, grounded out in the 3rd, hit a three-run home run off <Ruben Mezia:player#1065> in the 5th, flied out in the 7th and hit a solo-shot off <Freddy Guevara:player#1253> in the 9th.\n\nThis year <Franklin:player#1192> is hitting .259, produced 10 RBIs and 3 home runs, scored 6 times and gotten on base at a .286 rate. \n"), (150, "Heredia May Be Fined for Missed Bus", 1431, 0, 0, 0, 0, 54, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-4-24", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Word out of Zips camp today is that <Jordan Heredia:player#1431> might be fined by the team or benched for the next game as punishment for missing the team bus. \"It\'s unacceptable,\" said manager Josh Dalton. \"He should know better and should take responsibility for his actions. Something needs to be done to curb this behavior before it becomes a real problem.\" Pressed for a comment, Heredia simply said, \"I overslept. It happens.\"\n"), (151, "Newsome Sticks It to SL1 Pitchers", 1576, 0, 0, 0, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 5, 0, 0, "2022-4-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "26-year-old <Jayden Newsome:player#1576> sent shock waves through Fictional Baseball League last week with an eye-popping performance that brought him the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award.\n\nA newcomer to the league, <Newsome:player#1576> made the establishment sit up and take notice, punishing opposing pitchers with a .471 average, 8 hits in 17 at-bats, 1 home run and 4 RBI.\n\nWhere the <San Diego Fighting Knights:team#5> second baseman goes from here, only the baseball gods know for sure, but <Newsome:player#1576> certainly made his mark last week.\n\nFor the season <Newsome:player#1576> is batting .254 with 16 hits and 3 home runs. He has scored 13 times and batted in 9.\n"), (152, "SL2 Star of the Week Picked", 726, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-4-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Veteran <Jose Hernandez:player#726> had a great week at the plate for the <Valley Cats:team#9> to capture the majority of votes for Player of the Week in the Sub League 2.\n\nThe 40-year-old San Francisco third baseman built a .423 average on the strength of 11 hits in 26 at-bats, 6 home runs and 18 RBIs.\n\nThis year <Hernandez:player#726> is batting .328 with 9 home runs. He has scored 17 runs and driven in 27.\n"), (153, "SL1 Names Top Player of the Week", 204, 0, 0, 0, 0, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 24, 0, 0, "2022-4-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Player of the Week has been announced by the Sub League 1. The award went to <Ivan Montes:player#204>, first baseman of the <North Hempstead Knights:team#24>.\n\nHe dominated league pitchers with a .360 average to win the honor. <Montes:player#204> went 9-for-25 for the week, totaled 2 home runs with 5 RBIs and scored 5 times.\n\n"), (154, "SL2\'s #1 Player, Williams of Fair Haven", 985, 0, 0, 0, 0, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 25, 0, 0, "2022-4-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The votes have been tallied and the winner of the Sub League 2 Player of the Week has been named. It was awarded earlier today to <Ben Williams:player#985> for his great week at the plate.\n\nThe <Fair Haven:team#25> left fielder took home the trophy by banging out 8 hits in 19 at-bats for a .421 batting average, driving in 11 runs and scoring 6 times.\n\n"), (155, "SL1 Player of the Week Named", 73, 0, 0, 0, 0, 33, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 33, 0, 0, "2022-4-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "One of the league\'s most exciting young players, <Sean Ferraro:player#73> of the <Green