 the plate for <Chicago Quakes:team#12> left fielder <Ken Boren:player#539>, but a tough one for the team, as the Quakes dropped the contest 7-6 to the <Houston Seagulls:team#10>.\n\nEven with the loss, Boren was pure misery for the <Houston:team#10> pitching staff. He left them shell-shocked after going 5-for-5 in an explosive display of hitting. \n\n\"It\'s always good to get a bunch of hits in a game, but you also want to win,\" said Boren, who is the fan favorite . \n\n\"<Boren:player#539> really hit the ball hard and when you do that, you\'ve got a good chance to do some damage,\" Seagulls manager  <Joe Lohmeyer:coach#109> told BNN reporters after the game. \"I feel like we threw him some good pitches, but he just put some good swings on the ball.\" \n\n<Ken Boren:player#539> doubled in the 1st, singled in the 3rd, doubled in the 5th, singled in the 8th and hit a two-run home run off <Elias Mora:player#572> in the 9th.\n\nPresently <Boren:player#539> is batting .325 and has collected 4 home runs, 13 RBIs, .404 OBP and scored 15 runs.\n\n<View Boxscore:box#727>\n"), (169, "Rowdy Players Suspended by League", 220, 332, 0, 0, 0, 24, 19, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 24, 0, 0, "2022-4-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Zach Brougham:player#220> of the <North Hempstead Knights:team#24> and <Alexis Montejano:player#332> of the <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> received notification from the league commissioner\'s office that they had been suspended for 3 and 7 games respectively for their part in the on-field ruckus in a recent game at Knights Grove. \n\nThis season <Brougham:player#220> is batting .256 with 11 hits, 1 home run, 4 RBIs, 4 walks, .327 OBP and has scored 2 runs. He has played in 13 games.\n\n"), (170, "Channell and Gonzalez Suspended for Free-for-All", 502, 1200, 0, 0, 0, 26, 29, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 26, 0, 0, "2022-4-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Will Channell:player#502> of the <Leesburg Privateers:team#26> and <Juan Gonzalez:player#1200> of the <Tampa Brawlers:team#29> will be on the sidelines for a few days. They have been suspended for 4 and 9 games respectively by the league office for causing the bench-emptying free-for-all at the recent Privateers-Brawlers game at Privateers Park.\n\nNeither player had any comment about the suspensions. Both clubs told BNN <Channell:player#502> and <Gonzalez:player#1200> will begin serving them soon.\n\nThis season <Channell:player#502> is batting .239 with 7 RBIs, 6 runs scored and 4 home runs.\n\n"), (171, "Gomez Angry at Local Media Over Detroit Coverage", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-4-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Detroit skipper Ben Gomez blasted the media today over what he considered to be negative coverage of his slumping team.\n\n\"You guys are really something, you know that?\" Gomez shouted at reporters. \"All you want to do is place blame. Why can\'t you focus on what we\'re doing that\'s positive? Some of our guys are putting up great numbers this season, but you never talk about that. It\'s just a matter of getting everyone together on the same page. But you guys making your snide remarks isn\'t gonna help us with that, is it?\"\n\nGomez then abruptly stepped away from the bank of microphones and stormed angrily out of the room.\n"), (172, "Cardenas Joins 3-HR Club", 308, 0, 0, 0, 0, 5, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 5, 0, 0, "2022-4-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The \"hardest feat in sports\" debate is a never-ending one with no correct answer, but hitting three home runs is certainly in the conversation. That\'s exactly what <Cameron Cardenas:player#308> did today at Fighting Knights Park, going deep three times and carrying his team to victory, 5-4.\n\n\"It all came together. I was seeing the ball well and I got some good pitches to hit,\" Cardenas said. \"Good things happen, when that happens.\"\n\nThe <San Diego Fighting Knights:team#5> right fielder blistered the <Jacksonville Orange Sox:team#1> for 4 hits, batted in 4 runs and scored 3 times.\n\n\"It ain\'t like we weren\'t trying,\" <Jacksonville:team#1> manager <Enrique Vazquez:coach#19> said. \"He was hot and really torched my boys today.\"\n\n<Cameron Cardenas:player#308> struck out in the 1st, hit a two-run home run off <Johnny Cabrera:player#100> in the 3rd, singled in the 5th, hit a solo-shot off <Rich Ellison:player#941> in the 7th, walked in the 9th, struck out in the 11th, grounded out in the 13th, struck out in the 16th and hit a solo-shot off <Dan Gustavson:player#97> in the 18th.\n\nThis year <Cardenas:player#308> has batted at a .259 pace with 21 hits, 5 home runs, 17 RBIs and scored 12 times.\n"), (173, "Super Swinger -- Gransden Slams 5 Hits", 1790, 0, 0, 0, 0, 53, 56, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 53, 0, 0, "2022-4-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Steve Gransden:player#1790> got the glory and the headlines today, but the <Madison Astros:team#56> left with the win. The <Modesto:team#53> right fielder easily handled the Astros pitching, going 5-for-5, but his <Modesto Oil Barons:team#53> came out on the short end of the 6-5 score.\n\nGransden told BNN reporters in the postgame interview he would happily trade \"three or four\" of his hits for a win.\n\n\"Heck, maybe even all of them,\" he said with a laugh. \"Right now, it just seems like one loss in a long season but who knows what it could mean at the end.\"\n\n<Steve Gransden:player#1790> singled in the 1st, hit a solo-shot off <Mike Argabright:player#2599> in the 4th, singled in the 6th, hit an RBI single in the 7th and hit an RBI single in the 9th.\n\nTo date this year <Gransden:player#1790> is batting .319 with 5 home runs. \n"), (174, "DeMascio Expected to Miss 3 Weeks", 251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 8, 0, -5, "2022-4-28", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Justin DeMascio:player#251> could soon be placed on the injured list. The <Phoenix:team#8> first baseman told reporters that he expects to be \"out of commission\" for 3 weeks because of a concussion. He hasn\'t played since 04/25/2022 and, he said, he\'s \"itchin\' to get back out there.\"\n\nSo far this year in 19 games DeMascio is hitting .309 with 7 home runs, 14 RBIs and 12 runs scored.\n"), (175, "Valido Rumored to be Dating Pop Star", 402, 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-4-28", 0, 1, 1, 0, "<Óscar Valido:player#402> of the Boston Wild Riders is reportedly keeping company with singer Katelyn Martinez. The couple has been spotted recently at various clubs, concerts, and restaurants, as well as a number of public functions. Asked whether the two were involved romatically, Valido said he and Martinez were \'just good friends\'. \"We\'re just hanging out and enjoying each other\'s company at the moment,\" said the 26-year-old left fielder. However, when pressed as to whether their relationship might become more serious in the future, Valido seemed to dodge the question. \"Right now, I\'m really just focused on baseball and helping the Boston Wild Riders win games,\" he remarked, with a sly grin.\n"), (176, "5 Hits for Lumberjacks Rendon", 256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 6, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 8, 0, 0, "2022-4-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Getting 5 hits in a game has always been memorable feat in baseball. In the Phoenix\'s 13-5 win over <Brooklyn:team#6> today, shortstop <Antonio Rendon:player#256> was red-hot, scorching them for hit after hit at Storm Field. \n\n\"To hit the ball consistently well, you have to relax,\" Rendon said afterward. \"I was relaxed for the first four hits, but I have to admit, I got a little tight when I realized I had a chance for five. On the last at-bat, I was ready to swing at anything close.\"\n\n<Antonio Rendon:player#256> hit a solo-shot off <Sam Luna:player#810> in the 1st, doubled in the 3rd, hit an RBI double in the 5th, doubled in the 7th and tripled in the 9th.\n\n\n\n<View Boxscore:box#92>\n"), (177, "SL1 Presents Batter of Month Trophy to Watts", 117, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 1, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Mike Watts:player#117> battered Sub League 1 pitchers all April and wound up taking home the Batter of the Month Award.\n\n\"I\'ve been around Fictional Baseball League long enough to know you really have to work hard day in and day out to be able to put up this kind of consistency,\" the 27-year-old Watts told reporters. \"I put in a lot of work, even on the days I might not take the field, and it\'s always nice when everything comes together for me like it did this last month.\"\n\nIn 24 games, Watts hit .358 with 10 home runs, 19 RBIs and scored 17 runs.\n\n"), (178, "Hernandez Takes SL2\'s Best Bat Award", 726, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Though his face is weathered and his hands are callused, <Jose Hernandez:player#726> can still get it done in Fictional Baseball League. The 40-year-old third baseman for <San Francisco:team#9> was named the Sub League 2 Batter of the Month today after putting up an impressive performance at the plate.\n\nIn April he batted .333 with 12 home runs, 39 RBIs and 22 runs scored.\n\n"), (179, "Amenero Nets SL1 #1 Pitcher Award", 1357, 0, 0, 0, 0, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 7, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "When <Bobby Amenero:player#1357> took the hill in April, he was in charge. The <San Jose:team#7> starter never let the Sub League 1 batters get a foothold against him. For his peerless performance, he came away with an impressive 5-0 record and the Pitcher of the Month award.\n\nThe talented Spiders hurler made 5 starts, worked 33.2 innings, permitted 17 base hits, and struck out 30 while putting up a 1.07 ERA. \n\n"), (180, "Owls Starter Named April\'s Premier Pitcher", 1154, 0, 0, 0, 0, 14, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 14, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "In April, when the name of <Manny Martinez:player#1154> appeared on the <New York:team#14> lineup card it was a virtual lock on a victory. He started 6 times and chalked up 4 wins and no losses. With those stats it was also a virtual lock that he would be named the Sub League 2 Pitcher of the Month.\n\nMartinez shackled opposing batters on 36 base hits and a .252 batting average. He rang up 32 strikeouts in 36.2 innings of work, surrendered 13 walks and fashioned a sparkling 2.70 ERA.\n\n"), (181, "Amenero Wins Rookie of the Month", 1357, 0, 0, 0, 0, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 7, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Pitcher <Bobby Amenero:player#1357> of the <San Jose Spiders:team#7> was the premier rookie in the Sub League 1 last month and today the league honored him as the Rookie of the Month award winner.\n\nIn April his record was 5-0 with a 1.07 ERA and 30 strikeouts in 33.2 innings.\n\n"), (182, "Top SL2 Rookie of the Month Named", 1746, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Jose Cortez:player#1746> is giving fans of <San Francisco:team#9> a lot to be happy about lately. In April he logged a 3-1 mark on his way to earning Sub League 2 Rookie of the Month recognition.\n\nThe 21-year-old also chalked up 24 strikeouts in 28.2 innings with a 2.20 ERA and issued 8 walks.\n\n"), (183, "Mendez Crowned Batter of the Month in April", 122, 0, 0, 0, 0, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 22, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Jose Mendez:player#122> put together a good April to earn the Sub League 1 Batter of the Month prize. A virtual unknown, he made the most of his chance to prove to <Chandler:team#22> officials that he belongs on the big league roster.\n\nThe <Capitals:team#22> third baseman posted a .643 batting average with 5 home runs, 10 RBIs and 6 runs scored.\n\n"), (184, "SL2\'s #1 Batter Chosen", 1131, 0, 0, 0, 0, 28, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 28, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Donna Whitecaps:team#28> fans believe they\'ve got a talented young star in <Jose Hiciano:player#1131>.\n\nHe did nothing to dissuade that notion in April, as he hit .379 with 9 home runs, 22 RBIs and 16 runs scored.\n\nThe end result was the first baseman being named the Sub League 2 Batter of the Month.\n\n"), (185, "Jackson Picks up SL1 Monthly Pitching Honor", 379, 0, 0, 0, 0, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 21, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "When <Dan Jackson:player#379> takes the hill, he usually takes command of the game -- at least that\'s the way it was in April. The outcome was usually a <Fort Wayne:team#21> victory. His fine 3-0 performance earned him the Sub League 1 Pitcher of the Month trophy.\n\nThe talented Blue Falcons hurler made 3 starts, worked 23.1 innings, permitted 12 base hits, and struck out 15 while putting up a 0.77 ERA. \n\n"), (186, "Apple Sox Meagher Chosen April\'s Best in SL2", 2053, 0, 0, 0, 0, 32, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 32, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "April was a very good month for <Scott Meagher:player#2053> of the <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32>. He held opposing hitters for a .250 average and took home the Sub League 2 Pitcher of the Month award.\n\nIn 4 starts he claimed a 4-0 record as he put up a 2.57 ERA and struck out 18 in 28 innings.\n\n"), (187, "Arredondo Claims SL1 Batter of the Month Award", 118, 0, 0, 0, 0, 37, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 37, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Even though he is a newcomer to FBL Double A, <Omar Arredondo:player#118> put up some good numbers in April and earned the SL1 Batter of the Month award.\n\nHe was one of <San Bernardino:team#37>\'s offensive leaders with a .316 average in 22 games. He also racked up 12 home runs, 27 RBIs, and 20 runs scored.\n\n"), (188, "Sub League 2 Announces April\'s Best Batter", 1444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 41, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 2, 5, 41, 0, 0, "2022-5-1", 0, 1, -1, 0, "For a rookie just breaking in, <Ron Tanguy:player#1444> certainly put together a successful month. It was good enough to win the SL2 Batter of the Month award for April.\n\nThe 23-year-old first baseman for the <Orlando Schooners:team#41> hit .356 with 8 home runs, 18 RBIs and 18 runs scored. \n\n"), (189, "Gibbs Named Top SL1 Hu