or-4 on the day with 3 RBI.\n\n<Edwin Rivera:player#1963> hit a solo-shot off <Dale Cosman:player#1568> in the 2nd, hit a solo-shot off <Dale Cosman:player#1568> in the 4th, singled in the 6th and hit a solo-shot off <Hakaru Kamei:player#1047> in the 8th.\n\nTo date this season <Rivera:player#1963> is hitting .322 with 12 home runs. \n"), (213, "League Gives Garrett and Vigil 4-Game Suspensions", 1974, 432, 0, 0, 0, 64, 63, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 64, 0, 0, "2022-5-3", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Following a mass brawl, the league has suspended <Sam Garrett:player#1974> of <Aurora:team#64> and <Joel Vigil:player#432> of <Starks:team#63>. The players will have to sit out 4 games each after trouble flared up between the Tigers and the Westerners at a recent game at Comerica Park. \n\nIn 24 games this season <Garrett:player#1974> is batting .174 with 15 hits and 1 home run. He has scored 7 runs and driven in 6.\n\nTo this point in the season <Vigil:player#432> has no saves in 6 relief appearances with a 0-0 record and 7.20 ERA.\n"), (214, "Silvester Receives Updated Diagnosis", 58, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 2, 0, -5, "2022-5-4", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Team officials for the <Baltimore Legion:team#2> have revealed that the recent injury to <Justin Silvester:player#58> will keep him out for 7 weeks. The 31-year-old closer suffered a forearm strain on 04/29/2022. He has not played since.\n\nIn 2022 <Silvester:player#58> has totaled 12 relief appearances and saved 5. His record is 2-1 with 14 strikeouts in 15 innings and a 3.60 ERA. \n"), (215, "Injury Shuts Down Hudson for Season", 199, 0, 0, 0, 0, 46, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 46, 0, -5, "2022-5-4", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The season will end prematurely for <Ahmed Hudson:player#199>, the <Corpus Christi:team#46> reliever. He suffered a torn rotator cuff on 05/03/2022, an injury that is serious enough to knock him out of action for the rest of the year. Hudson was not available for comment.\n\nThis year <Hudson:player#199> is 1-and-0 with no saves and a 5.56 ERA. He has given up 7 hits in 11.1 innings with 13 strikeouts.\n"), (216, "League Punishes Pair for Fighting", 1790, 2193, 0, 0, 0, 53, 56, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 53, 0, 0, "2022-5-4", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Yesterday at Oil Barons Ballpark <Steve Gransden:player#1790> and <Simon Martin:player#2193> got into each other\'s space and then into each other\'s face. They began to grapple and fell to the ground. That\'s when it boiled over into a full-fledged bench-clearing tussle between the <Modesto Oil Barons:team#53> and <Madison Astros:team#56>. Reason finally prevailed as the umpires restored order. After much discussion, only the two major combatants were ejected from the game.\n\nToday the league office notified the ballclubs that <Gransden:player#1790> will have to sit out 5 while <Martin:player#2193> would be given a 3-game suspension for their roles in the brawl. \n\nOn the year <Gransden:player#1790> is hitting .273 with 27 hits, 6 home runs, 20 RBIs, .357 OBP and has scored 13 runs.\n\nThis season <Martin:player#2193> has logged 1 save. He has thrown 22.1 innings, dished out 14 strikeouts and walked 8 while putting up a 0-1 mark and a 3.22 ERA.\n"), (217, "Paisley and Dominguez Suspended, Out 3 Games", 1712, 1588, 0, 0, 0, 47, 48, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 47, 0, 0, "2022-5-4", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The league decided to come down hard on <Melvin Paisley:player#1712> of the Razorbacks and <Winston Dominguez:player#1588> of the Cheetahs for their roles in a brawl during a game between <Pittsburgh:team#47> and <Winston-Salem:team#48> at Razorbacks Grove. Both combatants will receive 3-game suspensions because of their confrontation.\n\n<Paisley:player#1712> is currently hitting at a .193 pace with 2 home runs, 6 RBIs and has scored 7 times. \n\nTo this point in the season <Dominguez:player#1588> has 1 save in 4 relief appearances with a 0-2 record and 4.80 ERA.\n"), (218, "Jones Announces Retirement", 210, 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-5-5", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Ken Jones:player#210> said he\'s looking forward to getting home to Warrington Township, Pennsylvania to relax and unwind.\n\nAt age 38, the <Memphis T-Bones:team#3> player has announced he will retire at the end of the season.\n\n\"I\'m thankful for my time in Fictional Baseball League, but all good things must come to an end,\" he said.\n\n"), (219, "7-Game Suspensions for Guiles-Martinez Fight", 769, 789, 0, 0, 0, 46, 41, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 46, 0, 0, "2022-5-5", 0, 1, -1, 0, "There was a mass free-for-all yesterday at Fighters Field. Both dugouts emptied when <Corpus Christi:team#46>\'s <Steve Guiles:player#769> and <Orlando:team#41>\'s <Edgar Martinez:player#789> scuffled with one another after some heated words.\n\nIn an official statement today, the league commissioner suspended both parties for 7 games.\n\n\n\nThis season <Martinez:player#789> has logged no saves. He has thrown 16 innings, dished out 11 strikeouts and walked 8 while putting up a 1-0 mark and a 5.06 ERA.\n"), (220, "Rowdy Players Suspended by League", 24, 330, 0, 0, 0, 6, 7, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 6, 0, 0, "2022-5-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "If there wasn\'t a history between <Eric Ratcliff:player#24> of <Brooklyn:team#6> and <Marco Jimenez:player#330> of <San Jose:team#7>, then there is one now. The incident between the two sparked a bench-clearing scrum with those two being the center of attention. Now they will miss 3 and 7 games respectively as a result of their actions. The league office announced their suspensions today.\n\n\"We\'re both really competitive,\" <Ratcliff:player#24> said later, \"and sometimes things go a little too far because of it.\"\n\n<Ratcliff:player#24> is currently batting .225 with 3 home runs and 17 RBIs.\n\nThis year <Jimenez:player#330> has gone 1-2 with an ERA of 1.74 and has 18 strikeouts in 31 innings.\n"), (221, "Brooklyn\'s Carlos Romero Suffers Setback", 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 6, 0, 0, "2022-5-8", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Things have gotten worse for <Carlos Romero:player#10> of the <Brooklyn Storm:team#6>. The 31-year-old reliever will not be back as soon as originally expected. <Romero:player#10> is undergoing treatment for a bone spur in his elbow, but his doctors have expanded his recovery time to at least 4 weeks. An unidentified team official told BNN, \"<Carlos:player#10> tried to rush his rehab and suffered a setback.\"\n\n"), (222, "Phoenix Shortstop Picked SL1 Player of the Week", 256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 8, 0, 0, "2022-5-9", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Antonio Rendon:player#256> has the tools to stick in this league for many years. The 22-year-old shortstop of the <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8> had a hot bat in the Sub League 1 over the past seven days and won the Player of the Week honors.\n\n<Rendon:player#256> batted .423 with 11 hits in 26 at-bats, no home runs and 3 RBIs. \n\nThus far this year Rendon is batting .463 with 2 home runs, 7 RBIs and 9 runs scored. \n"), (223, "Chicago\'s Boren Gets SL2 Player of the Week ", 539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 12, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-5-9", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Player of the Week has been announced by the Sub League 2. The award went to <Ken Boren:player#539>, left fielder of the <Chicago Quakes:team#12>.\n\nHe dominated league pitchers with a .520 average to win the honor. <Boren:player#539> went 13-for-25 for the week, totaled 3 home runs with 7 RBIs and scored 5 times.\n\nSo far in 2022 Boren is batting .347 with 9 home runs, 24 RBIs and 24 runs scored. He has 42 hits in 121 at-bats and a .433 OBP.\n"), (224, "Montes Caps Great Week", 204, 0, 0, 0, 0, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 24, 0, 0, "2022-5-9", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The votes have been tallied and the winner of the Sub League 1 Player of the Week has been named. It was awarded earlier today to <Ivan Montes:player#204> for his great week at the plate.\n\nThe <North Hempstead:team#24> first baseman took home the trophy by banging out 9 hits in 21 at-bats for a .429 batting average, driving in 9 runs and scoring 7 times.\n\nIn 23 games Montes is hitting .295 this season with 26 hits, 9 home runs, 17 RBIs, 12 walks, .386 OBP and has scored 15 runs.\n"), (225, "SL2 Announces Player of the Week", 453, 0, 0, 0, 0, 27, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 27, 0, 0, "2022-5-9", 0, 1, -1, 0, "There\'s no arguing that 40-year-old <Bryan L\'Esperance:player#453> has paid his dues and this this week he collected. The <Bakersfield Millionaires:team#27> left fielder had one of the best weeks of his career and captured the Sub League 2 Player of the Week trophy.\n\nHe hit .471 while collecting 8 hits in 17 at-bats, 2 home runs, 8 RBIs and 5 runs scored.\n\nThis year <L\'Esperance:player#453> is batting .302 with 2 home runs and 11 RBIs. In 14 games he has scored 8 times.\n"), (226, "SL1 Player of the Week Goes to Ghirlandaio of Burnside", 1183, 0, 0, 0, 0, 40, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 40, 0, 0, "2022-5-9", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Juan Ghirlandaio:player#1183> finds himself in the Sub League 1 spotlight today after his impossible-to-ignore performance last week. He carried the <Burnside Chaparrals:team#40> on his shoulders, earning Sub League 1 Player of the Week honors.\n\nThe 24-year-old hit .455 (10-for-22) with 4 home runs and 9 runs batted in.\n\nDuring the current season <Ghirlandaio:player#1183> is batting at a .356 clip with 10 home runs and 25 RBIs. He has played in 28 games and scored 23 times.\n"), (227, "SL2 Honors Corpus Christi First Baseman", 1547, 0, 0, 0, 0, 46, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 46, 0, 0, "2022-5-9", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s Sub League 2 Player of the Week is <Corey Walker:player#1547> of the <Corpus Christi Fighters:team#46>.\n\nHe ambushed SL2 pitching for 13 hits in 30 at-bats, 3 home runs and 6 RBIs, while hitting .433 and scoring 7 runs.\n\nThus far this season Walker is hitting .333 with 5 home runs, 13 RBIs and 17 runs scored. He has 42 hits in