old him he\'d better do good again next week.\"\n\nCurrently <Montejano:player#332> has a record of 1-2 with 21 strikeouts and 8 walks in 34 innings and a 3.71 ERA.\n"), (240, "Season Ends for Ortiz", 695, 0, 0, 0, 0, 48, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 48, 0, -5, "2022-5-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "In a news release, the <Winston-Salem Cheetahs:team#48> announced that reliever <Octavio Ortiz:player#695> would miss the rest of the season due to a torn flexor tendon in his elbow. Ortiz sustained the injury on 05/07/2022. He \"will be sorely missed,\" said his manager.\n\nThis season <Ortiz:player#695> has been credited with no saves. In 8 relief appearances and 8.2 innings he has a 0-0 won-lost mark, 6.23 ERA and 6 strikeouts\n"), (241, "Lockwood Receives Injury Update", 1322, 0, 0, 0, 0, 37, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 37, 0, -5, "2022-5-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Team officials for the <San Bernardino Ivy:team#37> have revealed that the recent injury to <Rich Lockwood:player#1322> will keep him out for 4 months. The 28-year-old center fielder suffered a concussion on 05/08/2022. He has not played since.\n\n<Lockwood:player#1322> is hitting .269 in 2022 with 18 RBIs and 6 home runs.\n"), (242, "Season Done for Loper", 1747, 0, 0, 0, 0, 54, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 54, 0, -5, "2022-5-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Oak View Zips:team#54> have lost the services of <Jesse Loper:player#1747> for the rest of this season. He suffered a ruptured ulnar collateral ligament in a recent ballgame and the follow-up report from the medical staff is not good. Loper is out for the year.\n\nTo date this season <Loper:player#1747> is 0-1 with 2 starts and an ERA of 5.51 with 11 strikeouts in 16.1 innings. \n"), (243, "Colon Goes Downtown 3 Times Against Wild Dogs", 904, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 23, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 19, 0, 0, "2022-5-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Every now and then, everything just comes together.\n\n<Carlos Colon:player#904> discovered that today at Blue Raiders Ballpark, as he smashed three home runs during the 16-5 <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> win over the <Jersey City Wild Dogs:team#23>.\n\n\"I got three balls to hit and nailed all three of them,\" the <Greendale:team#19> right fielder said in his postgame interview. \"The first was a hanging curve, the second was right down the middle and the last one was a good pitch, but I guessed right and put the wood to it.\"\n\nColon finished the day with 3 hits in 3 at-bats and 7 RBIs.\n\n<Carlos Colon:player#904> hit a solo-shot off <Albert Sandoval:player#788> in the 2nd, hit a solo-shot off <Albert Sandoval:player#788> in the 3rd, walked in a run in the 4th, hit a sac fly in the 6th and hit a three-run home run off <Jeff Carlson:player#746> in the 8th.\n\nCurrently <Colon:player#904> has 12 home runs and a .375 batting average.\n"), (244, "Bad Boy Brawlers Suspended 4 Games", 121, 42, 0, 0, 0, 22, 18, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 22, 0, 0, "2022-5-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The fans at Ballpark of Chandler saw it all yesterday in the Capitals-Rainiers game -- pushes, shoves, scuffles, a few tackles, a few swings, a few feeble punches -- and a baseball game, too. When the ruckus was over, only two players were sent to the showers by the umpire crew. <Chandler:team#22>\'s <Ramon Hernandez:player#121> and <Toledo:team#18>\'s <Roberto Martinez:player#42> were ejected from the game.\n\nToday the two players were suspended 4 games by the league commissioner.\n\nThus far in 2022 Hernandez is hitting .312 with 10 home runs, 22 RBIs, 19 runs scored and has compiled a .414 OBP.\n\nThis season <Martinez:player#42> has logged no saves. He has thrown 9.2 innings, dished out 5 strikeouts and walked 5 while putting up a 2-0 mark and a 2.79 ERA.\n"), (245, "Going, Going, Gone! Montes Hits 3 Homers", 204, 0, 0, 0, 0, 24, 17, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 24, 0, 0, "2022-5-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "In a powerful performance that left the fans at Mannford Grounds buzzing, <North Hempstead Knights:team#24> first baseman <Ivan Montes:player#204> blasted a trio of home runs en route to a 8-3 win over the <Mannford Monsters:team#17>.\n\n\"Everything was clicking,\" Montes told the press. \"My timing was good and I got pitches I could handle and I didn\'t miss them.\"\n\n<Montes:player#204> shined brilliantly in the win, with 3 hits in 4 at-bats, 7 RBIs and 3 runs scored.\n\n\"It\'s not just one guy, it\'s everybody,\" Knights manager Jim Riedesel said. \"Ivan played great but it takes more than one guy to win a game.\"\n\n<Ivan Montes:player#204> hit a two-run home run off <Josh Coleman:player#2131> in the 1st, walked in the 3rd, flied out in the 5th, hit a three-run home run off <Chris Turner:player#910> in the 7th and hit a two-run home run off <Manny Campos:player#617> in the 9th.\n\nLooking at his season stats, <Montes:player#204> has compiled a .310 batting average and a .395 on-base percentage, while hitting 12 home runs and driving in 24 runs.\n"), (246, "Mavericks Listless in 8-0 Loss to Ivy", 939, 0, 0, 0, 0, 37, 36, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 37, 0, 0, "2022-5-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Today was <Bill Armstrong:player#939>\'s turn in the rotation for the <San Bernardino Ivy:team#37> and he made the most of it, shutting out the <Sparta Mavericks:team#36> on 5 hits.\n\nThe 31-year-old right-hander led the Ivy to an easy 8-0 victory, allowing no walks and tallying 8 strikeouts.\n\n\"I hope we miss him next time,\" <Sparta:team#36> manager <Joe Sprang:coach#279> said. \"Armstrong certainly pitched a strong game against us today. He was in a groove, throwing everything for strikes. Throwing hard. Changing speeds.\"\n\nFor the season <Armstrong:player#939> has compiled a 1-1 record with a 3.60 ERA.\n"), (247, "Levesque Extends Hit Streak to 20 Games", 598, 0, 0, 0, 0, 29, 25, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 29, 0, 0, "2022-5-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The hot bat of Brawlers center fielder <Sean Levesque:player#598> continues to churn out hit after hit, game after game. His consecutive-game hitting streak now