whole game. He struck out 5 in the 4-0 win and walked 2 while surrendering 4 hits.\n\n\"Hopefully there will be plenty more of these in the future for us,\" he said.\n\nThis season <Krueger:player#2239> has gone 5-1 with an ERA of 3.28, posting 36 strikeouts in 57.2 innings.\n"), (251, "Boisclair May Leave Shamrocks", 625, 0, 0, 0, 0, 13, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 13, 0, 0, "2022-5-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "\"No comment,\" was the word from <Fort Worth Shamrocks:team#13> catcher <Bryant Boisclair:player#625> when asked about the trade rumors swirling around baseball circles.\n\nThe Shamrocks have been hush on the topic of a possible trade, but several unnamed sources have mentioned scenarios involving Boisclair being traded to a few different teams.\n"), (252, "Blue Raiders Get No Resistance from Blue Falcons in 9-0 Beat-Down", 332, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 21, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 19, 0, 0, "2022-5-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Alexis Montejano:player#332> of the <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> spun his magic on the <Fort Wayne Blue Falcons:team#21> today. He blanked them 9-0 on 2 hits, registering 2 strikeouts and 2 walks.\n\n\"The bottom line was I just kept the ball down,\" Montejano said. \"My breaking stuff was down. Everything was down.\"\n\nTalking to reporters in the postgame interview, <Greendale:team#19> skipper Bryan Skaggs said the team \"got solid pitching, good defense and took great team at-bats in a lot of different situations.\"\n\n\"Alexis pitched really well but this was a solid performance by everyone,\" he said.\n\nSo far this season <Montejano:player#332> has a 2-2 record, 6 starts, 43 innings, 23 strikeouts and a 2.93 ERA.\n"), (253, "Sub League 1\'s Best Batter Announced", 67, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 2, 0, 0, "2022-5-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "When it came to hitting the baseball, <Cullen Burge:player#67> had few peers in the Sub League 1 this past week.\n\nThe talented first baseman for Baltimore tagged opposing pitchers for a .346 average and was voted the Player of the Week Award. Included in his stats were 9 hits in 26 at-bats, 4 homers, 4 runs scored and 5 RBIs.\n\nThis year <Burge:player#67> is batting .283 with 12 home runs.\n"), (254, "Regis Burti Wins SL2 Trophy", 542, 0, 0, 0, 0, 12, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-5-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "One of the league\'s most exciting young players, <Regis Burti:player#542> of the <Chicago Quakes:team#12> earned himself Sub League 2 Player of the Week honors with a standout performance in last week\'s games.\n\nFor the week the 25-year-old right fielder had a lofty .600 average (15-for-25), collecting 7 home runs, 11 RBIs and 11 runs scored.\n\nThis season <Burti:player#542> has delivered 61 hits in 142 at-bats for a .430 average with 18 home runs. He is getting on base at a .503 clip and his totals also include 41 RBIs and 34 runs scored. This year <Burti:player#542> has played in 38 games.\n"), (255, "Colon\'s Strong Week Earns SL1 Trophy", 904, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 19, 0, 0, "2022-5-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 1 has named its Top Player of the Week. The honor went to <Carlos Colon:player#904>, left fielder of the <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19>.\n\nIn an extraordinary hitting display, he belted out hits at a .455 pace to win the award. <Colon:player#904> went 10-for-22 for the week, totaled 6 home runs, 13 RBIs and scored 8 times.\n\nFor the season <Colon:player#904> is currently batting .371 with 13 home runs and 32 RBIs. In 31 games he has reached base at a .420 rate and scored 23 runs to date.\n"), (256, "Tampa Center Fielder Nets SL2 Award", 598, 0, 0, 0, 0, 29, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 29, 0, 0, "2022-5-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 2 made it official today: <Sean Levesque:player#598> is the Player of the Week.\n\nHe really stood out on the diamond this week with a .444 average to take home the award. The <Tampa:team#29> center fielder went 12-for-27, drove in 9 runs, scored 7 times an