Fort Wayne manager <John Redfield:coach#204>, who could be seen scolding the famously outspoken right-hander as the clubs left the field. de Anda\'s own manager then intervened with some words for his counterpart.\n\nThe Blue Falcons skipper would not comment on the exchange, but at the Capitals press conference, de Anda confirmed that it was regarding the celebration.\n\n\"He basically told me I was being a lousy winner,\" de Anda said.\n\n\"And I told him he was being a lousy loser,\" Chandler manager Bobby Huebner added.\n\nTo date this year, <de Anda:player#1301> shows a 5-3 record, 10 starts, 60.2 innings, 57 strikeouts and a 4.01 ERA.\n"), (314, "Verdugo Batters Greenville for 5 Hits", 1220, 0, 0, 0, 0, 35, 33, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 35, 0, 0, "2022-5-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "5 hits in a game has always been a big milestone in baseball -- 5 hits in a game gets a player\'s name in the record book, win or lose. <Ricky Verdugo:player#1220> got his name recorded today, but the <Greenville Silver Wolves:team#33> picked up the win at Sluggers Grounds, topping the <Buffalo Sluggers:team#35>, 13-4. \n\n\"He bushwhacked us,\" said winning manager <Matt Berry:coach#282>. \"We were lucky to come out ahead.\"\n\nVerdugo, who leads the SL1 in runs scored with 39, spoke to reporters in the clubhouse following the game, saying his nerves only set in once he was on the cusp of the milestone.\n\n\"I got too much adrenaline going when I realized that this could be a once-in-a-lifetime day,\" the first baseman said. \"I think the coaches could tell I was going to be ready to swing at anything close. That\'s why my third base coach told me to calm down and wait for a good pitch. That got me back on track.\"\n\n<Ricky Verdugo:player#1220> doubled in the 1st, singled in the 2nd, hit a solo-shot off <Mike Fernandez:player#60> in the 4th, hit a solo-shot off <Mike Fernandez:player#60> in the 7th and singled in the 9th.\n\nIn the 2022 season <Verdugo:player#1220> is hitting .251 with 19 home runs.\n"), (315, "Big Day with Bat: Mondragon 5-for-8", 2016, 0, 0, 0, 0, 48, 44, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 48, 0, 0, "2022-5-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Ignacio Mondragon:player#2016> of the Cheetahs was unstoppable in today\'s 16-14 victory over the <Long Beach Bluebirds:team#44> at Long Beach Fields. He battered them for 5 hits in 8 at-bats. \n\n\"Boy, I was on the mark today,\" said the <Winston-Salem:team#48> second baseman after the game. \"I could see the ball real well. It\'s a great feeling to do this. And besides, 5-for-8 won\'t hurt your batting average like 0-for-5 will.\" \n\n<Ignacio Mondragon:player#2016> hit a solo-shot off <Dale Cosman:player#1568> in the 1st, hit an RBI single in the 2nd, flied out in the 4th, walked in the 6th, singled in the 8th, grounded out in the 9th, singled in the 11th, struck out in the 13th and hit an RBI double in the 15th.\n\nThis year <Mondragon:player#2016> is batting .233 with 35 hits and 8 home runs. He has scored 18 times and has batted in 18 runs.\n"), (316, "Martinez Nabs SL1 Weekly Award", 301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 5, 0, 0, "2022-5-30", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was an exceptional week for <Dave Martinez:player#301> of the <San Diego Fighting Knights:team#5>.\n\nFirst he beat the devil out of the ball, hitting .409 and as you would expect, he was voted the Player of the Week in the Sub League 1. Last week <Martinez:player#301> went 9-for-22, notched 4 home runs and 8 RBIs and scored 8 runs. All in all, a very good week for him.\n\nThis season in 50 games, <Martinez:player#301> has hit at a .326 clip with 61 hits, 19 home runs, 44 RBIs and 39 runs scored.\n"), (317, "Sub League 2 Selects Best Performer", 539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 12, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-5-30", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Last week <Ken Boren:player#539> was the toast of <Chicago:team#12> and the talk of the Sub League 2 -- this week he\'s the SL2 Player of the Week.\n\nThe standout left fielder sewed up the award with his 