layed. He also boasts an OBP of .352 with 14 walks and 29 runs scored.\n"), (369, "Yoon Red-Hot, SL2 Player of the Week", 541, 0, 0, 0, 0, 12, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-6-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was announced today that <Chicago:team#12> center fielder <Sang-hwa Yoon:player#541> had received the Sub League 2 Player of the Week Award for his impressive play last week.\n\nAll week long he was terrific at the plate and won the honor with a .593 BA (16-for-27), no home runs and 4 RBIs.\n\nThus far this season <Yoon:player#541> has hit .562 with no home runs, 4 RBIs and scored 5 times.\n"), (370, "Sub League 1 Names Top Player", 881, 0, 0, 0, 0, 20, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 20, 0, 0, "2022-6-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "According to the voters, <Ted Murphy:player#881> of the <Grand Rapids Blue Jackets:team#20> had the best week of all Sub League 1 hitters as he was named this week\'s Player of the Week.\n\nThe center fielder\'s accomplishments include 12 hits in 24 at-bats, a .500 batting average, 6 home runs, 8 RBIs and 7 runs scored.\n\nThis season <Murphy:player#881> is batting .285 with 51 hits, 15 home runs, 35 RBIs, .340 OBP and has scored 27 runs.\n"), (371, "Shih Week\'s Top Player", 1141, 0, 0, 0, 0, 28, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 28, 0, 0, "2022-6-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "All week long nobody could get <Cho-yun Shih:player#1141> out in the Sub League 2 and that is the prime reason he was voted the Player of the Week.\n\nThe <Donna:team#28> right fielder took home the trophy by blasting 11 hits in 13 at-bats for a .846 batting average, driving in 2 runs and scoring 5 times.\n\n"), (372, "Great Week for Sparta\'s Manuel Valderrama ", 1235, 0, 0, 0, 0, 36, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 36, 0, 0, "2022-6-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Manuel Valderrama:player#1235> went on a week-long hitting spree against Sub League 1 pitchers and captured the Player of the Week honors.\n\nThe <Sparta:team#36> first baseman battered the opposition for 12 hits, 4 home runs, 8 RBI and scored 7 runs. He hit .480 and posted a .500 on-base percentage.\n\nThis season <Valderrama:player#1235> is hitting at a .275 pace with 16 home runs, 43 RBIs and has scored 36 times.\n"), (373, "Palacio Selected Top Player", 1391, 0, 0, 0, 0, 47, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 47, 0, 0, "2022-6-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week he took his hitting to another level. That\'s why <Manny Palacio:player#1391> of the <Pittsburgh Razorbacks:team#47> was named the Sub League 2 Player of the Week.\n\nFor the week the 25-year-old first baseman batted .615 (8-for-13) with 3 home runs, 6 runs and 4 RBIs.\n\n<Palacio:player#1391>\'s current batting average stands at .323 and he has chalked up 7 home runs and 18 RBIs.\n"), (374, "Contreras of Modesto SL1\'s Standout Player", 2030, 0, 0, 0, 0, 53, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 53, 0, 0, "2022-6-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Modesto:team#53> pitcher, <Isidro Contreras:player#2030>, was voted Sub League 1 Player of the Week for his standout pitching performance over the past seven days.\n\nThe 19-year-old hurler racked up a 2-0 record, 8 strikeouts and an ERA of 0.00. He held the opposition to a .078 average, surrendered 4 hits and walked 1.\n\nThis season <Contreras:player#2030> has compiled a 8-2 record with a 2.80 ERA.\n"), (375, "Peaches Bermudez Snags SL2 Player of the Week", 2413, 0, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 60, 0, 0, "2022-6-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week <Alex Bermudez:player#2413>, left fielder for the <Lubbock Peaches:team#60>, hit everything in sight to win the Sub League 2 Player of the Week trophy.\n\nHe rattled fences and pitchers as he banged out a .391 average and .462 on-base percentage. <Bermudez:player#2413> logged 9 hits in 23 at-bats, 3 home runs, 6 RBIs, 3 walks and scored 7 times.\n\nIn this current campaign <Bermudez:player#2413> is hitting at a .295 clip with 11 home runs and 26 RBIs.\n"), (376, "Blaylock Receives Updated Diagnosis", 2595, 0, 0, 0, 0, 47, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 47, 0, -5, "