SL1 Hitter of the Week", 80, 0, 0, 0, 0, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 2, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Baltimore Legion:team#2> center fielder <Steve Tugai:player#80> rose above the controversy surrounding his soon-to-expire contract, thriving under pressure last week and copping the Player of the Week award in the Sub League 1.\n\nTugai put up a .450 batting average (9-for-20) with 1 home run, 3 RBIs and scored 4 times.\n\nThis season <Tugai:player#80> has 1 home run and a .412 batting average.\n"), (397, "SL2 Player of the Week Awarded", 674, 0, 0, 0, 0, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 15, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Craig Gibson:player#674>, known affectionately as \"the old man\" by the younger players in the <Lions:team#15> clubhouse, showed his teammates how to do it last week -- and in the process the 38-year-old vet beat out all competition for the Sub League 2 Player of the Week Award.\n\nHe put up a .625 batting average, 15 hits in 24 at-bats, 4 home runs and 12 RBIs. <Gibson:player#674> also scored 7 runs.\n\nCurrently <Gibson:player#674> has 11 home runs and a .320 batting average.\n"), (398, "Star of the Week Honored in SL1", 126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 22, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Gary Landreth:player#126> finds himself in the Sub League 1 spotlight today after his impossible-to-ignore performance last week. He carried the <Chandler Capitals:team#22> on his shoulders, earning Sub League 1 Player of the Week honors.\n\nThe 27-year-old hit .476 (10-for-21) with 2 home runs and 12 RBI.\n\nSo far this year, <Landreth:player#126> is batting .328 with 9 home runs and 34 RBIs.\n"), (399, "Star of the Week Picked in SL2", 687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 30, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 30, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s Sub League 2 Player of the Week is <Jim Sterling:player#687> of the <Irving Badlanders:team#30>.\n\nHe ambushed SL2 pitching for 11 hits in 29 at-bats, 4 home runs and 6 RBIs, while hitting .379 and scoring 10 runs.\n\nIn his stats this season, <Sterling:player#687> has posted a batting average of .296 with 59 hits in 199 at-bats, 23 home runs and 44 RBIs. He has also scored 44 runs, walked 22 times and compiled a .372 OBP.\n"), (400, "Yoo Bags SL1 Best Player Award", 923, 0, 0, 0, 0, 34, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 34, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Henderson:team#34>\'s <Chang-woon Yoo:player#923> nabbed the latest Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award for his batting prowess this past week.\n\nPosting a hefty .462 average with 5 home runs, 8 RBIs and 9 runs scored, the 26-year-old is the toast of <Henderson:team#34> right now.\n\nThis year <Yoo:player#923> is hitting .299 with 12 home runs and 27 RBIs to his credit. He has gotten on base at a .352 clip and scored 29 runs.\n"), (401, "SL2\'s #1 Player Named", 1634, 0, 0, 0, 0, 42, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 42, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Gus Garcia:player#1634> went on a hitting spree last week against Sub League 2 pitchers and today copped the Player of the Week Award.\n\nThe <St. Petersburg Naturals:team#42> left fielder peppered the opposition with 10 hits in 21 at-bats, 3 home runs, 5 RBIs and 8 runs scored. In the last 7 games he hit .476 with an on-base percentage of .542.\n\nGarcia is hitting .480 this year with 4 home runs, 7 RBIs and 9 runs scored. He has 12 hits in 25 at-bats, 3 walks and a .536 on-base percentage. <Garcia:player#1634> has played in 8 games.\n"), (402, "SL1 Votes Zips St. Clair Top Player", 1764, 0, 0, 0, 0, 54, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 54, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "When it came to hitting the baseball, <Dan St. Clair:player#1764> had few peers in the Sub League 1 this past week.\n\nThe talented left fielder for Oak View tagged opposing pitchers for a .435 average and was voted the Player of the Week Award. Included in his stats were 10 hits in 23 at-bats, 2 homers, 6 runs scored and 6 RBIs.\n\nIn 60 games this year St. Clair has posted a .280 average and put up these numbers: 10 home runs, 35 RBIs and 30 runs scored.\n"), (403, "Carrillo Wins SL2 Player of the Week Trophy", 1157, 0, 0, 0, 0, 63, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 63, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 2 has named its Top Player of the Week. The honor went to <Alex Carrillo:player#1157>, first baseman of the <Starks Westerners:team#63>.\n\nIn an extraordinary hitting display, he belted out hits at a .320 pace to win the award. <Carrillo:player#1157> went 8-for-25 for the week, totaled 4 home runs, 14 RBIs and scored 6 times.\n\nIn his season totals, <Carrillo:player#1157> has 5 home runs, .222 BA, .275 OBP, 20 RBIs and 9 runs scored. He has played in 22 games.\n"), (404, "Weekly Team Power Rankings", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 0, 2, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Here are the current team power rankings for Fictional Baseball League:\n\nTeams (Total Points, Tendency):\n1) <San Francisco Valley Cats:team#9> (127.8, o)\n2) <Chicago Quakes:team#12> (107.1, +)\n3) <Brooklyn Storm:team#6> (104.0, -)\n4) <Jacksonville Orange Sox:team#1> (102.1, +)\n5) <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8> (96.1, -)\n6) <Boston Wild Riders:team#16> (92.7, +)\n7) <Baltimore Legion:team#2> (92.4, ++)\n8) <San Diego Fighting Knights:team#5> (90.0, +)\n9) <San Jose Spiders:team#7> (89.0, o)\n10) <Houston Seagulls:team#10> (88.8, --)\n11) <El Paso Lions:team#15> (86.6, o)\n12) <Charlotte Nailers:team#11> (86.2, --)\n13) <Detroit Cannons:team#4> (76.9, o)\n14) <Memphis T-Bones:team#3> (70.8, o)\n15) <Fort Worth Shamrocks:team#13> (68.4, o)\n16) <New York Owls:team#14> (62.2, o)\n"), (405, "Weekly Team Power Rankings", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 0, 2, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-6-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Here are the current team power rankings for FBL Triple A:\n\nTeams (Total Points, Tendency):\n1) <Chandler Capitals:team#22> (123.8, ++)\n2) <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> (120.0, -)\n3) <Fair Haven Earthquakes:team#25> (114.7, -)\n4) <S