ns.\n\nSo far this season <Esquivel:player#1230> has picked up no saves in 13 relief appearances. He has also compiled a 1-1 won-lost mark with a 4.61 ERA and fanned 9 batters in 13.2 innings.\n"), (423, "Morales Whacks 3 out of the Park for Greendale", 172, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 17, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 19, 0, 0, "2022-6-19", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<John Morales:player#172> brutalized the <Mannford Monsters:team#17> pitching staff, launching three home runs in today\'s 6-5 victory at Blue Raiders Ballpark. The <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> right fielder was red-hot, the ball just exploding off his bat all day.\n\n\"I don\'t try to hit homers,\" he said later. \"I try to go out there and put a good swing on the ball, and sometimes it is going to go out of the park. I didn\'t try to hit the first one or the second one or the third one.\"\n\nFor the game, he went 3-for-4 with 3 RBIs and 3 runs scored.\n\n\"Too much <John Morales:player#172> today,\" Monsters manager <Tim Goodnight:coach#213> said. \"That\'s my assessment of the game. That\'s what our problems boiled down to.\"\n\n<John Morales:player#172> hit a solo-shot off <Mike Campbell:player#1279> in the 1st, hit a solo-shot off <Mike Campbell:player#1279> in the 3rd, flied out in the 5th and hit a solo-shot off <Tommy Lomas:player#618> in the 7th.\n\nBatting .254 to date, Morales has 8 home runs and 19 RBIs.\n"), (424, "Buonconte Smacks 5 Hits for T-Bones", 211, 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 2, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 3, 0, 0, "2022-6-19", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Memphis T-Bones:team#3> right fielder <Hector Buonconte:player#211> had a day to remember at Ballpark of Memphis today, ripping apart the <Baltimore Legion:team#2> and sparking the T-Bones to a 3-2 victory.\n\nBuonconte wrote his name in the record books with a 5-hit barrage, finishing his special day 5-for-8. \n\n\"I\'m usually a first ball hitter,\" <Buonconte:player#211> told BNN reporters in the postgame press conference. \"I think pitchers think batters are going to let the first one go by. I never do. I\'ve always found that it\'s better to pull the trigger early in the count. Pitchers get real nasty when they get ahead of you, so I try to avoid it.\"\n\n<Hector Buonconte:player#211> doubled in the 1st, singled in the 3rd, struck out in the 5th, grounded out in the 8th, singled in the 10th, singled in the 12th, grounded out in the 15th and singled in the 17th.\n\nThis season <Buonconte:player#211> is batting .297 with 1 home run. He has scored 16 runs and driven in 11.\n\n<View Boxscore:box#278>\n"), (425, "Star of the Week Named in SL1", 251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 8, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 1 made it official today: <Justin DeMascio:player#251> is the Player of the Week.\n\nHe really stood out on the diamond this week with a .417 average to take home the award. The <Phoenix:team#8> first baseman went 10-for-24, drove in 10 runs, scored 7 times and hit 4 home runs.\n\nSo far this year <DeMascio:player#251> has 20 home runs and a .328 batting average.\n"), (426, "Welch Picked SL2 Player of the Week", 675, 0, 0, 0, 0, 15, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 15, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Ken Welch:player#675> did nothing to hurt his value as an upcoming free agent last week, making contact with the ball at every opportunity and reeling in the Sub League 2 Player of the Week Award.\n\nThe second baseman hit .591 for the <Lions:team#15>, recording 13 hits in 22 at-bats, no home runs, 8 RBIs and 6 runs scored.\n\nPresently <Welch:player#675> is hitting .286 with 3 home runs and 24 RBIs. He has played in 62 games and scored 21 times.\n"), (427, "Rios Collects Player of the Week Award", 793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 23, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 23, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Micah Rios:player#793> went on a week-long hitting spree against Sub League 1 pitchers and captured the Player of the Week honors.\n\nThe <Jersey City:team#23> first baseman battered the opposition for 10 hits, 4 home runs, 13 RBI and scored 10 runs. He hit .417 and posted a .500 on-base percentage.\n\nThis season <Rios:player#793> has banged out 58 hits in 193 at-bats for a .301 average with 15 home runs. He is getting on base at a .395 pace and his totals also include 48 RBIs and 38 runs scored.\n"), (428, "Red-Hot Sterling SL2 Player of the Week", 687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 30, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 30, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week he took his hitting to another level. That\'s why <Jim Sterling:player#687> of the <Irving Badlanders:team#30> was named the Sub League 2 Player of the Week.\n\nFor the week the 30-year-old first baseman batted .375 (9-for-24) with 3 home runs, 5 runs and 8 RBIs.\n\nSo far this season Sterling is hitting .305 with 26 home runs, 52 RBIs and 49 runs scored. He has 68 hits in 223 at-bats and a .379 OBP. \n"), (429, "SL1 Names Blue Wings Luna Winner", 845, 0, 0, 0, 0, 39, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 39, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week <Israel Luna:player#845>, first baseman for the <Anaheim Blue Wings:team#39>, hit everything in sight to win the Sub League 1 Player of the Week trophy.\n\nHe rattled fences and pitchers as he banged out a .455 average and .538 on-base percentage. <Luna:player#845> logged 10 hits in 22 at-bats, 5 home runs, 11 RBIs, 3 walks and scored 5 times.\n\nOn the season, <Luna:player#845> is batting .312 with 9 home runs and 31 RBIs. He has played in 38 games.\n"), (430, "Week\'s Top Player: Corpus Christi\'s Walker", 1547, 0, 0, 0, 0, 46, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 46, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Corpus Christi sports fans can\'t stop singing the praises of <Corey Walker:player#1547>, who has been selected the Sub League 2 Player of the Week.\n\n<Walker:player#1547> was in a comfort zone all week, finishing with a .429 average (9-for-21), 6 RBIs and 4 home runs. \n\nSo far this season <Walker:player#1547> has gotten 82 hits in 254 at-bats for a .323 batting average with 13 home runs. His stats include 28 RBIs and 34 runs scored. He has played in 65 games.\n"), (431, "SL1\'s Top Player, Cooley of Cincinnati", 3007, 0, 0, 0, 0, 51, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 51, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Brady Cooley:player#3007> kept his eye on the ball last week and now all eyes are on him. The <Cincinnati Tropics:team#51> second baseman easily swung his way to the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award with 11 hits in 23 at-bats.\n\nCooley hit .478 last week with 1 home run, 6 RBIs and 4 runs scored.\n\nOn the year <Cooley:player#3007> has hit .378 with 2 home runs, 9 RBIs and scored 5 runs.\n"), (432, "Eastman of Plainview Crowned Best Player", 1863, 0, 0, 0, 0, 58, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 58, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s Player of the Week was <Dustin Eastman:player#1863> of the <Plainview Power:team#58>.\n\nHis big bat waylaid Sub League 2 pitching for 11 hits in 23 at-bats, 6 home runs and 11 RBIs while hitting .478 and scoring 7 runs.\n\nThis year <Eastman:player#1863> is hitting .267 with 10 home runs.\n"), (433, "Latest Injury Report on Amaro", 1199, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 10, 0, -5, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The season will end prematurely for <John Amaro:player#1199>, the <Houston:team#10> starting pitcher. He suffered a torn back muscle on 06/18/2022, an injury that is serious enough to knock him out of action for the rest of the year. Amaro was not available for comment.\n\nOn the season <Amaro:player#1199> has 1 win and 3 losses and a 7.85 ERA.\n"), (434, "Weekly Team Power Rankings", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 0, 2, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-6-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Here are the current team power rankings for Fictional Baseball League:\n\nTeams (Total Points, Tendency):\n1) <San Francisco Valley Cats:team#9> (127.4, o)\n2) <El Paso Lions:team#15> (110.3, ++)\n3) <Chicago Quakes:team#12> (108.4, -)\n4) <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8> (104.7, +)\n5) <Brooklyn Storm:team#6> (98.7, -)\n6) <Jacks