ting three balls out of Renegades Park to help the Razorbacks take the 10-9 victory.\n\n\"I got some good pitches to hit and I creamed them,\" he said after the game. \"The first was a big, fat fastball and the last two were hanging curves. All three were mistakes.\"\n\nFor the game, Paisley went 3-for-4 with 7 RBIs and 3 runs scored.\n\n\"There\'s a fine line between hitting home runs and line drives,\" Pittsburgh manager Ryan Bower said later. \"Seems like Melvin found his home run stroke today.\"\n\n<Melvin Paisley:player#1712> hit a two-run home run off <Corey Swift:player#45> in the 2nd, hit a three-run home run off <Corey Swift:player#45> in the 4th, grounded out in the 5th, hit a two-run home run off <Jaden Winterstein:player#35> in the 7th and walked in the 9th.\n\n<Paisley:player#1712> on the season is hitting .233 with 12 home runs. His stats include 26 RBIs and 27 runs scored.\n"), (459, "Rowdy Players Suspended by League", 2890, 3038, 0, 0, 0, 95, 89, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 95, 0, 0, "2022-6-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Baseball officials have suspended two players for \"inappropriate and aggressive conduct\" in yesterday\'s <Adel:team#95>-<Irvine:team#89> contest at Red Foxes Grounds. The Red Foxes <Danny Lugo:player#2890> and the Drillers <Phil Peggins:player#3038> will have to sit out 5 and 6 games respectively for their parts in the brawl. \n\nFor the year <Lugo:player#2890> has hit at a .231 clip with 3 RBIs, 2 home runs and 2 runs scored.\n\n"), (460, "SL1 Player of the Week Named", 351, 0, 0, 0, 0, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 7, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<San Jose Spiders:team#7> left fielder <Ichiro Yamamoto:player#351> walked away with the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award today after putting up some impressive numbers over the past seven days.\n\n\"The <Spiders:team#7> fans are really behind me right now,\" said the 32-year-old. \"That helps. They give you the confidence to go out there and do better.\"\n\n<Yamamoto:player#351> batted .393 (11-for-28) with 3 home runs and 13 RBIs this week on his way to the award.\n\n<Yamamoto:player#351> has collected 79 hits for the <Spiders:team#7> this year, 12 of them home runs. He has also netted 45 RBIs and scored 36 runs while batting .306. \n"), (461, "Week\'s Premier Performer Honored by SL2", 580, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 10, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Israel Salazar:player#580> of the Houston Seagulls had an enormous week at the plate and today was voted the Player of the Week by the Sub League 2.\n\nFor the week <Salazar:player#580> batted .556 (15-for-27) with 2 home runs and 5 RBIs.\n\nSo far this season, <Salazar:player#580> has recorded a .384 batting average with 117 hits, 13 home runs, 51 RBIs, 61 runs scored and a .428 OBP.\n"), (462, "Juan Tobar Captures SL1 Award", 929, 0, 0, 0, 0, 17, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 17, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was announced today by the Sub League 1 that <Mannford:team#17> second baseman <Juan Tobar:player#929> had received the Player of the Week Trophy for his superlative play last week.\n\nDuring his week-long batting binge he reeled off a .360 batting average, 9 hits and 4 home runs. <Tobar:player#929> also racked up 5 RBIs and scored 5 runs.\n\nTobar is batting .243 this year with 5 home runs, 7 RBIs and 7 runs scored. He has 18 hits in 74 at-bats.\n"), (463, "Apple Sox Gustavo Cavazos Swings Hot Bat, SL2 Winner", 1086, 0, 0, 0, 0, 32, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 32, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 2 made it official today: <Gustavo Cavazos:player#1086> is the Player of the Week.\n\nHe really sparkled on the diamond this week with a .400 average to take home the trophy. The <Sioux City:team#32> right fielder went 10-for-25, drove in 14 runs, scored 8 times and hit 4 home runs.\n\nSo far this year <Cavazos:player#1086> has hit .245 with 9 home runs, 28 RBIs and 19 runs scored.\n"), (464, "SL1 Awards Player of the Week Trophy", 1738, 0, 0, 0, 0, 35, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 35, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Todd White:player#1738> of the <Buffalo Sluggers:team#35> was locked in all week as he bullied the pitchers he faced. <White:player#1738> put up some great numbers and hauled in the Sub League 1 Player of the Week trophy.\n\nHe hit .500 with 2 home runs and 4 RBIs. The 23-year-old left fielder also scored 8 runs and for the week went 12-for-24.\n\nCurrently White is batting .305 with 13 home runs, 38 RBIs and 43 runs scored.\n"), (465, "SL2 Presents Player of the Week Trophy", 1712, 0, 0, 0, 0, 47, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 47, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "All week long <Melvin Paisley:player#1712> was the toughest out in the Sub League 2 and that is the prime reason he was voted the Player of the Week.\n\nThe <Pittsburgh:team#47> right fielder rapped out 7 hits in 18 at-bats for a .389 batting average, drove in 11 runs and scored 7 times.\n\nFor the year <Paisley:player#1712> is hitting .233 with 12 home runs. His stats include 26 runs batted in and 27 runs scored.\n"), (466, "Ellis Earns SL1 Player of the Week", 3183, 0, 0, 0, 0, 53, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 53, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The votes have been cast and counted and the winner of the Sub League 1 Player of the Week has been chosen. It was presented earlier today to <Steve Ellis:player#3183> for his red-hot week of hitting.\n\nThe <Modesto:team#53> center fielder took home the trophy by splurging with 10 hits in 25 at-bats for a .400 batting average, driving in 8 runs and scoring 5 times.\n\nIn 19 games this season <Ellis:player#3183> has batted at a .307 pace with 23 hits and 8 home runs.\n"), (467, "SL2\'s Best Player, Edwards of Des Moines", 1885, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 57, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 2 has selected its Player of the Week and the honor went to <Justin Edwards:player#1885>, <Des Moines:team#57>\'s fine first baseman.\n\nFor the week he batted .545 (6-for-11) with 2 home runs, 3 runs and 2 RBIs.\n\nEdwards is currently batting .244 with 11 home runs, 22 RBIs and 23 runs scored. He has 39 hits in 160 at-bats.\n"), (468, "Big Bat Pays Off, Grant Player of the Week", 3146, 0, 0, 0, 0, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 71, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "When it came to hitting the baseball, <Chris Grant:player#3146> was in a class by himself in the Sub League 1 this past week. Nobody did it better.\n\nThe outstanding catcher for Belcourt tagged opposing pitchers for a .571 average and was voted the Player of the Week Award. Included in his stats were 8 hits in 14 at-bats, 2 homers, 4 runs scored and 4 RBIs.\n\n"), (469, "SL2 Names Best Player", 3242, 0, 0, 0, 0, 78, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 78, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 2 has selected <Matt Wyatt:player#3242> of the <St. Louis Lopes:team#78> as Player of the Week.\n\nHe hit .526 (10-for-19) this past week collecting 9 RBIs, scored 6 runs and hit 2 home runs.\n\n"), (470, "Chavez Sub League 1\'s Hottest Hitter", 353, 0, 0, 0, 0, 84, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 84, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week <Jose Chavez:player#353>, left fielder for the <Colchester Victory:team#84>, hit his way to the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award.\n\n<Chavez:player#353> put on a hitting clinic with a .448 average as he belted and battered SL1 pitchers for 13 hits in 29 at-bats, no home runs, 5 RBIs and scored 5 runs.\n\n"), (471, "SL2\'s Top Player Named", 2756, 0, 0, 0, 0, 90, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 90, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Travis Bramlett:player#2756> must have thought he was in seventh heaven this week. First he went on a sensational hitting spree, belting the ball at a .429 pace, then the <Wilkes-Barre:team#90> right fielder finds out he has been selected the top performer and gets the Sub League 2 Player of the Week Award.\n\nAsked what his hitting philosophy was, <Bramlett:player#2756> quipped to the BNN reporters, \"Well, my theory of hitting is to just watch the ball as it comes in and hit it.\"\n\nIt was a good week\'s work for Bramlett. He hit .429 average (9-for-21) with 3 home runs and 3 RBIs.\n\n"), (472, "Rivas to Miss 5 Months", 563, 0, 0, 0, 0, 42, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 42, 0, -5, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Brad Rivas:player#563>, the <St. Petersburg:team#42> reliever, was less than thrilled to learn that his recent injury would keep him out of the rest of the season and any postseason action.\n\n\"The playoffs?\" he said. \"Are you kidding me? The playoffs?\"\n\nRivas has bone chips in his elbow, an injury that has hampered him since 06/26/2022.\n\nFor the season <Rivas:player#563> is 2-and-1 with no saves and a 3.19 ERA. He has given up 29 hits in 36.2 innings with 23 strikeouts.\n"), (473, "Trouble in San Francisco, Hernandez Suffers Setback", 726, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<San Francisco Valley Cats:team#9> third baseman <Jose Hernandez:player#726> is not healing as well as expected as he recovers from a strained oblique and will miss an additional 2 weeks as a result. <Hernandez:player#726> had been working with the team medical staff, but was taken to a specialist as a precaution. Examination revealed more damage than originally thought.\n\n<Hernandez:player#726> is presently batting .316 with 21 home runs, 42 runs scored and 67 RBIs. His OBP is .391.\n"), (474, "Brooklyn\'s Gaytan Diagnosis Revealed", 805, 0, 0, 0, 0, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 6, 0, -5, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Brooklyn Storm:team#6> have lost the services of <Fernando Gaytan:player#805> for the rest of this season. He suffered a damaged elbow ligament in a recent ballgame and the follow-up report from the medical staff is not good. Gaytan is out for the year.\n\nTo this point in the season, <Gaytan:player#805> shows a 7-2 record, 16 starts, 87.2 innings, 75 strikeouts and a 2.98 ERA.\n"), (475, "Injury Brings Season to End for Hall", 2952, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 57, 0, -5, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Obviously disappointed, <Geoff Hall:player#2952> confirmed today that his season is officially over. The <Des Moines:team#57> starting pitcher offered mostly monosyllabic responses to reporters. \"Nope,\" he said, when asked if he might possibly return this year. The 20-year-old Hall suffered shoulder inflammation on 06/23/2022 and has been out of action since.\n\nOn the season <Hall:player#2952> has a 5-2 record with a 3.86 ERA.\n"), (476, "Weekly Team Power Rankings", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 0, 2, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Here are the current team power rankings for Fictional Baseball League:\n\nTeams (Total Points, Tendency):\n1) <San Francisco Valley Cats:team#9> (123.4, o)\n2) <Chicago Quakes:team#12> (112.6, +)\n3) <Brooklyn Storm:team#6> (105.5, +)\n4) <Houston Seagulls:team#10> (102.9, ++)\n5) <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8> (101.8, -)\n6) <El Paso Lions:team#15> (101.0, --)\n7) <Detroit Cannons:team#4> (98.5, ++)\n8) <Jacksonville Orange Sox:team#1> (97.1, -)\n9) <San Diego Fighting Knights:team#5> (91.3, -)\n10) <Baltimore Legion:team#2> (86.7, -)\n11) <San Jose Spiders:team#7> (81.4, o)\n12) <Boston Wild Riders:team#16> (78.8, -)\n13) <Charlotte Nailers:team#11> (78.8, o)\n14) <New York Owls:team#14> (63.2, +)\n15) <Fort Worth Shamrocks:team#13> (60.3, o)\n16) <Memphis T-Bones:team#3> (56.2, -)\n"), (477, "Weekly Team Power Rankings", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 0, 2, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-6-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Here are the current team power rankings for FBL Triple A:\n\nTeams (Total Points, Tendency):\n1) <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> (124.7, o)\n2) <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> (119.1, +)\n3) <Irving Badlanders:team#30> (114.5, +)\n4) <Fair Haven Earthquakes:team#25> (112.0, -)\n5) <Cypress Royals:team#31> (110.4, ++)\n6) <Chandler Capitals:team#22> (108.0, -)\n7) <Donna Whitecaps