3 home runs, 13 hits in 30 at-bats, 10 RBIs and 8 runs.\n\nThat kind of hitting earned him the SL2 Player of the Week honors. \n\nThis season <Martinez:player#495> is swinging the bat at a .300 pace. He has hit 22 home runs and scored 63 times, while driving in 55. His on-base percentage is .338 and he has played in 74 games.\n"), (565, "Workman Wins SL1 Best Player Award", 773, 0, 0, 0, 0, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 24, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Joe Workman:player#773> must have thought he died and went to heaven this week. First he went on a remarkable batting rampage, hammering the ball at a .423 clip, then the <North Hempstead:team#24> third baseman finds out he has been voted the league\'s top performer and gets the SL1 Player of the Week Award.\n\nFor the week <Workman:player#773> batted .423 (11-for-26) with 3 home runs and 10 RBIs.\n\nPresently <Workman:player#773> is batting .278 and has collected 19 home runs, 52 RBIs, .355 OBP and scored 40 runs.\n"), (566, "Irving\'s Sterling Snaps Up Player of the Week", 687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 30, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 30, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The hottest bat of the week belonged to <Irving:team#30> first baseman <Jim Sterling:player#687>.\n\nHe went on a rampage last week against SL2 hurlers and rapped out 13 hits in 32 at-bats for a .406 average while hitting 5 home runs, driving in 10 runs and scoring 8 runs -- numbers quite worthy of the Sub League 2 Player of the Week trophy.\n\n<Sterling:player#687> was honored today at a press conference.\n\nThis season <Sterling:player#687> is batting .312 with 95 hits, 33 home runs, 67 RBIs, 32 walks, .383 OBP and has scored 62 runs. He has played in 78 games.\n"), (567, "Walters on the Attack, Player of the Week", 1375, 0, 0, 0, 0, 38, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 38, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Aaron Walters:player#1375> of the Seattle Invaders had a fantastic week and today was voted the Player of the Week by the Sub League 1.\n\nFor the week <Walters:player#1375> batted .419 (13-for-31) with 3 home runs and 12 RBIs.\n\nThis season <Walters:player#1375> is batting .270 with 42 RBIs, 35 runs scored and 12 home runs.\n"), (568, "SL2 Awards Player of the Week", 1469, 0, 0, 0, 0, 42, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 42, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Carlos Montalvan:player#1469> of the <St. Petersburg Naturals:team#42> has just enjoyed one of the better weeks of his career. That fact was not lost on Sub League 2 officials, who named him Player of the Week.\n\nMontalvan logged a .400 batting average for the <St. Petersburg Naturals:team#42>, racking up 11 RBIs and 6 home runs.\n\nThis year <Montalvan:player#1469> has batted at a .306 pace with 92 hits, 27 home runs, 61 RBIs and scored 53 times.\n"), (569, "Sub League 1 Names Burns Best Batter", 2126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 54, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 54, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Pitchers who faced the <Oak View Zips:team#54> last week were happy to see <Bob Burns:player#2126> in the rear-view mirror. The 20-year-old right fielder was dubbed the Sub League 1 Player of the Week for a 7-game tear that saw him hit at a .481 clip.\n\nFor the week he also chalked up 13 hits in 27 at-bats, 2 home runs, 5 RBIs and 6 runs scored.\n\nTo date this year <Burns:player#2126> is batting .288 with 15 home runs. \n"), (570, "Player of the Week: Hoagland\'s Sassetti", 1527, 0, 0, 0, 0, 59, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 59, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s premier performer in the Sub League 2 was third baseman <Javier Sassetti:player#1527> of the <Hoagland Killer Whales:team#59>.\n\nHe banged out a .550 average and was voted the Player of the Week. Over the last week <Sassetti:player#1527> socked 11 hits in 20 at-bats and 3 home runs, drove in 10 runs and scored 6 times.\n\nSo far this year in 28 games Sassetti is hitting .360 with 6 home runs, 25 RBIs and 10 runs scored.\n"), (571, "Week\'s Best Player Honored by SL1", 3127, 0, 0, 0, 0, 72, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 72, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Player of the Week has been announced by the Sub League 1. The award went to <Ash Burman:player#3127>, shortstop of the <Spokane A\'s:team#72>.\n\nHe dominated league pitchers with a .429 average to win the honor. <Burman:player#3127> went 12-for-28 for the week, totaled 3 home runs with 7 RBIs and scored 3 times.\n\nIn the current season, <Burman:player#3127> has put up a .472 batting average with 17 hits, 4 home runs, 12 runs batted in and scored 6 runs.\n"), (572, "Dietrick Chosen #1 Player", 1427, 0, 0, 0, 0, 74, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 74, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The votes have been tallied and the winner of the Sub League 2 Player of the Week has been named. It was awarded earlier today to <Mike Dietrick:player#1427> for his great week at the plate.\n\nThe <Wellston:team#74> right fielder took home the trophy by banging out 7 hits in 16 at-bats for a .438 batting average, driving in 6 runs and scoring 5 times.\n\nIn 2022 <Dietrick:player#1427> has hit at a .409 clip with 9 hits, 4 home runs, 6 RBIs and has scored 5 times.\n"), (573, "Owls Joe Gerardi Wins SL1 Award", 3199, 0, 0, 0, 0, 82, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 82, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was a week to remember for <Joe Gerardi:player#3199>. After wrapping up a torrid week at the plate, the <Stockton Owls:team#82> left fielder was named the Sub League 1 Player of the Week.\n\nGerardi collected 9 hits in 26 at-bats for a .346 average. He also accounted for 8 RBIs, 4 home runs and scored 9 runs.\n\nLooking at his stats this year, <Gerardi:player#3199> has compiled a .277 batting average, while hitting 5 home runs and driving in 11 runs. He has played in 19 games and scored 11 runs.\n"), (574, "Red-Hot Rampage Reaps SL2 Reward", 2755, 0, 0, 0, 0, 90, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 90, 0, 0, "2022-7-11", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Sub League 2 pitchers will attest that it was tough to get <Josh Westfall:player#2755> of