s and 21-year old minor league SS <Angel Martinez:player#2470> and 24-year old minor league RHP <Alex Reyes:player#1362> to the Cannons. \"Only time will tell if this is the right move for everyone,\" stated the <San Jose:team#7> GM.\n\n\nThis season <Baes:player#164> is batting .244 with 72 hits and 7 home runs. He has scored 33 times and has 25 RBI.\n"), (636, "Rowdy Players Suspended by League", 721, 1282, 0, 0, 0, 9, 13, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-7-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Baseball officials have suspended two players for \"inappropriate and aggressive conduct\" in yesterday\'s <San Francisco:team#9>-<Fort Worth:team#13> contest at Valley Cats Park. The Valley Cats <Andy Rodriguez:player#721> and the Shamrocks <Dusty Martz:player#1282> will have to sit out 4 and 9 games respectively for their parts in the brawl. \n\nThis season <Rodriguez:player#721> is batting .272 with 34 home runs.\n\nCurrently <Martz:player#1282> has 30 relief appearances, saving 2. His record is 3-5 with 13 strikeouts in 28.2 innings and a 7.53 ERA. \n"), (637, "Walker Belts 5 Hits", 1547, 0, 0, 0, 0, 46, 42, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 46, 0, 0, "2022-7-19", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Speaking with reporters after a dominating hitting performance, <Corey Walker:player#1547> said his club\'s tilt with the <St. Petersburg Naturals:team#42> \"felt almost like batting practice.\" The 23-year-old first baseman went a remarkable 5-for-7 at the plate.\n\n\"I saw the ball well and could just about hit it anywhere I wanted,\" he recalled later. \n\nHowever, his sensational day wasn\'t enough for the <Corpus Christi Fighters:team#46>, who were topped by the Naturals, 7-5.\n\n\"It\'s a good lesson for him, I guess,\" Fighters manager Ketevan Shakhsevev said. \"Sometimes Corey is going to lose. But I would rather him go 5-for-7 and lose than go 0-for-7 and lose.\" \n\n<Corey Walker:player#1547> doubled in the 1st, grounded out in the 4th, singled in the 6th, singled in the 8th, hit an RBI single in the 9th, singled in the 12th and flied out in the 14th.\n\nThus far this season <Walker:player#1547> has hit .295 with 16 home runs, 36 RBIs and scored 42 times.\n"), (638, "de Anda Receives Updated Diagnosis", 1301, 0, 0, 0, 0, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 22, 0, -5, "2022-7-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Chandler Capitals:team#22> have lost the services of <Juan de Anda:player#1301> for the rest of this season. He suffered a torn flexor tendon in his elbow in a recent ballgame and the follow-up report from the medical staff is not good. de Anda is out for the year.\n\n<de Anda:player#1301> has made 18 starts, tossed 102.2 innings, struck out 96 batters and walked 32. His record is 9-3 with a 3.86 ERA and he has limited other teams to a .234 batting average.\n"), (639, "Phoenix, Fort Worth Agree to Swap", 1964, 624, 0, 0, 0, 8, 13, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 1, 3, 5, 8, 0, 0, "2022-7-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Nick Rubeck:coach#50>, general manager of the <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8>, has signed off on a trade for <Fort Worth:team#13>\'s 26-year old RHP <Jose Vasquez:player#624>. To complete the deal, the Lumberjacks will send 24-year old minor league 2B <Matt Szymkowiak:player#1964> to the Shamrocks.\n\n\nThis season <Vasquez:player#624> has logged 3 saves. He has thrown 34.1 innings, dished out 27 strikeouts and walked 8 while putting up a 0-6 mark and a 6.55 ERA.\n"), (640, "Brawlers Selkirk Smacks 5 Hits", 1027, 0, 0, 0, 0, 29, 32, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 29, 0, 0, "2022-7-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Rex Selkirk:player#1027> really sizzled at the plate in today\'s 5-4 win over Apple Sox. The <Tampa:team#29> first baseman blistered <Sioux City:team#32> for 5 hits in 5 at-bats. \n\n\"Selkirk was too tough to get out today,\" the Apple Sox skipper said in the postgame interview. \"No matter what we threw him, he hit it. And he hit some good pitches, too.\" \n\n<Rex Selkirk:player#1027> singled in the 1st, hit an RBI double in the 3rd, singled in the 4th, hit a solo-shot off <Tomas Garza:player#1251> in the 6th and hit a solo-shot off <Frank Kral:player#87> in the 8th.\n\n<Selkirk:player#1027> has collected 56 hits for the <Brawlers:team#29> this year, 8 of them home runs. He has also netted 22 RBIs and scored 28 runs while batting .276. \n"), (641, "El Paso, Baltimore Swap Players ", 1418, 57, 0, 0, 0, 15, 2, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 1, 3, 5, 15, 0, 0, "2022-7-21", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <El Paso Lions:team#15> have parted ways with 23-year old minor league 2B <Chris McCall:player#1418> in a trade with the <Baltimore Legion:team#2> for 31-year old RHP <Chris Roberson:player#57>. Lions general manager Hock confirmed the deal in an announcement this morning.\n\n\nThis season <Roberson:player#57> has been credited with 1 save. In 34 relief appearances and 41 innings he has a 2-3 won-lost mark, 3.95 ERA and 37 strikeouts\n"), (642, "Mora Hears from Medical Staff", 572, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 10, 0, -5, "2022-7-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Obviously disappointed, <Elias Mora:player#572> confirmed today that his season is officially over. The <Houston:team#10> closer offered mostly monosyllabic responses to reporters. \"Nope,\" he said, when asked if he might possibly return this year. The 29-year-old Mora suffered a torn flexor tendon in his elbow on 07/19/2022 and has been out of action since.\n\nFor the season <Mora:player#572> has earned 29 saves, worked 41.2 innings, fanned 44 hitters and recorded a 3.24 ERA. He has held opposing teams to a .245 batting average.\n"), (643, "Larocque, Sanchez Swap Teams", 872, 497, 0, 0, 0, 12, 11, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 1, 3, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-7-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Sometimes a change of scenery can be a beneficial to a baseball player. That is the hope in <Chicago:team#12> and <Charlotte:team#11> as the teams came to an agreement today which sends 20-year old minor league 2B <Danny Larocque:player#872> to the Nailers and 26-year old C <Victor Sanchez:player#497> to the Quakes. \"Only time will tell if this is the right move for everyone,\" stated the <Charlotte:team#11> GM.\n\n\nThis season <Sanchez:player#497> is batting .197 with 13 hits, 1 home run, 11 RBIs, .303 OBP and has scored 7 runs.\n"), (644, "Aguilera Slams 5 Hits for Boston", 392, 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 11, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 16, 0, 0, "2022-7-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was a good day for the Wild Riders at Wild Riders Stadium as they clipped the <Charlotte Nailers:team#11>, 12-1. It was tremendous day for <Daniel Aguilera:player#392>, who was on a hitting barrage at the plate, finishing 5-for-5. \n\n\"I don\'t know what to call that,\" the <Boston:team#16> first baseman told reporters after his big performance. \"I\'m not \'dialed in\' or \'in a zone,\' I just try to keep it simple. Basically the pitcher throws the ball, I try to pick up the spin, then I hit it. Today I picked up the spin pretty well.\" \n\n<Daniel Aguilera:player#392> doubled in the 1st, singled in the 3rd, hit an RBI single in the 5th, singled in the 7th and hit a solo-shot off <Kyle Fritz:player#1440> in the 8th.\n\nThis season <Aguilera:player#392> is batting .278 with 5 home runs. He has scored 46 runs and driven in 25.\n\n<View Boxscore:box#1033>\n"), (645, "Kirk and Goff Suspended for Free-for-All", 2174, 2108, 0, 0, 0, 93, 94, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 93, 0, 0, "2022-7-23", 0, 1, -1, 0, "After an intense confrontation, both the Cannoneers <Zak Kirk:player#2174> and the Sparks <John Goff:player#2108> were handed their punishments today. The league commissioner\'s office issued suspensions for an on-the-field conflict that occurred at a recent <Scottsdale:team#93>-<Yonkers:team#94> game. <Zak Kirk:player#2174> will miss 3 games, while <John Goff:player#2108> was suspended for 7 games.\n\n\"Sometimes we go too far and have to pay the consequences,\" <Zak Kirk:player#2174> commented later. \"Hopefully cooler heads will prevail the next time we play.\"\n\nThis season <Kirk:player#2174> is hitting at a .364 pace with no home runs, 0 RBIs and has scored 2 times.\n\nThis season <Goff:player#2108> has logged no saves. He has thrown 12.1 innings, dished out 16 strikeouts and walked 6 while putting up a 1-1 mark and a 2.19 ERA.\n"), (646, "Johnson\'s Treatment Not Going Well, Suffers Setback", 630, 0, 0, 0, 0, 13, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 13, 0, 0, "2022-7-24", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Team doctors reported that the pace of recovery for <Jason Johnson:player#630> has been hampered by several recent setbacks and they have reassessed his injury situation. If all goes well, the <Fort Worth Shamrocks:team#13> shortstop should rejoin the club in 6-7 weeks. <Johnson:player#630> is suffering from a fractured rib. \n\n<Jason Johnson:player#630> is expected to undergo surgery in Fort Worth(Texas) tomorrow.\n\nThis year <Johnson:player#630> is batting .310 with 2 home runs and 30 RBIs. In 64 games he has scored 43 times.\n"), (647, "Sub League 1 Picks Top Player", 211, 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 3, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "What\'s in a number? In baseball, just about everything.\n\nThe numbers that Memphis\'s <Hector Buonconte:player#211> put up last week were the envy of the league, as Buonconte came away with Sub League 1 Player of the Week honors.\n\nHe belted out 13 hits in 27 at-bats, no home runs and 4 RBIs last week as he posted his .481 batting average. \n\nDuring the current season <Buonconte:player#211> is batting at a .332 clip with 1 home run and 26 RBIs. He has played in 67 games and scored 30 times.\n"), (648, "Great Week for San Francisco\'s Tommy Baker", 722, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Tommy Baker:player#722> of the <San Francisco Valley Cats:team#9> put the finishing touch on an exceptional week of play by being named the Sub League 2 Player of the Week.\n\nHe rocked the opposition with a .458 batting average, 11 hits in 24 at-bats, 3 home runs and 5 RBIs while scoring 7 times.\n\nThus far this season Baker is hitting .361 with 29 home runs, 87 RBIs and 89 runs scored. He has 128 hits in 355 at-bats and has played in 96 games.\n"), (649, "Landreth of Chandler Player of the Week", 126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 22, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 22, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 1 today announced <Gary Landreth:player#126> as its Player of the Week.\n\nThe <Chandler:team#22> first baseman was truly in a zone as he hit .571 (12-for-21) with 2 home runs and 8 RBIs. \n\nThis season <Landreth:player#126> has hit 14 home runs and posted a .348 batting average.\n"), (650, "Star of the Week Awarded in SL2", 1001, 0, 0, 0, 0, 26, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 26, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s Player of the Week was <Chris Brammer:player#1001> of the <Leesburg Privateers:team#26>.\n\nHe battered Sub League 2 pitching for 14 hits in 25 at-bats, 3 home runs and 13 RBIs while hitting .560 and scoring 7 runs.\n\nThus far this year <Brammer:player#1001> has hit .305 with 14 home runs and 47 RBIs.\n"), (651, "Sub League 1 Announces #1 Player", 1163, 0, 0, 0, 0, 36, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 36, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The top batter in the Sub League 1 last week was <Josh Headley:player#1163>, who batted .407 and towered above everybody with a 7-game hitting barrage.\n\nDuring the week Headley banged out a .407 batting average (11-for-27), 5 home runs, 9 RBI and scored 6 runs.\n\nToday the <Sparta:team#36> third baseman received the SL1 Player of the Week Award.\n\nThis year <Headley:player#1163> has hit at a .242 clip with 57 RBIs, 22 home runs and 47 runs scored.\n"), (652, "Cobb Takes This Week\'s Trophy", 1573, 0, 0, 0, 0, 44, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 44, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "His lightning swing and solid bat took the Sub League 2 by storm. All week <Jeff Cobb:player#1573> of the <Long Beach Bluebirds:team#44> shocked opponents with an electrifying performance to capture the Sub League 2 Player of the Week honors.\n\nThe talented first baseman sparked his team by hitting .393 with 5 home runs, 13 RBIs and 6 runs scored.\n\n<Cobb:player#1573> is hitting .258 in 2022 with 65 RBIs and 24 home runs.\n"), (653, "Sub League 1 Winner is Flores", 1608, 0, 0, 0, 0, 52, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 52, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "With some great hand-eye coordination and a sweet, compact swing, <Washington Hooks:team#52> left fielder <Alejandro Flores:player#1608> took the Sub League 1 by storm this past week to take the latest Player of the Week honors.\n\n\"The ball was looking like a beach ball all week,\" a happy <Flores:player#1608> said to BNN reporters. \"When it\'s that big, it doesn\'t matter where they throw it -- I can hit it anywhere.\"\n\nThe 24-year-old left fielder hit .478 (11-for-23) last week with 3 home runs, 4 RBIs and 4 runs scored.\n\nCurrently <Flores:player#1608> has 7 home runs and a .285 batting average.\n"), (654, "Crayton SL2\'s Best of the Week", 2390, 0, 0, 0, 0, 64, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 64, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was an exceptional week for <Jeff Crayton:player#2390> of the <Aurora Tigers:team#64>.\n\nFirst he beat the devil out of the ball, hitting .458 and as you would expect, he was voted the Player of the Week in the Sub League 2. Last week <Crayton:player#2390> went 11-for-24, notched 4 home runs and 11 RBIs and scored 6 runs. All in all, a very good week for him.\n\nThus far in 2022 Crayton is hitting .304 with 17 home runs, 62 RBIs, 54 runs scored and has compiled a .342 OBP.\n"), (655, "Player of the Week Trophy to Shaw", 3136, 0, 0, 0, 0, 71, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 71, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Last week <John Shaw:player#3136> was the toast of <Belcourt:team#71> and the talk of the Sub League 1 -- this week he\'s the SL1 Player of the Week.\n\nThe standout center fielder sewed up the award with his .438 average (14-for-32), 1 home run, 3 RBIs and 4 runs. \n\nLooking at his season stats, <Shaw:player#3136> has compiled a .333 batting average and a .408 on-base percentage, while hitting 2 home runs and driving in 7 runs.\n"), (656, "Dietz: Big Hit in the Sub League 2", 3083, 0, 0, 0, 0, 77, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 77, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Randy Dietz:player#3083> went on a week-long tirade against the Sub League 2 pitchers and was acclaimed the Player of the Week.\n\nThe <Montgomery:team#77> center fielder was hot as a firecracker, exploding with a .370 average, 4 home runs and 11 RBIs. For the week <Dietz:player#3083> bashed out 10 hits in 27 at-bats and scored 6 runs. \n\nThis year <Dietz:player#3083> is batting .271 with 32 hits, 7 home runs, 20 RBIs, 15 walks, .358 OBP and has scored 21 runs.\n"), (657, "Barrage of Hits Gets Kraeger SL1 Award", 2388, 0, 0, 0, 0, 87, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 87, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "There was no one hotter in the Sub League 1 last week as <Ryan Kraeger:player#2388> attacked enemy pitching with a vengeance to collect the Player of the Week Award.\n\nThe 21-year-old <Omaha:team#87> left fielder batted .391 with 9 hits in 23 at-bats, 4 home runs and 7 RBIs.\n\nSo far this season <Kraeger:player#2388> is batting .294 with 15 home runs.\n"), (658, "Irvine Second Baseman Picked SL2 Player of the Week", 3182, 0, 0, 0, 0, 89, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 89, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Irvine Drillers:team#89> fans are celebrating <Brad Houck:player#3182>\'s selection as Sub League 2 Player of the Week.\n\n<Houck:player#3182> put up some serious numbers over the past seven days as he cracked 10 hits in 25 at-bats. The 19-year-old second baseman hit .400, drove in 7 runs, scored 7 times and hit 4 home runs.\n\nThis year <Houck:player#3182> is batting .298 with 6 home runs.\n"), (659, "Weekly Team Power Rankings", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 0, 2, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-7-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Here are the current team power rankings for Fictional Baseball League:\n\nTeams (Total Points, Tendency):