 SB, 150 wRC+, 1.5 WAR\nRF <Bill Reese:player#2928> (BR) - .243/.377/.604, 111 AB, 12 HR, 158 wRC+, 1.3 WAR\n\n\nThe Sub League 2 All-Stars will have these players on their roster:\n\nSP <Dillon Alexander:player#1462> (CHE) - 2-1, 2.54 ERA, 39.0 IP, 1.33 WHIP, 8.5 K/9, 0.9 WAR\nSP <Devin Browne:player#3334> (WIL) - 1-0, 11 SV, 2.11 ERA, 21.1 IP, 1.36 WHIP, 13.5 K/9, 0.7 WAR\nSP <Jose Espinosa:player#3161> (YON) - 3-1, 2.87 ERA, 47.0 IP, 1.28 WHIP, 9.2 K/9, 1.3 WAR\nSP <Zack Herrera:player#2318> (DEX) - 5-1, 2.55 ERA, 42.1 IP, 0.80 WHIP, 15.5 K/9, 2.2 WAR\nSP <Joaquin Magana:player#1741> (YON) - 2-1, 2.38 ERA, 41.2 IP, 1.30 WHIP, 8.2 K/9, 1.0 WAR\nSP <Danny Ramirez:player#3058> (SCO) - 3-0, 1.93 ERA, 37.1 IP, 0.91 WHIP, 8.0 K/9, 0.7 WAR\nRP <Kevin Bailey:player#2735> (DUR) - 2-2, 3.04 ERA, 26.2 IP, 1.05 WHIP, 13.8 K/9, 0.3 WAR\nRP <Scott Clucas:player#2843> (IRV) - 1-0, 2.57 ERA, 21.0 IP, 1.38 WHIP, 13.3 K/9, 0.7 WAR\nRP <Chris Marshall:player#2845> (ADE) - 1-1, 3.08 ERA, 26.1 IP, 0.95 WHIP, 9.6 K/9, 0.2 WAR\nRP <Dan Nance:player#2313> (DEX) - 1-1, 2.27 ERA, 31.2 IP, 1.23 WHIP, 11.1 K/9, 0.9 WAR\nRP <Vince Taylor:player#2832> (DUR) - 3-0, 1.95 ERA, 27.2 IP, 1.05 WHIP, 9.8 K/9, 0.3 WAR\nC <Kevin Burleson:player#3281> (DEX) - .301/.343/.473, 93 AB, 4 HR, 126 wRC+, 0.5 WAR\nC <David Saldivar:player#2709> (YON) - .198/.309/.472, 106 AB, 8 HR, 116 wRC+, 0.5 WAR\n2B <Mike Brumley:player#3258> (CHE) - .268/.349/.714, 112 AB, 14 HR, 1 SB, 185 wRC+, 1.9 WAR\n2B <Brad Houck:player#3182> (IRV) - .284/.338/.461, 141 AB, 6 HR, 1 SB, 121 wRC+, 1.2 WAR\n2B <Tim Tate:player#2822> (DUR) - .230/.347/.500, 126 AB, 9 HR, 3 SB, 133 wRC+, 1.3 WAR\n3B <Adam Mielke:player#3093> (ADE) - .283/.400/.543, 46 AB, 2 HR, 162 wRC+, 0.7 WAR\nLF <Jared Lunn:player#3248> (IRV) - .279/.389/.400, 140 AB, 4 HR, 126 wRC+, 1.3 WAR\nLF <Alex Martinez:player#856> (WIL) - .341/.366/.587, 126 AB, 9 HR, 2 SB, 162 wRC+, 1.2 WAR\nCF <Victor Hernandez:player#305> (SCO) - .296/.361/.472, 142 AB, 6 HR, 1 SB, 129 wRC+, 0.9 WAR\nCF <Casey Kresge:player#3327> (YON) - .256/.354/.476, 82 AB, 4 HR, 5 SB, 130 wRC+, 0.9 WAR\nRF <Angelo Bonilla:player#2905> (ADE) - .365/.423/.754, 126 AB, 15 HR, 214 wRC+, 2.1 WAR\nRF <Travis Bramlett:player#2756> (WIL) - .316/.359/.537, 136 AB, 6 HR, 146 wRC+, 0.8 WAR\nRF <Oscar Cabrera:player#2941> (SCO) - .324/.378/.757, 136 AB, 17 HR, 2 SB, 206 wRC+, 2.3 WAR\nRF <Arturo Rocha:player#2757> (WIL) - .222/.315/.472, 144 AB, 11 HR, 116 wRC+, 0.4 WAR\n"), (754, "Rowdy Players Suspended by League", 347, 941, 0, 0, 0, 7, 1, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 7, 0, 0, "2022-8-3", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Paul Leppala:player#347> of <San Jose:team#7> and <Rich Ellison:player#941> of <Jacksonville:team#1> were the main participants in a recent bench-clearing brawl and today the league handed out its punishment. <Leppala:player#347> will have to miss 4 games for his part in the brawl, while <Ellison:player#941> was given 6 games. League officials announced their suspensions today.\n\nSo far this season Leppala is hitting .227 with 2 home runs, 14 RBIs and 12 runs scored. He has 29 hits in 128 at-bats and a .273 OBP. \n\nSo far in 33 appearances this season, <Ellison:player#941> has recorded 6 wins and sustained 4 losses. He has pitched 85.1 innings, yielded 67 hits, fanned 79 and has a 2.85 ERA.\n"), (755, "Legion Stop Buonconte at 22", 211, 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 2, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 3, 5, 3, 0, 0, "2022-8-3", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Hector Buonconte:player#211> came rolling into today\'s game against the <Baltimore Legion:team#2> with a 22-game hitting string, but he left it on the field at Legion Field.\n\nThe 29-year-old <Memphis T-Bones:team#3> first baseman went 0-for-4 against the Legion as the T-Bones fell, 2-1.\n\n\"I swung at a couple pitches I probably shouldn\'t have and I didn\'t swing at a couple I probably should have,\" he said, grimacing. \"But that\'s what makes a hit streak so impressive in the first place -- it only takes a couple mistakes to end it all.\"\n\nSo far this season Buonconte is batting .333 with 2 home runs, 29 RBIs and 33 runs scored. He has 102 hits in 306 at-bats, 8 walks and a .354 OBP. <Buonconte:player#211> has played in 77 games.\n"), (756, "Barraza Pops 3 Out of the Park Against Seagulls", 492, 0, 0, 0, 0, 11, 10, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 11, 0, 0, "2022-8-3", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Players don\'t hit three home runs in a game very often and when they do, it is something to celebrate. After today, <Marco Barraza:player#492> can celebrate.\n\nThe <Charlotte Nailers:team#11> left fielder powered three into the stands at Nailers Park today against the <Houston Seagulls:team#10>.\n\n\"It\'s rare that you actually try to hit a home run,\" <Barraza:player#492> told reporters after the game. \"Most of the time you fail, if you really try to hit one. But today, I was really trying on that last one.\"\n\nIn all, he was 3-for-5 as the Nailers toppled <Houston:team#10> by a score of 10-7, knocking in 3 runs and scoring 3 times.\n\n\"He is blessed with a natural home run swing,\" Charlotte manager Miles Holtzapple said. \"He gets the ball up in the air.\"\n\n<Marco Barraza:player#492> hit a solo-shot off <Gene Stroud:player#1013> in the 1st, hit a solo-shot off <Gene Stroud:player#1013> in the 3rd, struck out in the 4th, hit a solo-shot off <Jonathan Campos:player#1725> in the 6th and grounded out in the 8th.\n\nThis year <Barraza:player#492> has socked 15 hits in 49 at-bats for a .306 average with 7 home runs. He is getting on base at a .375 pace and his totals also include 14 RBIs and 12 runs scored.\n"), (757, "Oxnard Loses Hudes, Out 7 Months", 1923, 0, 0, 0, 0, 73, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 73, 0, -5, "2022-8-4", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Mike Hudes:player#1923> had hoped for the best, but expected the worst. Today, he learned from the <Oxnard:team#73> medical staff that he would miss the rest of the season. The <Oxnard:team#73> reliever suffered a torn labrum in an earlier ballgame. He admitted to being discouraged, but said he plans to come back strong next year.\n\nRunning the numbers on <Hudes:player#1923> for the year, he has made 14 relief appearances, recorded no saves and compiled a 2-1 won-lost mark with a 3.74 ERA. In pitching 21.2 innings, he has totaled 23 strikeouts and 8 walks.\n"), (758, "Monsters Whitewashed by Aldridge", 560, 0, 0, 0, 0, 20, 17, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 20, 0, 0, "2022-8-4", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<John Aldridge:player#560> of the <Grand Rapids Blue Jackets:team#20> permitted 5 hits, walked 0 and fanned 4 during the 4-0 shutout win over the <Mannford Monsters:team#17> at Mannford Grounds today.\n\n\"I told him, \'You did good today,\'\" said Grand Rapids manager Dorian Lawson. \"And I told him he\'d better do good again next week.\"\n\nThis year <Aldridge:player#560> has a 9-8 record with a 4.21 ERA. \n"), (759, "Stroud Arrives Late, Misses Game", 1013, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-8-4", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Showing up late for work can be costly. <Gene Stroud:player#1013> is expected to be fined or benched for the team\'s next game after getting to the ballpark 30 minutes late. \"I got stuck in traffic!\" screamed Stroud as he ran down the hallway to talk to manager Joe Lohmeyer about the situation. \"it\'s unacceptable,\" said Lohmeyer. \"He should know better and should take responsibility for his actions. Even though this appeared to be an honest mistake, he should take traffic into account. Leave 30 minutes earlier next time!\"\n"), (760, "Reese Shines in Winning 2022 FBL Rookie League HR Challenge", 2928, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 0, 1, 3, 205, -1, 0, "2022-8-4", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Some premier power hitters put on a show at this year\'s Home Run Challenge. <Bill Reese:player#2928> won the event, which took place at Airhogs Park. To get it done, he had to defeat <Josh Westfall:player#2755> in the final round. He did get it done, outscoring Westfall 7-6.\n\n\"I paced myself throughout,\" said Reese. \"It helped me get through that last round.\"\n\n"), (761, "Stein to Miss 6 Months", 889, 0, 0, 0, 0, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 7, 0, -5, "2022-8-5", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The latest news from the <San Jose Spiders:team#7> clubhouse is this: reliever <Cory Stein:player#889> is expected to be out of action for another 6 months. He has a ruptured bicep tendon, sustained on 08/01/2022. Stein expressed a bit of relief. \"At least now I know,\" he said.\n\nTo this point in the season he has had no saves. <Stein:player#889> has made 30 relief appearances, tossed 36.1 innings and struck out 38 with a record of 2 wins and 1 loss. \n"), (762, "Chris Cosby Wins MVP in Sub League 2 Victory over Sub League 1", 2540, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 0, 1, 3, 205, -1, 0, "2022-8-5", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Scottsdale Grounds was the place to be for baseball fans tonight, as the best FR players gathered for the annual all-star game.\n\nOn the field, the <Sub League 2:team#110> downed the <Sub League 1:team#109> by a score of 5-4. Off the field, game MVP <Chris Cosby:player#2540> said he thinks everyone had a good night.\n\n\"You looked into the stands and it seemed like everyone was having a fantastic time,\" said the 19-year-old, who went 2-for-2 in the game. \"A game like this is good for the sport.\"\n\n\n\n<View Boxscore:box#5302>\n<View Game Log:log#5302>\n<Watch Highlights:highlight#5302>\n"), (763, "Asbill Pitches Fort Worth to Shutout Victory", 612, 0, 0, 0, 0, 13, 11, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 13, 0, 0, "2022-8-5", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Fort Worth Shamrocks:team#13> hurler <Josh Asbill:player#612> logged a 5-hit, complete game shutout over the Nailers, stopping them 7-0 at Nailers Park today.\n\n\"I felt great out there,\" Asbill said in his postgame interview. \"After the second or third inning, I got real comfortable. Hopefully this is a building block for me. I\'d love a few more starts like this.\"\n\nHe rung up 11 strikeouts and gave up no walks in the performance.\n\nOn the year <Asbill:player#612> has compiled a 5-10 mark with a 4.15 ERA. \n\n<View Boxscore:box#1084>\n"), (764, "Glidewell and Ratzel Suspended for Free-for-All", 3133, 3294, 0, 0, 0, 65, 69, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 65, 0, 0, "2022-8-5", 0, 1, -1, 0, "After an intense confrontation, both the Tropics <Cody Glidewell:player#3133> and the Peregrines <Steve Ratzel:player#3294> were handed their punishments today. The league commissioner\'s office issued suspensions for an on-the-field conflict that occurred at a recent <Lexington:team#65>-<Po\'ipu:team#69> game. <Cody Glidewell:player#3133> will miss 4 games, while <Steve Ratzel:player#3294> was suspended for 9 games.\n\n\"Sometimes we go too far and have to pay the consequences,\" <Cody Glidewell:player#3133> commented later. \"Hopefully cooler heads will prevail the next time we play.\"\n\nGlidewell is batting .255 this year with 10 home runs, 31 RBIs and 25 runs scored. He has 38 hits in 149 at-bats.\n\nSo far this year <Ratzel:player#3294> has 2 wins and 2 losses and a 5.72 ERA.\n"), (765, "Jersey City\'s Concha Diagnosis Revealed", 752, 0, 0, 0, 0, 23, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 23, 0, -5, "2022-8-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The injury that has kept <Juan Concha:player#752> out of action since 08/02/2022 will keep him out a while longer. <Jersey City Wild Dogs:team#23> officials made the announcement this afternoon. They said that Concha is expected to miss at least 4 months with a torn labrum.\n\nOn the season <Concha:player#752> has compiled a 2-2 mark with a 4.22 ERA in 8 starts. In pitching 42.2 innings he has 27 strikeouts and 18 walks while limiting the opposition to a .213 batting average.\n"), (766, "Boren Hits in 20 Straight Games", 539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 12, 15, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-8-6", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The streak is alive and well -- at least for today.\n\n<Ken Boren:player#539> did it again, bashing 1 hit in the contest at Lions Field today. For the last 20 games in a row, the 29-year-old left fielder has collected at least one hit. His efforts helped the <Chicago Quakes:team#12> beat the <El Paso Lions:team#15> 3-0 today.\n\n\"I\'m happy I kept the streak going,\" Boren told a standing-room-only crowd of reporters gathered in the Chicago clubhouse. \"Honestly though, I\'m looking forward to going home and not thinking about this for the rest of the day.\"\n<Ken Boren:player#539> doubled in the 1st, grounded out in the 3rd, flied out in the 6th, flied out in the 8th and struck out in the 9th.\n\nA look at his season totals shows <Boren:player#539> with 35 home runs, .355 BA, .446 OBP, 86 RBIs and 88 runs scored.\n"), (767, "Injury Brings Season to End for Albertson", 2114, 0, 0, 0, 0, 54, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 54, 0, -5, "2022-8-7", 0, 1, -1, 0, "After several days of waiting for test results, bad news was delivered to <Josh Albertson:player#2114> today. The <Oak View:team#54> reliever will be out the rest of the year due to a torn ulnar collateral ligament he suffered on 08/06/2022. \n\nSo far this season <Albertson:player#2114> has 19 saves in 41 relief appearances with a 2-6 record and 3.48 ERA.\n"), (768, "5-Hit Game for Landreth", 126, 0, 0, 0, 0, 22, 21, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 22, 0, 0, "2022-8-7", 0, 1, -1, 0, "All game long, <Chandler:team#22>\'s <Gary Landreth:player#126> was rattling the walls at Ballpark of Chandler and banging out base hits against the <Fort Wayne Blue Falcons:team#21>. When the dust finally settled on the diamond, he had a 5-hit day and the Capitals had a 10-2 victory. \n\nSpeaking with reporters after his standout performance, the 27-year-old first baseman said, \"Get 5 hits, win a ballgame, it\'s nice. I could get used to this.\" \n\n<Gary Landreth:player#126> doubled in the 1st, hit an RBI single in the 2nd, singled in the 4th, singled in the 7th and singled in the 8th.\n\nSo far this year <Landreth:player#126> has hit .360 with 14 home runs, 59 RBIs and 60 runs scored.\n"), (769, "Boren\'s 20-Game Hitting Streak Ends", 539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 12, 15, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 3, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-8-7", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It just wasn\'t <Ken Boren:player#539>\'s day.\n\nThe <Chicago Quakes:team#12> took the 5-3 win today over the <El Paso Lions:team#15>, but the Lions mound staff did what nobody else could -- they stopped the 20-game hitting streak of Quakes left fielder <Ken Boren:player#539>.\n\n\"We might have focused a bit too much on stopping Boren,\" <El Paso:team#15> manager <Sergio Serrano:coach#127> commented afterward. \"He had a nice hitting streak going, but the Quakes have other hitters and they did their job today.\"\n\nCurrently <Boren:player#539> is batting .354 with 35 home runs and 86 RBIs.\n"), (770, "Lopes Spank Friars, 11-0", 3222, 0, 0, 0, 0, 78, 76, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 78, 0, 0, "2022-8-7", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Oklahoma City Friars:team#76> met their match today in <St. Louis:team#78> hurler <Phil Williams:player#3222>. He kept them guessing the whole game and spun a 3-hit shutout.\n\n\"He just worked us over,\" <Oklahoma City:team#76> skipper <Mark Arthur:coach#471> said. \"He probably didn\'t even need a shower after the game -- he barely worked up a sweat.\"\n\nIn the 11-0 victory, Williams whiffed 6 and gave up 1 walk.\n\n"), (771, "Memphis\'s Burket SL1 Star of the Week", 214, 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 3, 0, 0, "2022-8-8", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<John Burket:player#214> kept his eye on the ball last week and now all eyes are on him. The <Memphis T-Bones:team#3> center fielder easily swung his way to the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award with 12 hits in 24 at-bats.\n\nBurket hit .500 last week with 1 home run, 4 RBIs and 3 runs scored.\n\nThis season in 96 games, <Burket:player#214> has hit at a .309 clip with 111 hits, 15 home runs, 50 RBIs and 48 runs scored.\n"), (772, "SL2\'s Star Player Named", 580, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 10, 0, 0, "2022-8-8", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s Player of the Week was <Israel Salazar:player#580> of the <Houston Seagulls:team#10>.\n\nHis big bat waylaid Sub League 2 pitching for 16 hits in 28 at-bats, no home runs and 7 RBIs while hitting .571 and scoring 7 runs.\n\nThis season <Salazar:player#580> is batting .382 with 167 hits and 18 home runs. He has scored 85 times and has 67 RBI.\n"), (773, "SL1 Player of the Week Chosen", 880, 0, 0, 0, 0, 20, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 20, 0, 0, "2022-8-8", 0, 1, -1, 0, "A battle-tested <Jeff Peters:player#880> declared war on opposing pitchers last week, attacking the ball like the well-schooled veteran he is. Today the 33-year-old <Grand Rapids:team#20> left fielder collected the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award.\n\nHe wrapped up the week with a .476 average, 10 hits in 21 at-bats, 3 home runs, 6 RBIs and 8 runs scored.\n\nThis season <Peters:player#880> is batting .308 with 15 home runs.\n"), (774, "Whitecaps Hiciano Named SL2\'s #1 Player", 1131, 0, 0, 0, 0, 28, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 28, 0, 0, "2022-8-8", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 2 has selected <Jose Hiciano:player#1131> of the <Donna Whitecaps:team#28> as Player of the Week.\n\nHe hit .458 (11-for-24) this past week collecting 6 RBIs, scored 5 runs and hit 3 home runs.\n\nSo far this year <Hiciano:player#1131> is hitting .342 with 39 home runs.\n"), (775, "Perrone Punishes SL1 Pitchers This Week", 1320, 0, 0, 0, 0, 37, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 37, 0, 0, "2022-8-8", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week <Ed Perrone:player#1320>, first baseman for the <San Bernardino Ivy:team#37>, hit his way to the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award.\n\n<Perrone:player#1320> put on a hitting clinic with a .370 average as he belted and battered SL1 pitchers for 10 hits in 27 at-bats, 4 home runs, 10 RBIs and scored 7 runs.\n\nSo far this season Perrone is batting .280 with 12 home runs, 41 RBIs and 25 runs scored. He has 52 hits in 186 at-bats, 17 walks and a .351 OBP. <Perrone:player#1320> has played in 47 games.\n"), (776, "Sub League 2 Picks Top Performer", 