-1, 0, "Bad news for <Gus Guzman:player#1411>: the <Winston-Salem:team#48> starting pitcher will miss the duration of the season due to injury. He said that the team\'s medical staff made it official this afternoon. Guzman handled it philosophically. \"It\'s the end of the season for me,\" he said. \"It\'s not the end of the world.\"\n\nThus far this season, <Guzman:player#1411> has tossed 126 innings in 20 starts, fanned 104 batters, walked 40 and put up a 3.07 ERA with 8 wins and 3 losses.\n"), (798, "Ramirez Burned Badly During Kitchen Mishap", 265, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-8-9", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Lumberjacks catcher <Pedro Ramirez:player#265> required medical attention yesterday after severely burning himself while preparing dinner at his home. Ramirez apparently burned the palm of his right hand on a stove. The injury will reportedly keep Ramirez out of action anywhere from 5 days up to a week.\n"), (799, "Gray Wows Fans with Longball", 1948, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 0, 1, 3, 204, -1, 0, "2022-8-9", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The 2022 Home Run Challenge provided a raucous crowd at Lubbock Grounds with great drama.  Outlasting the competition was <Nick Gray:player#1948>. The <Lubbock Peaches:team#60> right fielder knocked off <Alfredo Dabula:player#2067> in the final round by a score of 8-7.\n\n\"What a unique experience,\" said Gray. \"It\'s something I\'ll always remember.\"\n\n"), (800, "Young Star Helps Propel Sub League 1 to Win in Midseason Classic", 2150, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 0, 1, 3, 204, -1, 0, "2022-8-10", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Sub League 1:team#107> All-Stars reigned supreme tonight at A\'s Ballpark, with a 7-2 triumph over the <Sub League 2:team#108> All-Stars.\n\nSub League 1 right fielder <Jose Ramos:player#2150> led the way for the winning club, putting up a  3-for-3 mark to earn game MVP honors.\n\n\"We had some fun out there,\" he said. \"We\'ve got a great league and a great team and I\'m not surprised we won.\"\n\n\n\n<View Boxscore:box#4693>\n<View Game Log:log#4693>\n<Watch Highlights:highlight#4693>\n"), (801, "McCasland Sparkles in 7-0 Shutout", 146, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 2, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 4, 0, 0, "2022-8-10", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was a masterful game today for <Chris McCasland:player#146>. The <Detroit Cannons:team#4> hurler pitched shutout ball against the <Baltimore Legion:team#2> en route to a 7-0 win at Legion Field. In the game, <McCasland:player#146> rang up 8 strikeouts, walked 1 and allowed 4 hits.\n\n\"Chris looked like a real ace out there,\" Detroit manager Ben Gomez said.\n\nTo date this year in 23 starts, <McCasland:player#146> has crafted a 7-4 mark with a 2.78 ERA. \n\n<View Boxscore:box#455>\n"), (802, "Martin Laces 3 HR Against Bakersfield ", 1421, 0, 0, 0, 0, 30, 27, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 30, 0, 0, "2022-8-10", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Danny Martin:player#1421> went on an explosive hitting spree against the <Bakersfield Millionaires:team#27> at Millionaires Ballpark today, launching a trio of blasts to lead the <Irving Badlanders:team#30> to the 18-1 win.\n\nThe first baseman finished 3-for-4 with 3 runs scored and 5 RBI.\n\n\"It was just one of those days,\" Martin said in a postgame interview. \"I don\'t know how to explain it. I\'m just putting a good swing on the ball.\"\n\n<Bakersfield:team#27> skipper <Zach Hart:coach#240> said Martin was \"locked-in.\"\n\n\"We made some pretty good pitches,\" he said. \"Those first two homers were exactly where the pitcher wanted to put them. He\'s just hot right now -- you\'ve just got to tip your hat to him.\"\n\n<Danny Martin:player#1421> flied out in the 1st, hit a solo-shot off <Mike Pataki:player#429> in the 2nd, hit a three-run home run off <Mike Pataki:player#429> in the 3rd and hit a solo-shot off <Bobby Alvarez:player#2655> in the 5th.\n\nOn the season, <Martin:player#1421> is batting .277 with 20 home runs and 51 RBIs. He has played in 90 games.\n"), (803, "Gus Galindo Strokes 3 Home Runs", 1426, 0, 0, 0, 0, 48, 42, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 48, 0, 0, "2022-8-10", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Gus Galindo:player#1426> was sending souvenirs to the sun gods all game long in the 7-1 <Winston-Salem Cheetahs:team#48> triumph at Cheetahs Park today.\n\nThe 25-year-old put on a show for fans, launching not one, not two, but three home runs into the stands and powering the Cheetahs past the <St. Petersburg Naturals:team#42>.\n\n\"One homer\'s good, two\'s great, three\'s out of sight,\" Galindo told BNN reporters after the game. \"I can\'t wait until next game. I really feel good at the plate.\"\n\nThe first baseman went 3-for-3, rung up 5 RBIs and scored 3 runs on his record-setting day.\n\n<Gus Galindo:player#1426> hit a two-run home run off <Benito Aguilar:player#520> in the 1st, walked in the 3rd, hit a two-run home run off <Corey Parker:player#1619> in the 5th and hit a solo-shot off <Corey Parker:player#1619> in the 7th.\n\nCurrently Galindo is batting .235 with 25 home runs, 71 RBIs and 62 runs scored.\n"), (804, "Thomas Goes Deep 3 Times", 3310, 0, 0, 0, 0, 88, 83, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 88, 0, 0, "2022-8-10", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Columbus Purple Warriors:team#88> third baseman <Johnny Thomas:player#3310> almost did it all today. He sent three shots out of the ballpark, scored 3 times and drove in 5 runs and had 4 hits in 5 at-bats.\n\nThe one thing he could not do, however, was lead the Purple Warriors to victory. The <Portland Marksmen:team#83> escaped with the 10-7 win by the <Portland:team#83> despite being on the receiving end of the barrage from Thomas.\n\n\"I\'d be lying if I said I didn\'t like hitting three homers, but losing takes a little glitter off the game,\" he admitted to BNN writers after the game.\n\n<Johnny Thomas:player#3310> doubled in the 1st, hit a solo-shot off <John Keogan:player#1144> in the 3rd, struck out in the 4th, hit a three-run home run off <Rusty Bem:player#2214> in the 6th and hit a solo-shot off <Bobby Zendejas:player#2904> in the 9th.\n\n\"When someone hits three home runs, you put yourself in a tough position to win,\" said Columbus manager Guillermo Zapien. \"We were lucky to win this one. I don\'t think it matters how hard you throw, especially in the Sub League 1. If you leave a ball out over the plate to good FBL Rookie League hitters, if they get a bead on you and you leave it over the middle, they\'re probably going to take a good hack at it.\"\n\nSo far this season <Thomas:player#3310> has gotten 48 hits in 172 at-bats for a .279 batting average with 8 home runs. His stats include 25 RBIs and 17 runs scored. He has played in 44 games.\n"), (805, "Medical Diagnosis Updated on Tanguy", 1444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 41, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 41, 0, -5, "2022-8-12", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Ron Tanguy:player#1444> could soon be placed on the injured list. The <Orlando:team#41> first baseman told reporters that he expects to be \"out of commission\" for 4 months because of a ruptured achilles tendon. He hasn\'t played since 08/10/2022 and, he said, he\'s \"itchin\' to get back out there.\"\n\nTanguy is hitting .292 this season with 30 home runs, 72 RBIs and 70 runs scored. He has 121 hits in 414 at-bats.\n"), (806, "Injury Derails Season for Lara", 1730, 0, 0, 0, 0, 55, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 55, 0, -5, "2022-8-12", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Ricardo Lara:player#1730> will have to wait a while longer. The <Kansas City:team#55> first baseman was informed this afternoon that he will miss another 5 months with a torn labrum. The injury has kept him off the field since 08/10/2022. Though Lara had hoped to return soon, he has no choice but to be patient. \"Gotta stay focused,\" he said. \"Gotta stay positive.\"\n\nCurrently <Lara:player#1730> is hitting .385 and has collected 5 home runs, 15 RBIs and scored 10 times, while playing in 12 games.\n"), (807, "Season Done for Patterson", 2361, 0, 0, 0, 0, 57, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 57, 0, -5, "2022-8-12", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Paul Patterson:player#2361> has to call it a season. The <Des Moines Road Warriors:team#57> left fielder learned today that the full extent his injury suffered on 08/11/2022 is worse than hoped. He will not play again this year according to club doctors, who diagnosed the injury as a ruptured foot tendon and stated that he would not be able to play for 5-6 months. \n\nThe team will likely place Patterson on the injured list today.\n\n<Patterson:player#2361> is currently hitting at a .240 pace with 7 home runs and 24 RBIs. \n"), (808, "Latimore Set to Miss 10-11 Months", 2733, 0, 0, 0, 0, 86, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 86, 0, -5, "2022-8-12", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The news was not unexpected, but that didn\'t make it easier to accept for the <Anchorage Fire Ants:team#86>: reliever <Tyler Latimore:player#2733> is out for the year. Latimore suffered a torn flexor tendon in his elbow on 08/09/2022. The team knew that the chances of seeing him return were slim to none. But today it was made official.\n\nThis season <Latimore:player#2733> has made 9 relief appearances with no saves. In 12.2 innings he has fanned 11 hitters and recorded 1 win and 1 loss with a 6.39 ERA.\n"), (809, "Cabrera Too Tough, Blanks San Diego", 100, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 1, 0, 0, "2022-8-12", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <San Diego Fighting Knights:team#5> met their match today in <Jacksonville:team#1> hurler <Johnny Cabrera:player#100>. He kept them guessing the whole game and spun a 2-hit shutout.\n\n\"He just worked us over,\" <San Diego:team#5> skipper <Drew Johnson:coach#172> said. \"He probably didn\'t even need a shower after the game -- he barely worked up a sweat.\"\n\nIn the 3-0 victory, Cabrera whiffed 6 and gave up 2 walks.\n\nThis season <Cabrera:player#100> has a 12-6 mark in 25 starts with a 2.43 ERA. He has given up 133 hits in 155.2 innings, struck out 122 and issued 34 walks. Opposing clubs have compiled a .231 batting average against him. \n\n<View Boxscore:box#459>\n"), (810, "Hart Parks 3 HR in the Seats", 641, 0, 0, 0, 0, 22, 18, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 22, 0, 0, "2022-8-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Aiden Hart:player#641> was sending souvenirs to the sun gods all game long in the 8-2 <Chandler Capitals:team#22> triumph at Ballpark of Chandler today.\n\nThe 31-year-old put on a show for fans, launching not one, not two, but three home runs into the stands and powering the Capitals past the <Toledo Rainiers:team#18>.\n\n\"One homer\'s good, two\'s great, three\'s out of sight,\" Hart told BNN reporters after the game. \"I can\'t wait until next game. I really feel good at the plate.\"\n\nThe left fielder went 4-for-4, rung up 3 RBIs and scored 4 runs on his record-setting day.\n\n<Aiden Hart:player#641> hit a solo-shot off <Lance Knaack:player#1516> in the 3rd, singled in the 5th, hit a solo-shot off <Ian Wertz:player#47> in the 6th and hit a solo-shot off <Antonio Cacho:player#36> in the 8th.\n\nOn the year <Hart:player#641> has hit .227 with 16 home runs, 37 RBIs and scored 33 runs.\n"), (811, "3 Roundtrippers for Tighe", 3313, 0, 0, 0, 0, 89, 92, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 89, 0, 0, "2022-8-13", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was a good day for the <Irvine Drillers:team#89> and an exceptional one for <Kenny Tighe:player#3313>. The 23-year-old third baseman sent three bombs out of the park to help the Drillers beat the <Chesapeake Norse:team#92> 11-6 at Irvine Fields.\n\n\"When you\'re in the zone, the game really slows down,\" <Tighe:player#3313> said when asked about his performance later. \"I couldn\'t even tell you what pitches were thrown. Today feels great, but it is a long season and tomorrow is another day.\"\n\nFor the day, he scored 3 times, drove in 5 runs and smacked 3 hits in 4 at-bats.\n\n<Kenny Tighe:player#3313> grounded out in the 1st, hit a solo-shot off <Bill Otto:player#2241> in the 3rd, hit a two-run home run off <Nate Arrant:player#2916> in the 5th and hit a two-run home run off <Chris Jordan:player#3284> in the 6th.\n\nFor the year <Tighe:player#3313> is hitting .355 with 4 home runs. His stats include 13 runs batted in and 6 runs scored.\n"), (812, "Latest Injury News for Sarrazin", 1355, 0, 0, 0, 0, 38, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 38, 0, -5, "2022-8-14", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The season will end prematurely for <John Sarrazin:player#1355>, the <Seattle:team#38> starting pitcher. He suffered a torn back muscle on 08/11/2022, an injury that is serious enough to knock him out of action for the rest of the year. Sarrazin was not available for comment.\n\nThis season <Sarrazin:player#1355> has compiled a 4-9 record with a 4.46 ERA in 21 starts.\n"), (813, "Bill Waite Gets Diagnosis, Out 5-6 Months", 2356, 0, 0, 0, 0, 40, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 40, 0, -5, "2022-8-14", 0, 1, -1, 0, "In a news release, the <Burnside Chaparrals:team#40> announced that shortstop <Bill Waite:player#2356> would miss the rest of the season due to a stretched elbow ligament. Waite sustained the injury on 08/12/2022. He \"will be sorely missed,\" said his manager.\n\nIn his 2022 season totals, <Waite:player#2356> has 6 home runs, .295 BA, .319 OBP, 21 RBIs and 16 runs scored.\n"), (814, "5-Hit Blitz by Lerner", 448, 0, 0, 0, 0, 14, 13, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 14, 0, 0, "2022-8-14", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was almost a perfect day for <Bryce Lerner:player#448>. \n\nThe <New York:team#14> first baseman displayed a hot bat today, enjoying an outstanding 5-hit day, but something was missing: The Owls lost to the <Fort Worth Shamrocks:team#13>, 5-4. Lerner told BNN reporters after the game that luck was \"fickle.\"\n\nNew York manager Seth Cowans told the beat writers otherwise.\n\n\"There was no luck today,\" the skipper said. \"He got 5 hits because he has a solid approach to hitting and he put it all together today, and we lost because the rest of us didn\'t put it together so well.\" \n\n<Bryce Lerner:player#448> singled in the 1st, singled in the 4th, walked in the 6th, singled in the 8th, singled in the 10th and singled in the 13th.\n\n<Lerner:player#448> is hitting at a .274 mark this season. His stats show 6 home runs, 33 RBIs and 44 runs scored. He has played 110 games for the <Owls:team#14>.\n\n<View Boxscore:box#1118>\n"), (815, "RF Rozier Receives 3-Game Suspension", 3279, 0, 0, 0, 0, 88, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 88, 0, 0, "2022-8-14", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Columbus Purple Warriors:team#88> were not very happy with the home plate umpire in today\'s loss to <Omaha:team#87> at Purple Warriors Ballpark. One in particular -- <Chris Rozier:player#3279>. Upon being called out on strikes, the Purple Warriors right fielder gave the ump quite an earful. For that, the man in blue gave him the thumb and sent him to an early shower.\n\nBut the disgruntled Rozier lingered on the field for another five minutes, berating the umpire. Finally his manager got him off the field and into the clubhouse.\n\nBut it got worse after the game, when Rozier told reporters, \"He was blind today. They played \'Three Blind Mice\' for him. If he doesn\'t know the words to the song, I\'m sure we can get it in Braille, so he can follow along.\"\n\nFor his escapades and after-the-game oration, the league office suspended Rozier for 3 games.\n\nThis year <Rozier:player#3279> is hitting .275 with 2 home runs.\n"), (816, "Rendon Nabs SL1 Weekly Award", 256, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 8, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Antonio Rendon:player#256> of the <Lumberjacks:team#8> relied on a sharp eye and a quick bat to outpace all other Sub League 1 hitters last week and collect the Player of the Week Award.\n\nHe hit .500 with 12 hits in 24 at-bats, 1 home run and 4 RBIs.\n\nCurrently <Rendon:player#256> is batting .277 with 103 hits and 7 home runs. He has knocked in 39 runs and scored 45 times.\n"), (817, "Sub League 2 Selects Best Performer", 539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 12, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Not every ball that came off <Ken Boren:player#539>\'s bat last week was a line drive or a towering shot -- it just seemed that way to the teams that played the <Chicago Quakes:team#12>. For his exploits, Boren was named this week\'s Sub League 2 Player of the Week award.\n\nThe Chicago left fielder put up 8 hits in 22 at-bats and 5 home runs while hitting .364 with 9 RBIs and 11 runs scored.\n\nFor the year <Boren:player#539> is batting .355 with 40 home runs, 95 RBIs and 99 runs scored.\n"), (818, "Star of the Week Selected in SL1", 1350, 0, 0, 0, 0, 21, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 21, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Matt Beiting:player#1350> of the <Fort Wayne Blue Falcons:team#21> cruised to Sub League 1 Player of the Week honors after putting together one of the finest stretches in his career last week.\n\nThe center fielder batted .462 (12-for-26) with 1 home run, 4 RBIs and 7 runs scored.\n\n<Beiting:player#1350> is currently batting .295 with 20 home runs and 69 RBIs.\n"), (819, "SL2 Player of the Week, Sterling of Irving", 687, 0, 0, 0, 0, 30, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 30, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Irving:team#30>\'s <Jim Sterling:player#687> would not be denied the Sub League 2 Player of the Week Award for this past week. His consistent stroke, which produced 9 hits in 26 at-bats and a .346 average, made him the clear favorite to win the honor.\n\n\"You just go out there and do what you have to do,\" said <Sterling:player#687>, \"When I\'m up, I try to focus and block everything else out of my mind and have a good at-bat. I\'m up there to get a hit or advance a runner, not to get caught up in the emotion of the moment. I hope I can win this award every week.\"\n\nHe also tallied 4 home runs, 10 RBIs, and scored 4 runs.\n\nLooking at his present stats, <Sterling:player#687> has compiled a .306 batting average in 106 games with a .381 on-base percentage, while hitting 48 home runs and driving in 99 runs.\n"), (820, "Eastman Week\'s #1 Player", 1863, 0, 0, 0, 0, 34, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 34, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "23-year-old third baseman <Dustin Eastman:player#1863> of the <Henderson Tartans:team#34> is the talk of the Sub League 1 for putting on a torrid hitting display last week and claiming the Player of the Week Award.\n\n<Eastman:player#1863> rapped out a sensational .367 batting average with 11 hits in 30 at-bats, 3 home runs and 9 RBIs. \n\nThis season in 84 games <Eastman:player#1863> is batting .276 with 23 home runs, 65 RBIs and has scored 54 times.\n"), (821, "This Week\'s Star Player is Flores", 1060, 0, 0, 0, 0, 44, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 44, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "A hot-hitting week got <Carlos Flores:player#1060> the Sub League 2 Player of the Week trophy. He really wore out his welcome with league pitchers.\n\nThe <Long Beach:team#44> left fielder slammed them for a .429 average, 9 hits in 21 at-bats, 5 home runs, 10 RBIs and scored 5 runs.\n\nIn the postgame press conference, <Flores:player#1060> shared his hitting philosophy with the BNN scribes: \"Just look for the seams and hit between them... nothin\' more than that.\"\n\n<Flores:player#1060> is batting at a .400 pace this season, picking up 10 hits in 25 at-bats with 5 home runs, 10 RBIs and 5 runs scored. \n"), (822, "Lozano Selected Top Performer in SL1", 1315, 0, 0, 0, 0, 53, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 53, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 1 announced today that <Tony Lozano:player#1315> of the <Modesto Oil Barons:team#53> earned Player of the Week honors for his performance over the past seven days.\n\n<Lozano:player#1315> hit .355 with 5 home runs, 10 RBIs and 6 runs scored. \n\n<Lozano:player#1315> currently has a .258 batting average with 71 hits, 26 homers, 52 RBIs, 44 runs scored and a .337 OBP.\n"), (823, "Powell Wins SL2 Honor", 2223, 0, 0, 0, 0, 63, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 63, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s top performer in the Sub League 2 was first baseman <Jace Powell:player#2223> of the <Starks Westerners:team#63>.\n\nHe lashed out a .438 average and was voted the Player of the Week. Over the last week <Powell:player#2223> tagged 7 hits in 16 at-bats and 4 home runs, drove in 9 runs and scored 4 times.\n\nPowell is batting .299 this season in 95 games with 18 home runs, 43 RBIs and 41 runs scored. He has 92 hits in 308 at-bats.\n"), (824, "Super Week for Dunwoody\'s Thomas!", 72, 0, 0, 0, 0, 68, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 68, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Swinging a hot stick last week, <Danny Thomas:player#72> picked up the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award today.\n\nThe 21-year-old left fielder for <Dunwoody:team#68> lashed 11 hits in 18 at-bats as he put together a .611 average with 1 home run. <Thomas:player#72> also drove in 5 runs, scored 4 times and compiled a .611 OBP.\n\nThomas is hitting .324 for the season with 10 home runs, 33 RBIs and 23 runs scored. He has 58 hits in 179 at-bats and played in 47 games.\n"), (825, "Kraeger Red-Hot, SL2 Player of the Week", 2388, 0, 0, 0, 0, 76, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 76, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Today the Sub League 2 announced the Player of the Week Award. This week\'s honoree is <Oklahoma City:team#76>\'s talented left fielder <Ryan Kraeger:player#2388>. When he steps into the batter\'s box, it\'s usually a bad omen for pitchers.\n\nFor the week <Kraeger:player#2388> batted .462 (6-for-13) with 3 home runs and 9 RBIs.\n\nHitting .206 to date, Kraeger has 3 home runs and 9 RBIs. He has played in 10 games.\n"), (826, "Sub League 1 Names Top Player", 3065, 0, 0, 0, 0, 84, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 84, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Today the Sub League 1 announced the Player of the Week Award. This week\'s honoree is <Colchester:team#84> first baseman <Joe Bartlett:player#3065>. When he steps into the batter\'s box, it\'s usually bad news for pitchers.\n\nFor the week he batted .556 (15-for-27) with 4 home runs and 5 RBIs.\n\nThis season <Bartlett:player#3065> is hitting at a .395 pace with 14 home runs, 28 RBIs and has scored 30 times.\n"), (827, "Tate Week\'s Top Player", 2822, 0, 0, 0, 0, 96, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 96, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week <Tim Tate:player#2822>, second baseman for the <Durham Silver Wolves:team#96>, slashed, mashed and bashed his way to the Sub League 2 Player of the Week trophy.\n\n<Tate:player#2822> put up a .500 average as he pounded out 13 hits, 5 home runs, 8 RBIs and scored 10 runs.\n\n<Tate:player#2822>\'s current batting average stands at .279 and he has chalked up 14 home runs and 26 RBIs.\n"), (828, "Injured Boyer Out 13 Months", 812, 0, 0, 0, 0, 6, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 6, 0, -5, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Tristan Boyer:player#812>, the <Brooklyn:team#6> reliever, was less than thrilled to learn that his recent injury would keep him out of the rest of the season and any postseason action.\n\n\"The playoffs?\" he said. \"Are you kidding me? The playoffs?\"\n\nBoyer has a ruptured ulnar collateral ligament, an injury that has hampered him since 08/13/2022.\n\nFor the season his stats show <Boyer:player#812> has 1 save in 58 relief appearances with a 5-3 record and 3.09 ERA.\n"), (829, "Season-Ending Injury for Talbert", 911, 0, 0, 0, 0, 58, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 58, 0, -5, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Plainview Power:team#58> have lost the services of <Lance Talbert:player#911> for the rest of this season. He suffered a torn labrum in a recent ballgame and the follow-up report from the medical staff is not good. Talbert is out for the year.\n\nTo date this year, he has registered 1 save, 2 wins and 3 losses with a 2.11 ERA. <Talbert:player#911> has made 46 relief appearances, worked a total of 64 innings and surrendered 45 hits. He has fanned 58, issued 24 free passes and held opposing clubs to a .194 batting average.\n"), (830, "It\'s Official: Hernandez Will Retire", 434, 0, 0, 0, 0, 36, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0,