", 521, 0, 0, 0, 0, 92, 96, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 92, 0, 0, "2022-8-15", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Chalk up another one for <Chesapeake Norse:team#92> center fielder <Eric Echols:player#521>. He now has hit in 20 straight games. <Echols:player#521> went 1-for-6 today\'s game at Silver Wolves Park but saw his club defeated 4-2 by the host <Durham Silver Wolves:team#96>.\n\n\"Playing on the road always makes it harder to get hits and to get wins,\" Norse manager <Armando Castro:coach#537> said after the game. \"We got one of the two, but unfortunately it was the wrong one.\"\n<Eric Echols:player#521> flied out in the 1st, flied out in the 3rd, struck out in the 5th, struck out in the 8th, struck out in the 9th and singled in the 12th.\n\nSo far this year <Echols:player#521> has hit .255 with 6 home runs, 17 RBIs and 28 runs scored.\n"), (843, "Rehab Road Tough for Royals Dennis Shaffer", 1057, 0, 0, 0, 0, 31, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 31, 0, 0, "2022-8-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It was learned today in <Cypress:team#31> that second baseman <Dennis Shaffer:player#1057> would miss more time because his recovery from a knee contusion was not going as well as expected. The Royals, however, were quick to relay that the setback did not seem to be serious and that <Shaffer:player#1057> would only miss one week more.\n\nIn this current campaign <Shaffer:player#1057> is hitting at a .269 clip with 2 home runs and 11 RBIs.\n"), (844, "Frank Irizarry Bashes Three over the Wall ", 1707, 0, 0, 0, 0, 47, 42, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 47, 0, 0, "2022-8-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Pittsburgh Razorbacks:team#47> third baseman <Frank Irizarry:player#1707> sensed he was going to have a good day at the plate, but he still might have underestimated it a little.\n\nPrior to the start of today\'s contest with the <St. Petersburg Naturals:team#42>, Irizarry told teammates he was sure he would hit a home run. He did -- three times.\n\n\"During batting practice I really had my swing down pat,\" he recalled. \"I felt some thunder in the lumber.\"\n\nThe big day from Irizarry pushed the Razorbacks past the Naturals, 7-3. To go along with the homers, he collected 5 RBIs and scored 3 runs.\n\n\"I was seeing good, feeling good and swinging good,\" Irizarry told reporters after the game.\n\n<Frank Irizarry:player#1707> hit a solo-shot off <Benito Aguilar:player#520> in the 3rd, hit a solo-shot off <Benito Aguilar:player#520> in the 5th, flied out in the 7th and hit a three-run home run off <Morgan Garrett:player#1618> in the 9th.\n\nSo far on the season Irizarry is hitting .209 with 9 home runs, 21 RBIs and 22 runs scored. He has 34 hits and played in 57 games.\n"), (845, "Minnick Hits in 20 Consecutive Games ", 3306, 0, 0, 0, 0, 61, 57, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 61, 0, 0, "2022-8-16", 0, 1, -1, 0, "And the streak goes on.\n\n<Chris Minnick:player#3306> collected yet another hit in the 6-5 <Hialeah Hornets:team#61> win over the Road Warriors at Hornets Field today. The Hialeah center fielder finished 1-for-6 in the game. During an extended batting practice session before the game, the famously hard-working Minnick had fielded questions from reporters about his hitting streak, which now sits at 20 games.\n\n\"I\'m not doing too much special,\" he said. \"I\'m well-prepared and I\'m just trying to get the bat on the ball and put it in play.\"\n<Chris Minnick:player#3306> struck out in the 1st, grounded out in the 2nd, grounded out in the 5th, singled in the 7th, struck out in the 9th and flied out in the 12th.\n\nThis year <Minnick:player#3306> is hitting .289 with 2 home runs.\n"), (846, "Invaders Bass Blanks Ivy", 372, 0, 0, 0, 0, 38, 37, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 38, 0, 0, "2022-8-17", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Seattle Invaders:team#38> right-hander <Shane Bass:player#372> used his full arsenal today to shoot down the <San Bernardino Ivy:team#37> 9-0. All day long, he exhibited fine command of all his pitches, giving up 1 walk and striking out 7. <Bass:player#372> allowed 8 hits to <San Bernardino:team#37> in the victory.\n\n\"It felt like my catcher and I were on the same page all day, and San Bernardino was on a way, way different page,\" Bass said.\n\n<Bass:player#372> has gone 2-5 this season with an ERA of 4.27 and 51 strikeouts in 71.2 innings pitched. Other clubs are hitting .258 against him.\n"), (847, "5-Hit Blitz by Scottsdale\'s Fanjul", 2934, 0, 0, 0, 0, 93, 94, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 93, 0, 0, "2022-8-17", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Scottsdale Cannoneers:team#93> first baseman <Willie Fanjul:player#2934> went 5-for-5 today and paced Scottsdale to a 12-8 victory over the <Yonkers Sparks:team#94> at Scottsdale Grounds. \n\n\"Well, that was fun,\" Fanjul said following the game.\n\n<Willie Fanjul:player#2934> hit a two-run double in the 1st, singled in the 3rd, hit an RBI double in the 4th, hit a two-run double in the 5th and hit a solo-shot off <Manuel Velez:player#1742> in the 7th.\n\nFor the year <Fanjul:player#2934> is batting .421 with 1 home run, 6 RBIs and 4 runs scored.\n"), (848, "Update: Duckworth Out 4 Months", 1029, 0, 0, 0, 0, 91, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 91, 0, -5, "2022-8-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Obviously disappointed, <Mike Duckworth:player#1029> confirmed today that his season is officially over. The <Dexter:team#91> third baseman offered mostly monosyllabic responses to reporters. \"Nope,\" he said, when asked if he might possibly return this year. The 18-year-old Duckworth suffered a torn calf muscle on 08/17/2022 and has been out of action since.\n\nIn 41 games this season <Duckworth:player#1029> has compiled a .214 batting average with 22 hits and 5 home runs. He has also scored 10 times and knocked in 17 runs.\n"), (849, "Garcia Set to Retire", 408, 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-8-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Gabriel Garcia:player#408> said years of hard work have taken their toll on him physically, and he\'s decided it\'s now time to retire.\n\n\"I don\'t know any way other than full throttle, I\'ve always been that way,\" he said. \"Going so hard for so many years might have cost me some time on my career, but I don\'t regret a thing.\"\n\nThe <Boston Wild Riders:team#16> second baseman is leaving the game behind at age 37.\n\n\n"), (850, "Earthquakes Flame Out Against Salinas, Badlanders", 1091, 0, 0, 0, 0, 30, 25, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 30, 0, 0, "2022-8-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "In a sharp 1-hit performance, <Larry Salinas:player#1091> led the <Irving Badlanders:team#30> to a 7-0 shutout victory over the <Fair Haven Earthquakes:team#25>, fanning 7 and walking 0.\n\n\"That\'s as good of stuff as I\'ve seen in a long time,\" <Fair Haven:team#25> manager <Aaron Smith:coach#219> said in a postgame interview.\n\nTo date this season, <Salinas:player#1091> has a record of 11 wins and 6 losses and a 4.41 ERA. He has appeared in 24 games and struck out 120 in 157 innings. \n"), (851, "Reed Catches up on Yard Work -- Slams 4 Homers", 439, 0, 0, 0, 0, 27, 32, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 4, 3, 5, 27, 0, 0, "2022-8-18", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Nothing could stop <David Reed:player#439> today -- certainly not the <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> pitching staff.\n\nThe 25-year-old first baseman for the <Bakersfield Millionaires:team#27> sent 4 baseballs soaring out of Apple Sox Park and made his name a part of history. Behind his barrage, the Millionaires took a 11-6 win over the Apple Sox.\n\n\"In the standings, a loss is just a loss, but this one was frustrating,\" Apple Sox manager <Chris Bingle:coach#231> said later. \"He clobbered us.\"\n\nReed\'s dream game included 4 hits in 5 at-bats, 4 homers, 7 runs driven in and 4 runs scored.\n\n\"I know all the stories are going to be about me today, and that\'s OK,\" Reed told the press in the locker room after the game. \"Next time, it\'ll be one of the other guys.\"\n\n<David Reed:player#439> flied out in the 1st, hit a solo-shot off <David Treat:player#51> in the 4th, hit a solo-shot off <David Treat:player#51> in the 6th, hit a three-run home run off <Willie Rodriguez:player#1954> in the 7th and hit a two-run home run off <Alberto Hernandez:player#1252> in the 9th.\n\nFor the season, <Reed:player#439> is hitting at a .277 clip with 25 home runs, 82 RBIs and has scored 54 runs. He has 114 hits, 34 walks and a .332 on-base percentage. \n"), (852, "Cowans Unleashes Tirade Against Media During Press Conference", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 14, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-8-18", 0, 1, 2, 0, "<New York Owls:team#14> manager, <Seth Cowans:coach#82>, wasn\'t happy with his team or the local media. Pressured for answers to better understand his team\'s performance, <Cowans:coach#82> let go of all reason in a profanity-laced tirade to the media, his own team, and anyone within earshot. \"You know, it doesn\'t help the situation when you people are shoving microphones down our throats looking for answers! Well, this is your answer - I don\'t have one! We\'re doing all we can out there. Some players are pulling their weight, but others are not. They have enough pressure on their own, and then all of you don\'t make it any better. They just have to work out of it themselves.\" \n\nWhen it was commented that Cowans wasn\'t doing a good enough job of motivating his players, his time bomb went off. \"Oh, that\'s a bunch of [expletive], and you know it. Players motivate themselves. I\'m happy to take the blame most of the time, but not for that. That\'s not my [expletive] job!\" At that point, <Cowans:coach#82> walked out of the press conference.\n"), (853, "Hornets Celebrate Postseason Clinch", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 61, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 61, 0, 0, "2022-8-19", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Stop the presses, the <Hialeah Hornets:team#61> are heading to the postseason!\n\nA berth in the playoffs became assured for Hialeah tonight, with the club\'s record sitting at 75-48.\n\n\"We\'re right where we want to be at this point of the season,\" said reliever <Ricardo Valencia:player#2167>.\n"), (854, "Contreras Spectacular in 12-0 Win", 2030, 0, 0, 0, 0, 53, 52, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 53, 0, 0, "2022-8-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Isidro Contreras:player#2030> of the <Modesto Oil Barons:team#53> was really in the zone as he mowed down the <Washington:team#52> hitters 12-0 in a sterling mound performance.\n\n\"I\'m feeling good overall,\" he said. \"I\'m executing my pitches, I\'m able to hit my spots and I\'m getting outs in key situations.\"\n\nContreras shut down the <Washington Hooks:team#52>, blanking them on 3 hits while registering 9 strikeouts and 1 walk.\n\nThis season <Contreras:player#2030> has compiled a 16-5 mark, 2.42 ERA and made 25 starts.\n"), (855, "Starks Stops Minnick\'s Hit Streak", 3306, 0, 0, 0, 0, 61, 63, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 4, 3, 5, 61, 0, 0, "2022-8-20", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Chris Minnick:player#3306>\'s 23-game hitting streak has now come and gone. It was snapped today as the <Hialeah Hornets:team#61> suffered a 4-2 setback against the <Starks Westerners:team#63>.\n\nMinnick went without a hit in 3 trips to the plate. He was visibly upset during a postgame press conference, but it appeared that the streak had little to do with it.\n\n\"The hitting streak was one of those things where it was fun while it lasted, but I\'m not going to lose any sleep about it tonight,\" he said. \"On the other hand, I am going to lose sleep about dropping this game today.\"\n\n<Minnick:player#3306> is currently batting .287 with 2 home runs and 22 RBIs.\n"), (856, "Craddock Out of Commission 8 Months", 596, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 10, 0, -5, "2022-8-21", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Clearly dejected, <Matt Craddock:player#596> left the <Houston:team#10> clubhouse nearly in tears this afternoon. He acknowledged that his season is over after sustaining a ruptured medial collateral ligament in a ballgame recently. It brings an early end to the <Houston:team#10> center fielder\'s season.\n\nThis year <Craddock:player#596> has socked 37 hits in 157 at-bats for a .236 average with 3 home runs. He is getting on base at a .330 pace and his totals also include 22 RBIs and 19 runs scored.\n"), (857, "Perez Out 4 Months", 1611, 0, 0, 0, 0, 80, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 80, 0, -5, "2022-8-21", 0, 1, -1, 0, "\"Not what I wanted to hear,\" said <Elkridge:team#80>\'s <Rich Perez:player#1611> to reporters this afternoon, as he revealed that the injury he sustained on 08/20/2022 would force him to miss the rest of the season. \"The doctor made it clear,\" Perez said. \"There\'s no chance for me -- none at all -- to come back this year. That\'s the last thing I wanted to hear.\" Perez has been out of action since he suffered a torn labrum.\n\nThis season-to-date <Perez:player#1611> has 3 wins and 2 losses and a 5.45 ERA.\n"), (858, "Gonzalez Learns More about Injury", 2134, 0, 0, 0, 0, 58, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 58, 0, -5, "2022-8-21", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Team officials for the <Plainview Power:team#58> confirmed that a torn flexor tendon in his elbow will force <Javier Gonzalez:player#2134> to miss the rest of the season. Gonzalez sustained the injury on 08/18/2022. It remains to be seen who will replace Gonzalez on the active roster.\n\nFor the season <Gonzalez:player#2134> has made 10 relief appearances, recorded 1 save and compiled a 1-1 won-lost mark and a 2.25 ERA. In pitching 12 innings, he has totaled 11 strikeouts and 5 walks.\n"), (859, "Red-Hot Bat: Martinez Collects Cycle", 495, 0, 0, 0, 0, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 11, 0, 0, "2022-8-21", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Most fans have never seen a player hit for the cycle, and most players have never done it -- but it happened today at Nailers Park. <Daniel Martinez:player#495> of the <Charlotte Nailers:team#11> accomplished the feat against <Boston Wild Riders:team#16>.\n\nMartinez went 5-for-5 with 1 single, 2 doubles, 1 triple and 1 home run in the 12-7 Charlotte victory.\n\n\"That was one for the grandkids, am I right?\" Martinez said after the game. \n\nMartinez also scored 3 runs and had 2 RBI in a day to remember for both <Martinez:player#495> and the crowd at Nailers Park.\n\n<Daniel Martinez:player#495> tripled in the 1st, singled in the 3rd, doubled in the 4th, hit a solo-shot off <Edgar Rojas:player#2294> in the 6th and hit an RBI double in the 8th.\n\n<Martinez:player#495> on the season is hitting .316 with 35 home runs. His stats include 87 RBIs and 98 runs scored.\n\n<View Boxscore:box#1140>\n"), (860, "Hit Parade: Martinez Pops 5 Hits", 495, 0, 0, 0, 0, 11, 16, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 11, 0, 0, "2022-8-21", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It seemed that <Charlotte:team#11> center fielder <Daniel Martinez:player#495> could do no wrong as the Nailers KO\'d the Wild Riders, 12-7 today. Martinez rapped out 5 hits in 5 at-bats and seemed to know which pitches Wild Riders hurlers were throwing. \n\n\"I think the Nailers were stealing signs,\" growled one unhappy <Boston:team#16> fan after the game. \n\n\"I just felt good today. I saw the ball well and just wanted to make good contact and put the ball in play,\" said the jubilant <Martinez:player#495> in the postgame press interview. \n\n<Daniel Martinez:player#495> tripled in the 1st, singled in the 3rd, doubled in the 4th, hit a solo-shot off <Edgar Rojas:player#2294> in the 6th and hit an RBI double in the 8th.\n\nFor the year <Martinez:player#495> has hit at a .316 clip with 87 RBIs, 35 home runs and 98 runs scored.\n\n<View Boxscore:box#1140>\n"), (861, "Josh Burrell Institutes \'Casual Fridays\'", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-8-21", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Josh Burrell:coach#73> is well known for being an easygoing manager and he\'s taken that to a whole new level.\n\nThe <Boston Wild Riders:team#16> skipper has instituted a \'Casual Friday\' policy for his club. While the team is expected to dress in professional looking attire throughout the season, he\'s allowing them to dress however they want one day a week.\n\n\"Jeans, T-shirts, shorts, whatever,\" he said. \"They do it in offices, so why not with a pro ball team? And while it\'s casual on Friday, I think the guys know they can be pretty casual the rest of the week too. Being comfortable is more important than looking like a suit model.\"\n\nThe players say their manager\'s approach has been well received.\n\n\"He\'s pretty relaxed, makes it easier for us to just relax as well and focus on baseball,\" said <Omar Garcia:player#398>.\n"), (862, "Cowans Fined by League After Tirade", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 16, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 0, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-8-21", 0, 1, 2, 0, "<Owls:team#14> manager, <Seth Cowans:coach#82>, was fined by the league for his angry rant during a press conference two days ago. <Cowans:coach#82>, who verbally assaulted reporters gathered for the post-game Q and A session, avoided suspension. He will, however, be forced to pay an undisclosed fine as punishment for his actions. \n\n\"It\'s fair\", commented <Cowans:coach#82> after the decision was handed down. \"Honestly, I\'m very lucky I didn\'t get suspended for what I said.\" Cowans, who was much more gracious and civil with reporters today, took full responsibility for his previous behavior. \"My actions were stupid and unforgivable,\" he added. \"Frankly, I\'m embarrassed that I let myself lose control like that. You guys were just doing your jobs. I apologize to anyone who witnessed that ugliness. And not just the media, but the league, the organization, and the fans. I\'ll try to keep it together better next time.\"\n"), (863, "Great Week for Detroit\'s Jonathan Van Vooren ", 159, 0, 0, 0, 0, 4, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 4, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s best performer in the Sub League 1 was second baseman <Jonathan Van Vooren:player#159> of the <Detroit Cannons:team#4>.\n\nHe slashed out a .455 average and was voted the Player of the Week. Over the last week <Van Vooren:player#159> stroked 10 hits in 22 at-bats and 3 home runs, drove in 9 runs and scored 3 times.\n\nCurrently <Van Vooren:player#159> is batting .292 with 12 home runs and 53 RBIs.\n"), (864, "Rosales Selected Top Player", 720, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 9, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Emanuel Rosales:player#720> more than did his part for the <San Francisco Valley Cats:team#9> over the last seven days and earned Sub League 2 Player of the Week honors in the process.\n\nThe club\'s catcher logged an impressive .600 average, drove in 6 runs, hit no home runs and scored 4 times. \n\n<Rosales:player#720> is hitting at a .346 mark this season. His stats show 5 home runs, 50 RBIs and 47 runs scored. He has played 98 games for the <Valley Cats:team#9>.\n"), (865, "Knights Rodriguez Snags SL1 Player of the Week", 218, 0, 0, 0, 0, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 24, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This past week the best batter in the Sub League 1 was <Danny Rodriguez:player#218>, who banged his way to the Player of the Week Trophy.\n\nDuring the week the <North Hempstead:team#24> first baseman compiled a .444 batting average (12-for-27) with 3 home runs, 5 runs batted in and scored 7 runs.\n\nThis season <Rodriguez:player#218> has 16 home runs and a .293 batting average.\n"), (866, "Earthquakes Studdard SL2 Hitter of the Week", 1394, 0, 0, 0, 0, 25, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 25, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week he let his bat do the talking. That\'s why <Scott Studdard:player#1394> of the <Fair Haven Earthquakes:team#25> was named the Sub League 2 Player of the Week.\n\nFor the week the 25-year-old third baseman batted .409 (9-for-22) with 4 home runs, 5 runs and 7 RBIs.\n\nCurrently <Studdard:player#1394> has 13 home runs and a .263 batting average.\n"), (867, "SL1 Player of the Week Awarded", 1892, 0, 0, 0, 0, 40, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 40, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "A red-hot bat made <Andrew Wall:player#1892> the obvious choice for this week\'s Sub League 1 Player of the Week.\n\nThe <Burnside:team#40> center fielder laid down some numbers that no one else could match, including a .400 average on 10 hits in 25 at-bats, 5 home runs, 12 RBIs, and 9 runs scored. Say no more ... he got the award.\n\nSo far this year, <Wall:player#1892> is batting .265 with 31 home runs and 79 RBIs.\n"), (868, "Star of the Week Honored in SL2", 1527, 0, 0, 0, 0, 45, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 45, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "His solid numbers speak for themselves. That\'s why <Javier Sassetti:player#1527> of the <Dixie Inn Renegades:team#45> was named the Sub League 2 Player of the Week.\n\nFor the week <Sassetti:player#1527> batted .474 (9-for-19) with 4 home runs and 5 RBIs.\n\nIn his stats this season, <Sassetti:player#1527> has posted a batting average of .213 with 56 hits in 263 at-bats, 11 home runs and 20 RBIs. He has also scored 34 runs, walked 17 times and compiled a .267 OBP.\n"), (869, "Star of the Week Picked in SL1", 1346, 0, 0, 0, 0, 49, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 49, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Justin Anderson:player#1346> punched, poked and pummeled the baseball last week and today he garnered a majority of the votes for the Sub League 1 Player of the Week award.\n\nThe <Atlanta Dingos:team#49> left fielder slashed out a .526 average with 10 hits in 19 at-bats, 5 home runs and 10 RBIs.\n\nThis year <Anderson:player#1346> is hitting .385 with 7 home runs and 13 RBIs to his credit. He has gotten on base at a .419 clip and scored 9 runs.\n"), (870, "Doby Bags SL2 Best Player Award", 3195, 0, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 60, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Matt Doby:player#3195> of the Lubbock Peaches had a spectacular week and today was voted the Player of the Week by the Sub League 2.\n\nFor the week <Doby:player#3195> batted .579 (11-for-19) with 3 home runs and 5 RBIs.\n\nDoby is hitting .299 this year with 8 home runs, 22 RBIs and 16 runs scored. He has 47 hits in 157 at-bats, 14 walks and a .358 on-base percentage. <Doby:player#3195> has played in 44 games.\n"), (871, "SL1\'s #1 Player Named", 3230, 0, 0, 0, 0, 66, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 66, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Jeremiah Hurdle:player#3230> of the Maude Buffaloes had an outstanding week and today was voted the Player of the Week by the Sub League 1.\n\nFor the week the 23-year-old first baseman batted .520 (13-for-25) with 2 home runs and 9 RBIs.\n\nIn 12 games this year Hurdle has posted a .422 average and put up these numbers: 2 home runs, 9 RBIs and 8 runs scored.\n"), (872, "SL2 Votes Golden Bears Atkinson Top Player", 444, 0, 0, 0, 0, 75, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 75, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Norfolk Golden Bears:team#75> second baseman <Dennis Atkinson:player#444> had a great time at the plate last week, running up some sensational numbers that no one else could match. Few people were surprised today when the Sub League 2 named him Player of the Week.\n\nAtkinson banged out 17 hits in 31 at-bats on the way to a .548 batting average. He also racked up 2 home runs, 4 RBIs and 7 runs scored.\n\nIn his season totals, <Atkinson:player#444> has 3 home runs, .311 BA, .359 OBP, 17 RBIs and 23 runs scored. He has played in 54 games.\n"), (873, "Cooper Wins SL1 Player of the Week Trophy", 3193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 87, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 87, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The #1 hitter in the Sub League 1 was <Omaha:team#87> center fielder <David Cooper:player#3193>. He was selected the Player of the Week.\n\nDuring the week Cooper banged out a .579 batting average (11-for-19), 3 home runs, 10 runs batted in and scored 6 runs. \n\nA look at his current stats shows <Cooper:player#3193> with a .600 average, 3 home runs, 10 RBIs and 10 runs scored. He has played in 8 games.\n"), (874, "Star of the Week Named in SL2", 2822, 0, 0, 0, 0, 96, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 96, 0, 0, "2022-8-22", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Tim Tate:player#2822> of the Durham Silver Wolves had a super week and today was voted the Player of the Week by