ory today behind the shutout pitching of <Frank Sanchez:player#276>. He surrendered no runs, gave up 2 hits and finished the game with 2 walks and 3 strikeouts. The Whitecaps won the game by a score of 3-0.\n\nChecking out his stats for the season, <Sanchez:player#276> has racked up 3 wins and 7 losses in 7 starts, 4.48 ERA and struck out 56 batters in 84.1 innings. \n"), (914, "DeMascio Smashes 3 Homers for Phoenix", 251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 3, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 8, 0, 0, "2022-8-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Justin DeMascio:player#251> went on an explosive hitting spree against the <Memphis T-Bones:team#3> at Ballpark of Memphis today, launching a trio of blasts to lead the <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8> to the 6-5 win.\n\nThe first baseman finished 3-for-6 with 3 runs scored and 4 RBI.\n\n\"It was just one of those days,\" DeMascio said in a postgame interview. \"I don\'t know how to explain it. I\'m just putting a good swing on the ball.\"\n\n<Memphis:team#3> skipper <Brett Cox:coach#37> said DeMascio was \"locked-in.\"\n\n\"We made some pretty good pitches,\" he said. \"Those first two homers were exactly where the pitcher wanted to put them. He\'s just hot right now -- you\'ve just got to tip your hat to him.\"\n\n<Justin DeMascio:player#251> flied out in the 1st, struck out in the 3rd, hit a solo-shot off <Craig Farrell:player#1536> in the 5th, struck out in the 7th, hit a solo-shot off <Tom Berry:player#758> in the 9th and hit a two-run home run off <Edgar Gomez:player#197> in the 11th.\n\nFor the season, <DeMascio:player#251> is hitting at a .312 clip with 38 home runs, 78 RBIs and has scored 80 runs. He has 120 hits, 60 walks and a .420 on-base percentage. \n"), (915, "3 Boomers for Nungaray ", 1911, 0, 0, 0, 0, 63, 57, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 63, 0, 0, "2022-8-25", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Every now and then, everything just comes together.\n\n<Hector Nungaray:player#1911> discovered that today at Road Warriors Field, as he smashed three home runs during the 7-3 <Starks Westerners:team#63> win over the <Des Moines Road Warriors:team#57>.\n\n\"I got three balls to hit and nailed all three of them,\" the <Starks:team#63> first baseman said in his postgame interview. \"The first was a hanging curve, the second was right down the middle and the last one was a good pitch, but I guessed right and put the wood to it.\"\n\nNungaray finished the day with 3 hits in 4 at-bats and 5 RBIs.\n\n<Hector Nungaray:player#1911> hit a solo-shot off <Riley DeLuca:player#1881> in the 2nd, hit a two-run home run off <Riley DeLuca:player#1881> in the 4th, grounded out in the 6th and hit a two-run home run off <Jordan Carrasco:player#2349> in the 8th.\n\nSo far this year, <Nungaray:player#1911> is batting .258 with 10 home runs and 27 RBIs.\n"), (916, "Saldana Has Season End", 2770, 0, 0, 0, 0, 91, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 91, 0, -5, "2022-8-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Leonel Saldana:player#2770> had to wait several agonizing days to find out his diagnosis after suffering a bone spur in his elbow on 08/22/2022. Today he received word from the <Dexter:team#91> doctor that he would be out the rest of the year. Team officials called it a huge setback but something they would have to overcome.\n\nThis year <Saldana:player#2770> has earned 2 saves, worked 22 innings, fanned 34 hitters and recorded a 3.68 ERA. He has also put up a 1-4 won-lost mark.\n"), (917, "Early Season End for Santos", 3267, 0, 0, 0, 0, 65, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 65, 0, -5, "2022-8-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Danny Santos:player#3267> had hoped for the best, but expected the worst. Today, he learned from the <Lexington:team#65> medical staff that he would miss the rest of the season. The <Lexington:team#65> starting pitcher suffered an arthritic elbow in an earlier ballgame. He admitted to being discouraged, but said he plans to come back strong next year.\n\nThis season-to-date, <Santos:player#3267> has fashioned a 6-3 mark and 2.69 ERA in 63.2 innings. Opposing clubs are batting .220 against him and he has logged 51 strikeouts. \n"), (918, "Lumberjacks Justin DeMascio Sidelined", 251, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 8, 0, -5, "2022-8-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8> will be without the services of <Justin DeMascio:player#251> for 4-5 weeks after an incident in a game against the <Jacksonville Orange Sox:team#1>. The 30-year-old first baseman was injured while running the bases and suffered a strained hamstring.\n\nCurrently DeMascio is batting .310 with 38 home runs, 78 RBIs and 80 runs scored.\n"), (919, "Players Suspended in Bluebirds-Renegades Donnybrook", 1582, 1511, 0, 0, 0, 44, 45, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 44, 0, 0, "2022-8-26", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Josh Platteter:player#1582> of the <Long Beach Bluebirds:team#44> and <Trent Millen:player#1511> of the <Dixie Inn Renegades:team#45> will be on the sidelines for a few days. They have been suspended for 5 and 11 games respectively by the league office for causing the bench-emptying free-for-all at the recent Bluebirds-Renegades game at Long Beach Fields.\n\nNeither player had any comment about the suspensions. Both clubs told BNN <Platteter:player#1582> and <Millen:player#1511> will begin serving them soon.\n\nPlatteter is currently batting .254 with 22 home runs, 51 RBIs and 50 runs scored. He has 85 hits in 334 at-bats.\n\nIn 5 starts this season <Millen:player#1511> has compiled a 8-1 record and a 3.74 ERA. \n"), (920, "Hialeah Hornets Win Top Spot in Sub League 2 East Division", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 61, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 61, 0, 0, "2022-8-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Members of the <Hialeah Hornets:team#61> say winning the Sub League 2 East Division title is special, but ultimately they will only be remembered with a championship season.\n\n\"We want to put ourselves in the history books and win the World Series,\" said starting pitcher <Oscar Cardenas:player#3070>. \"We all believe it can happen, it\'s just a matter of putting in the hard work and getting the breaks.\"\n\nIt\'s the 0 division win for the club and they will be vying for their 1st World Series win.\n\n\"To see the team get here, it makes you believe in yourself and all the systems you\'ve put in place,\" said manager <Nick Duhart:coach#375>.\n"), (921, "Injury Sidelines Petersen for Season", 1793, 0, 0, 0, 0, 31, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 31, 0, -5, "2022-8-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The latest news from the <Cypress Royals:team#31> clubhouse is this: closer <Mike Petersen:player#1793> is expected to be out of action for another 8-9 months. He has a partially torn ulnar collateral ligament, sustained on 08/25/2022. Petersen expressed a bit of relief. \"At least now I know,\" he said.\n\nThis season <Petersen:player#1793> has notched 8 saves with 11 strikeouts and 7 walks in 11.1 innings while registering a 2.38 ERA and a 0-0 won-lost record. \n"), (922, "Omaha\'s Cooper Goes Ballistic with 5 Hits", 3193, 0, 0, 0, 0, 87, 84, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 87, 0, 0, "2022-8-27", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Omaha:team#87> center fielder <David Cooper:player#3193> had a big day at Victory Field today against the <Colchester Victory:team#84>. The 21-year-old, who is not typically considered a big threat with the bat, went 5-for-5 and led the Imperials to a 5-3 triumph over Colchester.\n\n\"Hey, I\'m as surprised as you guys are,\" Cooper said in his postgame comments, smiling as he scolded the press corps for underestimating him. \"Maybe I\'m not so bad at the plate after all.\"\n\n<David Cooper:player#3193> singled in the 1st, hit an RBI double in the 3rd, singled in the 5th, singled in the 8th and hit an RBI single in the 9th.\n\nIn his stats this season, <Cooper:player#3193> has posted a batting average of .468 with 22 hits in 47 at-bats, 3 home runs and 14 RBIs. He has also scored 13 runs, walked 13 times and compiled a .583 OBP.\n"), (923, "Mavericks Headed to the Postseason", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 36, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 36, 0, 0, "2022-8-28", 0, 1, -1, 0, "An \"enormous burden\" has been lifted off the shoulders of the <Sparta Mavericks:team#36>, according to their second baseman.\n\n\"We\'re in the playoffs now, for sure, and that\'s all that matters,\" said <Perry Fehnel:player#2225>.\n\nSparta currently has a record of 74-57.\n"), (924, "Lubbock Headed to the Postseason", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 60, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 60, 0, 0, "2022-8-28", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Lubbock Peaches:team#60> will be a part of this year\'s postseason.\n\nOn the strength of their 70-61 record, the Peaches have clinched a spot in the postseason, although it\'s not yet official whether or not that will be a division title or a wild card berth.\n\nThe Sub League 2 West Division team will be seeking its 1st FBL Class A championship once playoffs begin.\n"), (925, "Did Camacho Demand Trade?", 590, 0, 0, 0, 0, 10, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 10, 0, 0, "2022-8-28", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It is unknown at this time if there is any truth to the rumor that <Houston:team#10>\'s <Edgar Camacho:player#590> has asked his team for a trade. Insiders indicate the left fielder might not be happy with club management. So far, the team\'s owners have refused to comment.\n"), (926, "Scott Bashes 5 Base Hits", 3095, 0, 0, 0, 0, 55, 56, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 4, 2, 5, 55, 0, 0, "2022-8-28", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Kareem Scott:player#3095> of the <Kansas City Capitals:team#55> went on a hitting spree today against the <Madison Astros:team#56> pitching staff, racking up 5 hits in 5 at-bats, but to no avail -- the Astros put a damper on his day and prevailed 6-5 over the Capitals.\n\n\"It was a heck of a day and I was kind of looking forward to a better ending than that,\" he said later.\n\n<Kareem Scott:player#3095> singled in the 2nd, hit an RBI single in the 3rd, hit an RBI single in the 5th, singled in the 8th and hit an RBI single in the 9th.\n\nThis year <Scott:player#3095> is hitting .276 with 4 home runs and 9 RBIs to his credit. He has gotten on base at a .337 clip and scored 7 runs.\n"), (927, "Rowdy Players Suspended by League", 1914, 1562, 0, 0, 0, 63, 61, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 63, 0, 0, "2022-8-28", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Baseball officials have suspended two players for \"inappropriate and aggressive conduct\" in yesterday\'s <Starks:team#63>-<Hialeah:team#61> contest at Starks Stadium. The Westerners <Victor Gomez:player#1914> and the Hornets <Danny Broskey:player#1562> will have to sit out 4 and 8 games respectively for their parts in the brawl. \n\nThis season <Gomez:player#1914> is hitting .182 with 33 hits, 2 home runs, 13 RBIs, scored 9 runs and played in 57 games.\n\nThis year <Broskey:player#1562> has posted a record of 7 wins and 4 losses with a 4.20 ERA. He has appeared in 22 games and struck out 103 in 137 innings. \n"), (928, "Ramirez Picked SL1 Player of the Week", 265, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 8, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Today the Sub League 1 announced its Player of the Week Award winner -- <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8> catcher <Pedro Ramirez:player#265>, who batted .571 (8-for-14) with 2 home runs, 5 RBIs and 4 runs scored. \n\nBatting .208 to date, Ramirez has 7 home runs and 29 RBIs.\n"), (929, "Boren Collects Player of the Week Award", 539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 12, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 12, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 2 made it official today: <Ken Boren:player#539> is the Player of the Week.\n\nHe really glistened on the diamond this week with a .440 average to take home the honor. The <Chicago:team#12> left fielder went 11-for-25, drove in 4 runs, scored 7 times and hit 2 home runs.\n\nThis season <Boren:player#539> is batting .361 with 45 home runs. He has scored 117 runs and driven in 104.\n"), (930, "Red-Hot Cervantes SL1 Player of the Week", 205, 0, 0, 0, 0, 24, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 24, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Player of the Week has been announced by the Sub League 1. The honor went to <Ruben Cervantes:player#205>, second baseman of the <North Hempstead Knights:team#24>.\n\nHe burned up the league with a .524 average to win the award. <Cervantes:player#205> went 11-for-21 for the week, totaled 1 home run with 5 RBIs and scored 3 times.\n\nSo far this year <Cervantes:player#205> has 2 home runs and a .500 batting average.\n"), (931, "SL2 Names Millionaires Garcia Winner", 1236, 0, 0, 0, 0, 27, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 27, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "His teammates, fans, peers and even the BNN sportswriters all agreed that <Ricky Garcia:player#1236> was worthy of the Sub League 2 Player of the Week Award.\n\nDuring the week the <Bakersfield:team#27> shortstop compiled a .375 batting average (9-for-24) with 3 home runs, 5 RBI and scored 5 runs.\n\nPresently <Garcia:player#1236> is hitting .264 with 14 home runs and 45 RBIs. He has played in 117 games and scored 59 times.\n"), (932, "Week\'s Top Player: Buffalo\'s Martinez", 1736, 0, 0, 0, 0, 35, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 35, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 1 has chosen <Ernesto Martinez:player#1736> of the <Buffalo Sluggers:team#35> as Player of the Week.\n\nWhat a week <Martinez:player#1736> had. He hit .750 (6-for-8) with 2 home runs, 4 RBIs and 4 runs scored. \n\nThis season <Martinez:player#1736> has banged out 106 hits in 392 at-bats for a .270 average with 27 home runs. He is getting on base at a .343 pace and his totals also include 63 RBIs and 64 runs scored.\n"), (933, "SL2\'s Top Player, Welke of St. Petersburg", 1471, 0, 0, 0, 0, 42, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 42, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Josh Welke:player#1471> of the <St. Petersburg Naturals:team#42> put the wraps on a fantastic week of play by being named the Sub League 2 Player of the Week.\n\nThe hot-hitting third baseman was a bonafide batting machine as he racked up 9 hits in 22 at-bats, 3 home runs, .409 BA, 7 RBIs, 6 runs, 1 walk and a .480 OBP.\n\nSo far this season Welke is hitting .271 with 11 home runs, 37 RBIs and 38 runs scored. He has 82 hits in 303 at-bats and a .325 OBP. \n"), (934, "Berkowitz of Atlanta Crowned Best Player", 1342, 0, 0, 0, 0, 49, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 49, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Like a machine, <David Berkowitz:player#1342> hit the baseball with brutal efficiency last week, gaining himself the Sub League 1 Player of the Week title for that stretch.\n\nThe <Atlanta Dingos:team#49> third baseman rapped out a .429 average with 12 hits in 28 at-bats, 2 home runs, 6 runs batted in and 3 runs scored.\n\nOn the season, <Berkowitz:player#1342> is batting .241 with 12 home runs and 44 RBIs. He has played in 119 games.\n"), (935, "SL2 Player of the Week Named", 2926, 0, 0, 0, 0, 61, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 61, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "This week\'s standout performer in the Sub League 2 was second baseman <Bob Weicker:player#2926> of the <Hialeah Hornets:team#61>.\n\nHe belted out a .455 average and was voted the Player of the Week. Over the last week <Weicker:player#2926> collected 10 hits in 22 at-bats and 6 home runs, drove in 10 runs and scored 6 times.\n\nSo far this season <Weicker:player#2926> has gotten 92 hits in 438 at-bats for a .210 batting average with 24 home runs. His stats include 65 RBIs and 60 runs scored. He has played in 121 games.\n"), (936, "Week\'s Premier Performer Honored by SL1", 3180, 0, 0, 0, 0, 72, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 72, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 1 has selected its Player of the Week. The honor went to <Pat Greene:player#3180>, center fielder of the <Spokane A\'s:team#72>.\n\nIn a standout performance, he lit up the league with a .429 average to win the award. <Greene:player#3180> went 12-for-28 for the week, totaled 2 home runs with 8 RBIs and scored 6 times.\n\nOn the year <Greene:player#3180> has hit .294 with 11 home runs, 33 RBIs and scored 39 runs.\n"), (937, "Jairo Lopez Captures SL2 Award", 2539, 0, 0, 0, 0, 76, 0, 0, 0, 0, 204, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 76, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Jairo Lopez:player#2539> of the Oklahoma City Friars had a big week with the bat and today was voted the Player of the Week by the Sub League 2.\n\nFor the week <Lopez:player#2539> batted .524 (11-for-21) with no home runs and 1 RBIs.\n\nThis year <Lopez:player#2539> is hitting .243 with 2 home runs.\n"), (938, "Steelers Josh Hicks Swings Hot Bat, SL1 Winner", 3336, 0, 0, 0, 0, 85, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 85, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Josh Hicks:player#3336> swung a blistering bat last week for <Amarillo:team#85>, rapping out 9 hits in 17 at-bats against Steelers opponents to propel himself to the Sub League 1 Player of the Week Award.\n\nWhenever the first baseman hit the ball, he hit it with authority. The 19-year-old racked up a .529 batting average with 3 home runs, 5 RBIs and 5 runs scored.\n\nFor the season, <Hicks:player#3336> is hitting at a .413 clip with 4 home runs, 9 RBIs and has scored 9 runs. He has 19 hits, 5 walks and a .472 on-base percentage. \n"), (939, "SL2 Awards Player of the Week Trophy", 3086, 0, 0, 0, 0, 91, 0, 0, 0, 0, 205, 0, 3, 7, 1, 5, 91, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Ronnie Tish:player#3086> made quite a splash in the Sub League 2 this past week. The <Dexter 76ers:team#91> right fielder drilled opposing pitchers for 11 hits in 27 at-bats to roll up a .407 batting average and the Sub League 2 Player of the Week Award.\n\nHe also contributed 6 home runs, 9 RBIs and 8 runs scored to his club\'s offensive attack.\n\n<Tish:player#3086> on the season is hitting .326 with 16 home runs. His stats include 26 RBIs and 36 runs scored.\n"), (940, "Blue Raiders Off to the Postseason", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 19, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The math is in the favor of the <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19>. The club can no longer be ousted from a playoff position, with a berth in the postseason now a guarantee.\n\nGreendale boasts a 78-48 record and will be looking for the 1st World Series in team history.\n"), (941, "Winston-Salem Cheetahs Clinch Spot in Postseason", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 48, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 48, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "It remains to be seen how the 2022 <Winston-Salem Cheetahs:team#48> will be remembered, but one thing is now assured - the team will have a chance to win their 1st World Series.\n\nOn the strength of their 73-59 record, the Cheetahs today officially punched their ticket for the postseason, although it remains to be seen whether that will be as a division winner.\n"), (942, "Dixie Inn Makes the Playoffs", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 45, 0, 0, 0, 0, 202, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 45, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Postseason baseball is coming to Dixie Inn.\n\nThe <Dixie Inn Renegades:team#45> have punched their ticket past the regular season, by today securing a playoff berth on the strength of their 73-59 record.\n\nThe Sub League 2 West Division club can now focus on trying to win the division, but mathematically the club can no longer be ousted from a playoff spot.\n"), (943, "Postseason Bid Ends for Akron", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 50, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 50, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The playoff hopes of the <Akron Steelhounds:team#50> have been extinguished for the year. Today, the team was mathematically eliminated from qualifying for the 2022 postseason. \n\n\"It\'s weird, yesterday we were all talking about what we needed to do to make it to the World Series and now we\'re just counting down the days until the offseason, said Steelhounds starting pitcher <Sean Lieberman:player#3207>.\n\n"), (944, "Wild Card Clinched by Killer Whales", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 59, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 59, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The <Hoagland Killer Whales:team#59> have secured a berth in the FBL Class A playoffs.\n\nThe club officially claimed a wild card position today, on the strength of their 69-63 record.\n\n\"Obviously we would have liked to have won the Sub League 2 East Division, but we\'re still proud of our accomplishment,\" said reliever <Jason Johnson:player#37>.\n\nThe club will be vying for their franchise\'s 1st championship when the playoffs get underway.\n"), (945, "Power Won\'t Get Playoff Berth", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 58, 0, 0, 0, 0, 203, 0, 1, 3, 3, 5, 58, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Postseason baseball won\'t be coming to Plainview this year. The quest for the playoffs ended for the <Plainview Power:team#58> today, as they were mathematically eliminated from contention.\n\n\"Not the first time I\'ve experienced this,\" said Power manager <Josh Diez:coach#381>, \"but it never gets fun.\"\n\n"), (946, "Season-Ending Injury for Zielinski", 651, 0, 0, 0, 0, 17, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 8, 1, 5, 17, 0, -5, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The injury that has kept <Skylar Zielinski:player#651> out of action since 08/26/2022 will keep him out a while longer. <Mannford Monsters:team#17> officials made the announcement this afternoon. They said that Zielinski is expected to miss at least 6-7 months with radial nerve compression.\n\nThis season <Zielinski:player#651> has made 41 relief appearances and saved 6 games. His record is 5-6 with 43 strikeouts in 51 innings with a 6.35 ERA.\n"), (947, "Trade Rumors in the Air in San Jose", 153, 0, 0, 0, 0, 7, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 7, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Danny Duran:player#153> might be headed to another team -- that is, if rumors around the <San Jose:team#7> clubhouse have any merit. The 36-year-old reliever has said publicly that he welcomes a trade.\n"), (948, "Weekly Team Power Rankings", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 9, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 0, 2, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-8-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Here are the current team power rankings for Fictional Baseball League:\n\nTeams (Total Points, Tendency):\n1) <San Francisco Valley Cats:team#9> (110.5, o)\n2) <Chicago Quakes:team#12> (108.9, +)\n3) <Phoenix Lumberjacks:team#8> (108.6, -)\n4) <Jacksonville Orange Sox:team#1> (108.4, -)\n5) <Houston Seagulls:team#10> (104.2, ++)\n6) <Charlo