, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 6, 2, 5, 23, 0, 0, "2022-10-28", 0, 1, -1, 0, "When <Steve Boudreau:coach#198> was hired to lead the <Jersey City Wild Dogs:team#23>, fans were expecting improvement over the last manager. Today, flanked by team officials, <Boudreau:coach#198> accepted the Sub League 1 Manager of the Year Award, noting the level of passion for the <Jersey City Wild Dogs:team#23>.\n\n\"The biggest challenge was the fans. I don\'t know how many times I was asked, if I thought the club was good enough. It was as if they expected failure. It was much easier to win over the ballplayers. Slowly but surely the fans began to believe in us.\"\n\n<Boudreau:coach#198> led <Jersey City:team#23> to a second place finish in the Sub League 1 East Division. The Wild Dogs ended up with a 74-70 record.\n\n<Boudreau:coach#198> is looking forward to the offseason. \"We\'re reviewing our options. You never stand still in baseball. You either get better or worse, \'cause everyone else is out to get your free agents or deal for your prospects. It\'s going to be a challenge.\" But the skipper has more than proven he is equal to the task.\n"), (1337, "Bingle Captures SL2 Award for Best Manager", 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 32, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 6, 2, 5, 32, 0, 0, "2022-10-28", 0, 1, -1, 0, "<Chris Bingle:coach#231> stepped before the microphone today and accepted his Sub League 2 Manager of the Year award, thanking the whole <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> organization for making the 2022 season such a success.\n\n<Bingle:coach#231> struggled to find the right words. \"My father was a drill instructor in the military. He taught me that you have to work hard, set goals and accept responsibility for your actions. That\'s what the entire <Sioux City:team#32> organization did this year. My dedicated owner, coaching staff, hard-working and talented players and loyal front office all made this award possible. I thank them for it.\"\n\nAnd what a year it was. <Bingle:coach#231> sparked the Apple Sox to a 90-54 record and a first in the Sub League 2 West Division standings.\n"), (1338, "Miles Scores SL1 Best Hurler Honors", 335, 0, 0, 0, 0, 19, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 6, 3, 5, 19, 0, 0, "2022-10-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "The Sub League 1 announced today that <Neil Miles:player#335> has been chosen the Pitcher of the Year Award winner for 2022. The <Greendale:team#19> starter had everything working for him this past season as he breezed to a 7-2 record.\n\nIn his award-winning season Miles crafted a 2.70 ERA in 83.1 innings with 78 strikeouts and 26 walks. Opposing batters hit .197 against him in his 12 starts.\n\nHe received 12 first place votes out of a possible 16. <Tony Tankersley:player#1434> of the <Jersey City Wild Dogs:team#23> finished second in voting with 2 first place votes, while <Greg McGriff:player#940> of the <Chandler Capitals:team#22> finished third.\n\n<Player - Team - First Place - Total Points:value_bold#0>\n<Neil Miles:player#335> - <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> - 12 - 93\n<Tony Tankersley:player#1434> - <Jersey City Wild Dogs:team#23> - 2 - 61\n<Greg McGriff:player#940> - <Chandler Capitals:team#22> - 0 - 42\n<Hector Carranza:player#1640> - <Fort Wayne Blue Falcons:team#21> - 1 - 30\n<Josh Vaughn:player#98> - <Chandler Capitals:team#22> - 0 - 17\n<Juan de Anda:player#1301> - <Chandler Capitals:team#22> - 1 - 14\n<Esteve Reynolds:player#375> - <Greendale Blue Raiders:team#19> - 0 - 7\n<John Aldridge:player#560> - <Grand Rapids Blue Jackets:team#20> - 0 - 5\n<Albert Sandoval:player#788> - <Jersey City Wild Dogs:team#23> - 0 - 1\n<Zack Smith:player#557> - <Grand Rapids Blue Jackets:team#20> - 0 - 1\n<Steve Van Dyke:player#1538> - <North Hempstead Knights:team#24> - 0 - 1\n"), (1339, "SL2 Awards Outstanding Pitcher Trophy", 2053, 0, 0, 0, 0, 32, 0, 0, 0, 0, 201, 0, 3, 6, 3, 5, 32, 0, 0, "2022-10-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "Poise, confidence, and good stuff -- a great combination that brought <Scott Meagher:player#2053> the Sub League 2 Pitcher of the Year Award this year. This <Sioux City:team#32> mound star excelled with an impressive 16-6 mark.\n\nIn 28 starts, <Meagher:player#2053> tossed 184.2 innings, fashioning an impressive 3.02 ERA. He held opposing hitters to a .244 average, struck out 141 and walked 63.\n\nHe received 16 first place votes, as a unanimous winner. <Johnny Esquivel:player#1669> of the <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> finished second in voting, while <Kyle Scott:player#1076> of the <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> finished third.\n\n<Player - Team - First Place - Total Points:value_bold#0>\n<Scott Meagher:player#2053> - <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> - 16 - 112\n<Johnny Esquivel:player#1669> - <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> - 0 - 57\n<Kyle Scott:player#1076> - <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> - 0 - 52\n<Tomas Garza:player#1251> - <Sioux City Apple Sox:team#32> - 0 - 29\n<Bobby King:player#280> - <Donna Whitecaps:team#28> - 0 - 20\n<Jose Dimas:player#1174> - <Leesburg Privateers:team#26> - 0 - 2\n"), (1340, "Walston Makes it Official, Will Retire", 191, 0, 0, 0, 0, 3, 0, 0, 0, 0, 200, 0, 3, 3, 1, 5, 0, 0, 0, "2022-10-29", 0, 1, -1, 0, "His <Memphis T-Bones:team#3> teammates were not terribly surprised when <Tommy Walston:player#191> announced his retirement today.\n\n\nIn a low-key affair, Walston explained his rationale.\n\n\"My aches and pains have caught up with me. They don\'t seem to go away like they used to when I was a kid,\" he said. \"I\'m spending more and more time in the trainer\'s room and less and less time preparing for my next game. I\'ve come to a realization that I\'ve done what I can in this game and spending more time playing baseball is just stealing from my future self.\"\n\n\nWhen asked, the team manager noted \"Tommy has always been an honest man and when he says he\'s done, well, he\'s done.\"\n\n<Walston:player#191> has pitched in 35 games over his career, registering 1 save and a 1-3 won-lost mark. He has an ERA of 4.77 in 54.2 innings and 42 strikeouts.\n"), (1341, "Landreth 